2442  case Builtin::BI__builtin_logl:
2443  case Builtin::BI__builtin_logf128:
2444  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(*this, E,
2445  Intrinsic::log,
2446  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log));

2448  case Builtin::BIlog10:

3078  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isgreater:
3079  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isgreaterequal:
3080  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isless:
3081  case Builtin::BI__builtin_islessequal:
3082  case Builtin::BI__builtin_islessgreater:
3083  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isunordered: {
3084  // Ordered comparisons: we know the arguments to these are matching scalar
3085  // floating point values.
3086  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
3087  // FIXME: for strictfp/IEEE-754 we need to not trap on SNaN here.
3088  Value *LHS = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3089  Value *RHS = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
3090 
3091  switch (BuiltinID) {
3092  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown ordered comparison");
3093  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isgreater:
3094  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpOGT(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3095  break;
3096  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isgreaterequal:
3097  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpOGE(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3098  break;
3099  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isless:
3100  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpOLT(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3101  break;
3102  case Builtin::BI__builtin_islessequal:
3103  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpOLE(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3104  break;
3105  case Builtin::BI__builtin_islessgreater:
3106  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpONE(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3107  break;
3108  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isunordered:
3109  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmpUNO(LHS, RHS, "cmp");
3110  break;
3111  }
3112  // ZExt bool to int type.
3113  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateZExt(LHS, ConvertType(E->getType())));
3114  }
3115  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isnan: {
3116  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
3117  Value *V = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3118  llvm::Type *Ty = V->getType();
3119  const llvm::fltSemantics &Semantics = Ty->getFltSemantics();
3120  if (!Builder.getIsFPConstrained() ||
3121  Builder.getDefaultConstrainedExcept() == fp::ebIgnore ||
3122  !Ty->isIEEE()) {
3123  V = Builder.CreateFCmpUNO(V, V, "cmp");
3124  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateZExt(V, ConvertType(E->getType())));
3125  }
3126 
3127  if (Value *Result = getTargetHooks().testFPKind(V, BuiltinID, Builder, CGM))
3128  return RValue::get(Result);
3129 
3130  // NaN has all exp bits set and a non zero significand. Therefore:
3131  // isnan(V) == ((exp mask - (abs(V) & exp mask)) < 0)
3132  unsigned bitsize = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
3133  llvm::IntegerType *IntTy = Builder.getIntNTy(bitsize);
3134  Value *IntV = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IntTy);
3135  APInt AndMask = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(bitsize);
3136  Value *AbsV =
3137  Builder.CreateAnd(IntV, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, AndMask));
3138  APInt ExpMask = APFloat::getInf(Semantics).bitcastToAPInt();
3139  Value *Sub =
3140  Builder.CreateSub(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, ExpMask), AbsV);
3141  // V = sign bit (Sub) <=> V = (Sub < 0)
3142  V = Builder.CreateLShr(Sub, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, bitsize - 1));
3143  if (bitsize > 32)
3144  V = Builder.CreateTrunc(V, ConvertType(E->getType()));
3145  return RValue::get(V);
3146  }

3318  case Builtin::BIfinite:
3319  case Builtin::BI__finite:
3320  case Builtin::BIfinitef:
3321  case Builtin::BI__finitef:
3322  case Builtin::BIfinitel:
3323  case Builtin::BI__finitel:
3324  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isinf:
3325  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isfinite: {
3326  // isinf(x) --> fabs(x) == infinity
3327  // isfinite(x) --> fabs(x) != infinity
3328  // x != NaN via the ordered compare in either case.
3329  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
3330  Value *V = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3331  llvm::Type *Ty = V->getType();
3332  if (!Builder.getIsFPConstrained() ||
3333  Builder.getDefaultConstrainedExcept() == fp::ebIgnore ||
3334  !Ty->isIEEE()) {
3335  Value *Fabs = EmitFAbs(*this, V);
3336  Constant *Infinity = ConstantFP::getInfinity(V->getType());
3337  CmpInst::Predicate Pred = (BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_isinf)
3338  ? CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ
3339  : CmpInst::FCMP_ONE;
3340  Value *FCmp = Builder.CreateFCmp(Pred, Fabs, Infinity, "cmpinf");
3341  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateZExt(FCmp, ConvertType(E->getType())));
3342  }
3343 
3344  if (Value *Result = getTargetHooks().testFPKind(V, BuiltinID, Builder, CGM))
3345  return RValue::get(Result);
3346 
3347  // Inf values have all exp bits set and a zero significand. Therefore:
3348  // isinf(V) == ((V << 1) == ((exp mask) << 1))
3349  // isfinite(V) == ((V << 1) < ((exp mask) << 1)) using unsigned comparison
3350  unsigned bitsize = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
3351  llvm::IntegerType *IntTy = Builder.getIntNTy(bitsize);
3352  Value *IntV = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IntTy);
3353  Value *Shl1 = Builder.CreateShl(IntV, 1);
3354  const llvm::fltSemantics &Semantics = Ty->getFltSemantics();
3355  APInt ExpMask = APFloat::getInf(Semantics).bitcastToAPInt();
3356  Value *ExpMaskShl1 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, ExpMask.shl(1));
3357  if (BuiltinID == Builtin::BI__builtin_isinf)
3358  V = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Shl1, ExpMaskShl1);
3359  else
3360  V = Builder.CreateICmpULT(Shl1, ExpMaskShl1);
3361  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateZExt(V, ConvertType(E->getType())));
3362  }

3364  case Builtin::BI__builtin_isinf_sign: {
3365  // isinf_sign(x) -> fabs(x) == infinity ? (signbit(x) ? -1 : 1) : 0
3366  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
3367  // FIXME: for strictfp/IEEE-754 we need to not trap on SNaN here.
3368  Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3369  Value *AbsArg = EmitFAbs(*this, Arg);
3370  Value *IsInf = Builder.CreateFCmpOEQ(
3371  AbsArg, ConstantFP::getInfinity(Arg->getType()), "isinf");
3372  Value *IsNeg = EmitSignBit(*this, Arg);
3373 
3374  llvm::Type *IntTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
3375  Value *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(IntTy);
3376  Value *One = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 1);
3377  Value *NegativeOne = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, -1);
3378  Value *SignResult = Builder.CreateSelect(IsNeg, NegativeOne, One);
3379  Value *Result = Builder.CreateSelect(IsInf, SignResult, Zero);

3381  }

3414  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fpclassify: {
3415  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
3416  // FIXME: for strictfp/IEEE-754 we need to not trap on SNaN here.
3417  Value *V = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(5));
3418  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertType(E->getArg(5)->getType());
3419 
3420  // Create Result
3421  BasicBlock *Begin = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3422  BasicBlock *End = createBasicBlock("fpclassify_end", this->CurFn);
3423  Builder.SetInsertPoint(End);
3424  PHINode *Result =
3425  Builder.CreatePHI(ConvertType(E->getArg(0)->getType()), 4,
3426  "fpclassify_result");
3427 
3428  // if (V==0) return FP_ZERO
3429  Builder.SetInsertPoint(Begin);
3430  Value *IsZero = Builder.CreateFCmpOEQ(V, Constant::getNullValue(Ty),
3431  "iszero");
3432  Value *ZeroLiteral = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(4));
3433  BasicBlock *NotZero = createBasicBlock("fpclassify_not_zero", this->CurFn);
3434  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsZero, End, NotZero);
3435  Result->addIncoming(ZeroLiteral, Begin);
3436 
3437  // if (V != V) return FP_NAN
3438  Builder.SetInsertPoint(NotZero);
3439  Value *IsNan = Builder.CreateFCmpUNO(V, V, "cmp");
3440  Value *NanLiteral = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3441  BasicBlock *NotNan = createBasicBlock("fpclassify_not_nan", this->CurFn);
3442  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNan, End, NotNan);
3443  Result->addIncoming(NanLiteral, NotZero);
3444 
3445  // if (fabs(V) == infinity) return FP_INFINITY
3446  Builder.SetInsertPoint(NotNan);
3447  Value *VAbs = EmitFAbs(*this, V);
3448  Value *IsInf =
3449  Builder.CreateFCmpOEQ(VAbs, ConstantFP::getInfinity(V->getType()),
3450  "isinf");
3451  Value *InfLiteral = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
3452  BasicBlock *NotInf = createBasicBlock("fpclassify_not_inf", this->CurFn);
3453  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsInf, End, NotInf);
3454  Result->addIncoming(InfLiteral, NotNan);
3455 
3456  // if (fabs(V) >= MIN_NORMAL) return FP_NORMAL else FP_SUBNORMAL
3457  Builder.SetInsertPoint(NotInf);
3458  APFloat Smallest = APFloat::getSmallestNormalized(
3459  getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(E->getArg(5)->getType()));
3460  Value *IsNormal =
3461  Builder.CreateFCmpUGE(VAbs, ConstantFP::get(V->getContext(), Smallest),
3462  "isnormal");
3463  Value *NormalResult =
3464  Builder.CreateSelect(IsNormal, EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2)),
3465  EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3)));
3466  Builder.CreateBr(End);
3467  Result->addIncoming(NormalResult, NotInf);
3468 
3469  // return Result
3470  Builder.SetInsertPoint(End);
3471  return RValue::get(Result);
3472  }

3636  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemchr: {
3637  // The MSVC runtime library does not provide a definition of wmemchr, so we
3638  // need an inline implementation.
3639  if (!getTarget().getTriple().isOSMSVCRT())
3640  break;
3641 
3642  llvm::Type *WCharTy = ConvertType(getContext().WCharTy);
3643  Value *Str = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3644  Value *Chr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
3645  Value *Size = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
3646 
3647  BasicBlock *Entry = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3648  BasicBlock *CmpEq = createBasicBlock("wmemchr.eq");
3649  BasicBlock *Next = createBasicBlock("wmemchr.next");
3650  BasicBlock *Exit = createBasicBlock("wmemchr.exit");
3651  Value *SizeEq0 = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Size, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0));
3652  Builder.CreateCondBr(SizeEq0, Exit, CmpEq);
3653 
3654  EmitBlock(CmpEq);
3655  PHINode *StrPhi = Builder.CreatePHI(Str->getType(), 2);
3656  StrPhi->addIncoming(Str, Entry);
3657  PHINode *SizePhi = Builder.CreatePHI(SizeTy, 2);
3658  SizePhi->addIncoming(Size, Entry);
3659  CharUnits WCharAlign =
3660  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(getContext().WCharTy);
3661  Value *StrCh = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(WCharTy, StrPhi, WCharAlign);
3662  Value *FoundChr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(WCharTy, StrPhi, 0);
3663  Value *StrEqChr = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(StrCh, Chr);
3664  Builder.CreateCondBr(StrEqChr, Exit, Next);
3665 
3666  EmitBlock(Next);
3667  Value *NextStr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(WCharTy, StrPhi, 1);
3668  Value *NextSize = Builder.CreateSub(SizePhi, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 1));
3669  Value *NextSizeEq0 =
3670  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(NextSize, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0));
3671  Builder.CreateCondBr(NextSizeEq0, Exit, CmpEq);
3672  StrPhi->addIncoming(NextStr, Next);
3673  SizePhi->addIncoming(NextSize, Next);
3674 
3675  EmitBlock(Exit);
3676  PHINode *Ret = Builder.CreatePHI(Str->getType(), 3);
3677  Ret->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Str->getType()), Entry);
3678  Ret->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Str->getType()), Next);
3679  Ret->addIncoming(FoundChr, CmpEq);
3680  return RValue::get(Ret);
3681  }
3682  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcmp: {
3683  // The MSVC runtime library does not provide a definition of wmemcmp, so we
3684  // need an inline implementation.
3685  if (!getTarget().getTriple().isOSMSVCRT())
3686  break;
3687 
3688  llvm::Type *WCharTy = ConvertType(getContext().WCharTy);
3689 
3690  Value *Dst = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3691  Value *Src = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
3692  Value *Size = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
3693 
3694  BasicBlock *Entry = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3695  BasicBlock *CmpGT = createBasicBlock("wmemcmp.gt");
3696  BasicBlock *CmpLT = createBasicBlock("wmemcmp.lt");
3697  BasicBlock *Next = createBasicBlock("wmemcmp.next");
3698  BasicBlock *Exit = createBasicBlock("wmemcmp.exit");
3699  Value *SizeEq0 = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Size, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0));
3700  Builder.CreateCondBr(SizeEq0, Exit, CmpGT);
3701 
3702  EmitBlock(CmpGT);
3703  PHINode *DstPhi = Builder.CreatePHI(Dst->getType(), 2);
3704  DstPhi->addIncoming(Dst, Entry);
3705  PHINode *SrcPhi = Builder.CreatePHI(Src->getType(), 2);
3706  SrcPhi->addIncoming(Src, Entry);
3707  PHINode *SizePhi = Builder.CreatePHI(SizeTy, 2);
3708  SizePhi->addIncoming(Size, Entry);
3709  CharUnits WCharAlign =
3710  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(getContext().WCharTy);
3711  Value *DstCh = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(WCharTy, DstPhi, WCharAlign);
3712  Value *SrcCh = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(WCharTy, SrcPhi, WCharAlign);
3713  Value *DstGtSrc = Builder.CreateICmpUGT(DstCh, SrcCh);
3714  Builder.CreateCondBr(DstGtSrc, Exit, CmpLT);
3715 
3716  EmitBlock(CmpLT);
3717  Value *DstLtSrc = Builder.CreateICmpULT(DstCh, SrcCh);
3718  Builder.CreateCondBr(DstLtSrc, Exit, Next);
3719 
3720  EmitBlock(Next);
3721  Value *NextDst = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(WCharTy, DstPhi, 1);
3722  Value *NextSrc = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(WCharTy, SrcPhi, 1);
3723  Value *NextSize = Builder.CreateSub(SizePhi, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 1));
3724  Value *NextSizeEq0 =
3725  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(NextSize, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0));
3726  Builder.CreateCondBr(NextSizeEq0, Exit, CmpGT);
3727  DstPhi->addIncoming(NextDst, Next);
3728  SrcPhi->addIncoming(NextSrc, Next);
3729  SizePhi->addIncoming(NextSize, Next);
3730 
3731  EmitBlock(Exit);
3732  PHINode *Ret = Builder.CreatePHI(IntTy, 4);
3733  Ret->addIncoming(ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0), Entry);
3734  Ret->addIncoming(ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 1), CmpGT);
3735  Ret->addIncoming(ConstantInt::get(IntTy, -1), CmpLT);
3736  Ret->addIncoming(ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0), Next);
3737  return RValue::get(Ret);
3738  }
3739  case Builtin::BI__builtin_dwarf_cfa: {
3740  // The offset in bytes from the first argument to the CFA.
3741  //
3742  // Why on earth is this in the frontend? Is there any reason at
3743  // all that the backend can't reasonably determine this while
3744  // lowering llvm.eh.dwarf.cfa()?
3745  //
3746  // TODO: If there's a satisfactory reason, add a target hook for
3747  // this instead of hard-coding 0, which is correct for most targets.
3748  int32_t Offset = 0;
3749 
3750  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::eh_dwarf_cfa);
3751  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateCall(F,
3752  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Offset)));
3753  }

3796  case Builtin::BI__builtin_eh_return: {
3797  Value *Int = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3798  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
3799 
3800  llvm::IntegerType *IntTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Int->getType());
3801  assert((IntTy->getBitWidth() == 32 || IntTy->getBitWidth() == 64) &&
3802  "LLVM's __builtin_eh_return only supports 32- and 64-bit variants");
3803  Function *F =
3804  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntTy->getBitWidth() == 32 ? Intrinsic::eh_return_i32
3805  : Intrinsic::eh_return_i64);
3806  Builder.CreateCall(F, {Int, Ptr});
3807  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3808 
3809  // We do need to preserve an insertion point.
3810  EmitBlock(createBasicBlock("builtin_eh_return.cont"));

3817  }
3818  case Builtin::BI__builtin_extend_pointer: {
3819  // Extends a pointer to the size of an _Unwind_Word, which is
3820  // uint64_t on all platforms. Generally this gets poked into a
3821  // register and eventually used as an address, so if the
3822  // addressing registers are wider than pointers and the platform
3823  // doesn't implicitly ignore high-order bits when doing
3824  // addressing, we need to make sure we zext / sext based on
3825  // the platform's expectations.
3826  //
3827  // See: http://gcc.gnu.org/ml/gcc-bugs/2002-02/msg00237.html
3828 
3829  // Cast the pointer to intptr_t.
3830  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3831  Value *Result = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy, "extend.cast");
3832 
3833  // If that's 64 bits, we're done.
3834  if (IntPtrTy->getBitWidth() == 64)
3835  return RValue::get(Result);
3836 
3837  // Otherwise, ask the codegen data what to do.
3838  if (getTargetHooks().extendPointerWithSExt())
3839  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateSExt(Result, Int64Ty, "extend.sext"));
3840  else
3841  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateZExt(Result, Int64Ty, "extend.zext"));
3842  }
3843  case Builtin::BI__builtin_setjmp: {
3844  // Buffer is a void**.
3845  Address Buf = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
3846 
3847  // Store the frame pointer to the setjmp buffer.
3848  Value *FrameAddr = Builder.CreateCall(
3849  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::frameaddress, AllocaInt8PtrTy),
3850  ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0));
3851  Builder.CreateStore(FrameAddr, Buf);
3852 
3853  // Store the stack pointer to the setjmp buffer.
3854  Value *StackAddr =
3855  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::stacksave));
3856  Address StackSaveSlot = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(Buf, 2);
3857  Builder.CreateStore(StackAddr, StackSaveSlot);
3858 
3859  // Call LLVM's EH setjmp, which is lightweight.
3860  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::eh_sjlj_setjmp);
3861  Buf = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Buf, Int8Ty);
3862  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateCall(F, Buf.getPointer()));
3863  }
3864  case Builtin::BI__builtin_longjmp: {
3865  Value *Buf = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
3866  Buf = Builder.CreateBitCast(Buf, Int8PtrTy);
3867 
3868  // Call LLVM's EH longjmp, which is lightweight.
3869  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::eh_sjlj_longjmp), Buf);
3870 
3871  // longjmp doesn't return; mark this as unreachable.
3872  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3873 
3874  // We do need to preserve an insertion point.
3875  EmitBlock(createBasicBlock("longjmp.cont"));
3876 
3877  return RValue::get(nullptr);
3878  }

3883  if (TypeRequiresBuiltinLaunder(CGM, ArgTy))
3884  Ptr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(Ptr);
3885 
3886  return RValue::get(Ptr);

4082  // Look at the argument type to determine whether this is a volatile
4083  // operation. The parameter type is always volatile.
4084  QualType PtrTy = E->getArg(0)->IgnoreImpCasts()->getType();
4085  bool Volatile =
4086  PtrTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType().isVolatileQualified();

4090  Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, Int8Ty->getPointerTo(AddrSpace));
4091  Value *NewVal = Builder.getInt8(1);
4092  Value *Order = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
4093  if (isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)) {
4094  int ord = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)->getZExtValue();

4096  switch (ord) {
4097  case 0: // memory_order_relaxed
4098  default: // invalid order
4099  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, Ptr, NewVal,
4100  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
4101  break;
4102  case 1: // memory_order_consume
4103  case 2: // memory_order_acquire
4104  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, Ptr, NewVal,
4105  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire);
4106  break;
4107  case 3: // memory_order_release
4108  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, Ptr, NewVal,
4109  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release);
4110  break;
4111  case 4: // memory_order_acq_rel
4112 
4113  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, Ptr, NewVal,
4114  llvm::AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease);
4115  break;
4116  case 5: // memory_order_seq_cst
4117  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
4118  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, Ptr, NewVal,
4119  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
4120  break;
4121  }
4122  Result->setVolatile(Volatile);
4123  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Result, "tobool"));
4124  }

4291  case Builtin::BI__builtin_signbit:

4298  case Builtin::BI__warn_memset_zero_len:
4299  return RValue::getIgnored();
4300  case Builtin::BI__annotation: {
4301  // Re-encode each wide string to UTF8 and make an MDString.
4302  SmallVector<Metadata *, 1> Strings;
4303  for (const Expr *Arg : E->arguments()) {
4304  const auto *Str = cast<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenCasts());
4305  assert(Str->getCharByteWidth() == 2);
4306  StringRef WideBytes = Str->getBytes();
4307  std::string StrUtf8;
4308  if (!convertUTF16ToUTF8String(
4309  makeArrayRef(WideBytes.data(), WideBytes.size()), StrUtf8)) {
4310  CGM.ErrorUnsupported(E, "non-UTF16 __annotation argument");
4311  continue;
4312  }
4313  Strings.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(getLLVMContext(), StrUtf8));
4314  }
4315 
4316  // Build and MDTuple of MDStrings and emit the intrinsic call.
4317  llvm::Function *F =
4318  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::codeview_annotation, {});
4319  MDTuple *StrTuple = MDTuple::get(getLLVMContext(), Strings);
4320  Builder.CreateCall(F, MetadataAsValue::get(getLLVMContext(), StrTuple));
4321  return RValue::getIgnored();
4322  }
4323  case Builtin::BI__builtin_annotation: {
4324  llvm::Value *AnnVal = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4325  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::annotation,
4326  AnnVal->getType());
4327 
4328  // Get the annotation string, go through casts. Sema requires this to be a
4329  // non-wide string literal, potentially casted, so the cast<> is safe.
4330  const Expr *AnnotationStrExpr = E->getArg(1)->IgnoreParenCasts();
4331  StringRef Str = cast<StringLiteral>(AnnotationStrExpr)->getString();

4333  EmitAnnotationCall(F, AnnVal, Str, E->getExprLoc(), nullptr));
4334  }
4335  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcb:
4336  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcs:
4337  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addc:
4338  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcl:
4339  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcll:
4340  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcb:
4341  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcs:
4342  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subc:
4343  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcl:
4344  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcll: {
4345 
4346  // We translate all of these builtins from expressions of the form:
4347  // int x = ..., y = ..., carryin = ..., carryout, result;
4348  // result = __builtin_addc(x, y, carryin, &carryout);
4349  //
4350  // to LLVM IR of the form:
4351  //
4352  // %tmp1 = call {i32, i1} @llvm.uadd.with.overflow.i32(i32 %x, i32 %y)
4353  // %tmpsum1 = extractvalue {i32, i1} %tmp1, 0
4354  // %carry1 = extractvalue {i32, i1} %tmp1, 1
4355  // %tmp2 = call {i32, i1} @llvm.uadd.with.overflow.i32(i32 %tmpsum1,
4356  // i32 %carryin)
4357  // %result = extractvalue {i32, i1} %tmp2, 0
4358  // %carry2 = extractvalue {i32, i1} %tmp2, 1
4359  // %tmp3 = or i1 %carry1, %carry2
4360  // %tmp4 = zext i1 %tmp3 to i32
4361  // store i32 %tmp4, i32* %carryout
4362 
4363  // Scalarize our inputs.
4364  llvm::Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4365  llvm::Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
4366  llvm::Value *Carryin = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
4367  Address CarryOutPtr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(3));
4368 
4369  // Decide if we are lowering to a uadd.with.overflow or usub.with.overflow.
4370  llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicId;
4371  switch (BuiltinID) {
4372  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown multiprecision builtin id.");
4373  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcb:
4374  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcs:
4375  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addc:
4376  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcl:
4377  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addcll:
4378  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
4379  break;
4380  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcb:
4381  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcs:
4382  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subc:
4383  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcl:
4384  case Builtin::BI__builtin_subcll:
4385  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
4386  break;
4387  }
4388 
4389  // Construct our resulting LLVM IR expression.
4390  llvm::Value *Carry1;
4391  llvm::Value *Sum1 = EmitOverflowIntrinsic(*this, IntrinsicId,
4392  X, Y, Carry1);
4393  llvm::Value *Carry2;
4394  llvm::Value *Sum2 = EmitOverflowIntrinsic(*this, IntrinsicId,
4395  Sum1, Carryin, Carry2);
4396  llvm::Value *CarryOut = Builder.CreateZExt(Builder.CreateOr(Carry1, Carry2),
4397  X->getType());
4398  Builder.CreateStore(CarryOut, CarryOutPtr);
4399  return RValue::get(Sum2);
4400  }
4401 
4402  case Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow:
4403  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow:
4404  case Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow: {
4405  const clang::Expr *LeftArg = E->getArg(0);
4406  const clang::Expr *RightArg = E->getArg(1);
4407  const clang::Expr *ResultArg = E->getArg(2);
4408 
4409  clang::QualType ResultQTy =
4410  ResultArg->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
4411 
4412  WidthAndSignedness LeftInfo =
4413  getIntegerWidthAndSignedness(CGM.getContext(), LeftArg->getType());
4414  WidthAndSignedness RightInfo =
4415  getIntegerWidthAndSignedness(CGM.getContext(), RightArg->getType());
4416  WidthAndSignedness ResultInfo =
4417  getIntegerWidthAndSignedness(CGM.getContext(), ResultQTy);
4418 
4419  // Handle mixed-sign multiplication as a special case, because adding
4420  // runtime or backend support for our generic irgen would be too expensive.
4421  if (isSpecialMixedSignMultiply(BuiltinID, LeftInfo, RightInfo, ResultInfo))
4422  return EmitCheckedMixedSignMultiply(*this, LeftArg, LeftInfo, RightArg,
4423  RightInfo, ResultArg, ResultQTy,
4424  ResultInfo);
4425 
4426  if (isSpecialUnsignedMultiplySignedResult(BuiltinID, LeftInfo, RightInfo,
4427  ResultInfo))
4428  return EmitCheckedUnsignedMultiplySignedResult(
4429  *this, LeftArg, LeftInfo, RightArg, RightInfo, ResultArg, ResultQTy,
4430  ResultInfo);
4431 
4432  WidthAndSignedness EncompassingInfo =
4433  EncompassingIntegerType({LeftInfo, RightInfo, ResultInfo});
4434 
4435  llvm::Type *EncompassingLLVMTy =
4436  llvm::IntegerType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), EncompassingInfo.Width);
4437 
4438  llvm::Type *ResultLLVMTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(ResultQTy);
4439 
4440  llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicId;
4441  switch (BuiltinID) {
4442  default:
4443  llvm_unreachable("Unknown overflow builtin id.");
4444  case Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow:
4445  IntrinsicId = EncompassingInfo.Signed
4446  ? llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow
4447  : llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
4448  break;
4449  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow:
4450  IntrinsicId = EncompassingInfo.Signed
4451  ? llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow
4452  : llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
4453  break;
4454  case Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow:
4455  IntrinsicId = EncompassingInfo.Signed
4456  ? llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow
4457  : llvm::Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow;
4458  break;
4459  }
4460 
4461  llvm::Value *Left = EmitScalarExpr(LeftArg);
4462  llvm::Value *Right = EmitScalarExpr(RightArg);
4463  Address ResultPtr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(ResultArg);
4464 
4465  // Extend each operand to the encompassing type.
4466  Left = Builder.CreateIntCast(Left, EncompassingLLVMTy, LeftInfo.Signed);
4467  Right = Builder.CreateIntCast(Right, EncompassingLLVMTy, RightInfo.Signed);
4468 
4469  // Perform the operation on the extended values.
4470  llvm::Value *Overflow, *Result;
4471  Result = EmitOverflowIntrinsic(*this, IntrinsicId, Left, Right, Overflow);
4472 
4473  if (EncompassingInfo.Width > ResultInfo.Width) {
4474  // The encompassing type is wider than the result type, so we need to
4475  // truncate it.
4476  llvm::Value *ResultTrunc = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, ResultLLVMTy);
4477 
4478  // To see if the truncation caused an overflow, we will extend
4479  // the result and then compare it to the original result.
4480  llvm::Value *ResultTruncExt = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4481  ResultTrunc, EncompassingLLVMTy, ResultInfo.Signed);
4482  llvm::Value *TruncationOverflow =
4483  Builder.CreateICmpNE(Result, ResultTruncExt);
4484 
4485  Overflow = Builder.CreateOr(Overflow, TruncationOverflow);
4486  Result = ResultTrunc;
4487  }
4488 
4489  // Finally, store the result using the pointer.
4490  bool isVolatile =
4491  ResultArg->getType()->getPointeeType().isVolatileQualified();
4492  Builder.CreateStore(EmitToMemory(Result, ResultQTy), ResultPtr, isVolatile);
4493 
4494  return RValue::get(Overflow);
4495  }
4496 
4497  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uadd_overflow:
4498  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddl_overflow:
4499  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddll_overflow:
4500  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usub_overflow:
4501  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubl_overflow:
4502  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubll_overflow:
4503  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umul_overflow:
4504  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umull_overflow:
4505  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umulll_overflow:
4506  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sadd_overflow:
4507  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddl_overflow:
4508  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddll_overflow:
4509  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssub_overflow:
4510  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubl_overflow:
4511  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubll_overflow:
4512  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smul_overflow:
4513  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smull_overflow:
4514  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smulll_overflow: {
4515 
4516  // We translate all of these builtins directly to the relevant llvm IR node.
4517 
4518  // Scalarize our inputs.
4519  llvm::Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4520  llvm::Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
4521  Address SumOutPtr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(2));
4522 
4523  // Decide which of the overflow intrinsics we are lowering to:
4524  llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicId;
4525  switch (BuiltinID) {
4526  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown overflow builtin id.");
4527  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uadd_overflow:
4528  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddl_overflow:
4529  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddll_overflow:
4530  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
4531  break;
4532  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usub_overflow:
4533  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubl_overflow:
4534  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubll_overflow:
4535  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
4536  break;
4537  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umul_overflow:
4538  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umull_overflow:
4539  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umulll_overflow:
4540  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow;
4541  break;
4542  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sadd_overflow:
4543  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddl_overflow:
4544  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddll_overflow:
4545  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow;
4546  break;
4547  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssub_overflow:
4548  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubl_overflow:
4549  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubll_overflow:
4550  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow;
4551  break;
4552  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smul_overflow:
4553  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smull_overflow:
4554  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smulll_overflow:
4555  IntrinsicId = llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow;
4556  break;
4557  }
4558 
4559 
4560  llvm::Value *Carry;
4561  llvm::Value *Sum = EmitOverflowIntrinsic(*this, IntrinsicId, X, Y, Carry);
4562  Builder.CreateStore(Sum, SumOutPtr);
4563 
4564  return RValue::get(Carry);
4565  }
4566  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addressof:
4567  return RValue::get(EmitLValue(E->getArg(0)).getPointer(*this));
4568  case Builtin::BI__builtin_function_start:
4569  return RValue::get(CGM.GetFunctionStart(
4570  E->getArg(0)->getAsBuiltinConstantDeclRef(CGM.getContext())));
4571  case Builtin::BI__builtin_operator_new:

4573  E->getCallee()->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>(), E, false);
4574  case Builtin::BI__builtin_operator_delete:

4602  case Builtin::BI_InterlockedCompareExchangePointer_nf: {

4605  IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(),
4606  getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()));
4607  llvm::Type *IntPtrType = IntType->getPointerTo();

4610  Builder.CreateBitCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), IntPtrType);

4620  BuiltinID == Builtin::BI_InterlockedCompareExchangePointer_nf ?
4621  AtomicOrdering::Monotonic : AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;

4624  Ordering, Ordering);

4626

4628  0),
4629  RTy));

4769  case Builtin::BIread_pipe:

4771  Value *Arg0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)),
4772  *Arg1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
4773  CGOpenCLRuntime OpenCLRT(CGM);

4775  Value *PacketAlign = OpenCLRT.getPipeElemAlign(E->getArg(0));
4776

4778  unsigned GenericAS =
4779  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic);
4780  llvm::Type *I8PTy = llvm::PointerType::get(
4781  llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getLLVMContext()), GenericAS);

4786  : "__write_pipe_2";

4789  llvm::Type *ArgTys[] = {Arg0->getType(), I8PTy, Int32Ty, Int32Ty};

4791  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);

4793  return RValue::get(

4795  {Arg0, BCast, PacketSize, PacketAlign}));
4796  } else {

4798  "Illegal number of parameters to pipe function");

4800  : "__write_pipe_4";

4807  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);
4808  Value *BCast = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Arg3, I8PTy);

4810  // it to i32.

4812  Arg2 = Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(Arg2, Int32Ty);
4813  return RValue::get(

4815  {Arg0, Arg1, Arg2, BCast, PacketSize, PacketAlign}));
4816  }

4896  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.16.4 Built-in pipe query functions
4897  case Builtin::BIget_pipe_num_packets:
4898  case Builtin::BIget_pipe_max_packets: {
4899  const char *BaseName;
4900  const auto *PipeTy = E->getArg(0)->getType()->castAs<PipeType>();
4901  if (BuiltinID == Builtin::BIget_pipe_num_packets)
4902  BaseName = "__get_pipe_num_packets";
4903  else
4904  BaseName = "__get_pipe_max_packets";
4905  std::string Name = std::string(BaseName) +
4906  std::string(PipeTy->isReadOnly() ? "_ro" : "_wo");
4907 
4908  // Building the generic function prototype.
4909  Value *Arg0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4910  CGOpenCLRuntime OpenCLRT(CGM);
4911  Value *PacketSize = OpenCLRT.getPipeElemSize(E->getArg(0));
4912  Value *PacketAlign = OpenCLRT.getPipeElemAlign(E->getArg(0));
4913  llvm::Type *ArgTys[] = {Arg0->getType(), Int32Ty, Int32Ty};
4914  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4915  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);
4916 
4917  return RValue::get(EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name),
4918  {Arg0, PacketSize, PacketAlign}));
4919  }
4920 
4921  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.9 - Address space qualifier functions.
4922  case Builtin::BIto_global:
4923  case Builtin::BIto_local:
4924  case Builtin::BIto_private: {
4925  auto Arg0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4926  auto NewArgT = llvm::PointerType::get(Int8Ty,
4927  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic));
4928  auto NewRetT = llvm::PointerType::get(Int8Ty,
4929  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(
4930  E->getType()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace()));
4931  auto FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(NewRetT, {NewArgT}, false);
4932  llvm::Value *NewArg;
4933  if (Arg0->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() !=
4934  NewArgT->getPointerAddressSpace())
4935  NewArg = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Arg0, NewArgT);
4936  else
4937  NewArg = Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(Arg0, NewArgT);
4938  auto NewName = std::string("__") + E->getDirectCallee()->getName().str();
4939  auto NewCall =
4940  EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, NewName), {NewArg});
4941  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(NewCall,
4942  ConvertType(E->getType())));
4943  }
4944 
4945  // OpenCL v2.0, s6.13.17 - Enqueue kernel function.
4946  // It contains four different overload formats specified in Table 6.13.17.1.
4947  case Builtin::BIenqueue_kernel: {
4948  StringRef Name; // Generated function call name
4949  unsigned NumArgs = E->getNumArgs();
4950 
4951  llvm::Type *QueueTy = ConvertType(getContext().OCLQueueTy);
4952  llvm::Type *GenericVoidPtrTy = Builder.getInt8PtrTy(
4953  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic));
4954 
4955  llvm::Value *Queue = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
4956  llvm::Value *Flags = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
4957  LValue NDRangeL = EmitAggExprToLValue(E->getArg(2));
4958  llvm::Value *Range = NDRangeL.getAddress(*this).getPointer();
4959  llvm::Type *RangeTy = NDRangeL.getAddress(*this).getType();
4960 
4961  if (NumArgs == 4) {
4962  // The most basic form of the call with parameters:
4963  // queue_t, kernel_enqueue_flags_t, ndrange_t, block(void)
4964  Name = "__enqueue_kernel_basic";
4965  llvm::Type *ArgTys[] = {QueueTy, Int32Ty, RangeTy, GenericVoidPtrTy,
4966  GenericVoidPtrTy};
4967  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4968  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);
4969 
4970  auto Info =
4971  CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().emitOpenCLEnqueuedBlock(*this, E->getArg(3));
4972  llvm::Value *Kernel =
4973  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.Kernel, GenericVoidPtrTy);
4974  llvm::Value *Block =
4975  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.BlockArg, GenericVoidPtrTy);
4976 
4977  AttrBuilder B(Builder.getContext());
4978  B.addByValAttr(NDRangeL.getAddress(*this).getElementType());
4979  llvm::AttributeList ByValAttrSet =
4980  llvm::AttributeList::get(CGM.getModule().getContext(), 3U, B);
4981 
4982  auto RTCall =
4983  EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name, ByValAttrSet),
4984  {Queue, Flags, Range, Kernel, Block});
4985  RTCall->setAttributes(ByValAttrSet);
4986  return RValue::get(RTCall);
4987  }
4988  assert(NumArgs >= 5 && "Invalid enqueue_kernel signature");
4989 
4990  // Create a temporary array to hold the sizes of local pointer arguments
4991  // for the block. \p First is the position of the first size argument.
4992  auto CreateArrayForSizeVar = [=](unsigned First)
4993  -> std::tuple<llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *> {
4994  llvm::APInt ArraySize(32, NumArgs - First);
4995  QualType SizeArrayTy = getContext().getConstantArrayType(
4996  getContext().getSizeType(), ArraySize, nullptr, ArrayType::Normal,
4997  /*IndexTypeQuals=*/0);
4998  auto Tmp = CreateMemTemp(SizeArrayTy, "block_sizes");
4999  llvm::Value *TmpPtr = Tmp.getPointer();
5000  llvm::Value *TmpSize = EmitLifetimeStart(
5001  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Tmp.getElementType()), TmpPtr);
5002  llvm::Value *ElemPtr;
5003  // Each of the following arguments specifies the size of the corresponding
5004  // argument passed to the enqueued block.
5005  auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0);
5006  for (unsigned I = First; I < NumArgs; ++I) {
5007  auto *Index = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, I - First);
5008  auto *GEP = Builder.CreateGEP(Tmp.getElementType(), TmpPtr,
5009  {Zero, Index});
5010  if (I == First)
5011  ElemPtr = GEP;
5012  auto *V =
5013  Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(I)), SizeTy);
5014  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(
5015  V, GEP, CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(SizeTy));
5016  }
5017  return std::tie(ElemPtr, TmpSize, TmpPtr);
5018  };
5019 
5020  // Could have events and/or varargs.
5021  if (E->getArg(3)->getType()->isBlockPointerType()) {
5022  // No events passed, but has variadic arguments.
5023  Name = "__enqueue_kernel_varargs";
5024  auto Info =
5025  CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().emitOpenCLEnqueuedBlock(*this, E->getArg(3));
5026  llvm::Value *Kernel =
5027  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.Kernel, GenericVoidPtrTy);
5028  auto *Block = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.BlockArg, GenericVoidPtrTy);
5029  llvm::Value *ElemPtr, *TmpSize, *TmpPtr;
5030  std::tie(ElemPtr, TmpSize, TmpPtr) = CreateArrayForSizeVar(4);
5031 
5032  // Create a vector of the arguments, as well as a constant value to
5033  // express to the runtime the number of variadic arguments.
5034  llvm::Value *const Args[] = {Queue, Flags,
5035  Range, Kernel,
5036  Block, ConstantInt::get(IntTy, NumArgs - 4),
5037  ElemPtr};
5038  llvm::Type *const ArgTys[] = {
5039  QueueTy, IntTy, RangeTy, GenericVoidPtrTy,
5040  GenericVoidPtrTy, IntTy, ElemPtr->getType()};
5041 
5042  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(Int32Ty, ArgTys, false);
5043  auto Call = RValue::get(
5044  EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name), Args));
5045  if (TmpSize)
5046  EmitLifetimeEnd(TmpSize, TmpPtr);
5047  return Call;
5048  }
5049  // Any calls now have event arguments passed.
5050  if (NumArgs >= 7) {
5051  llvm::Type *EventTy = ConvertType(getContext().OCLClkEventTy);
5052  llvm::PointerType *EventPtrTy = EventTy->getPointerTo(
5053  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic));
5054 
5055  llvm::Value *NumEvents =
5056  Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3)), Int32Ty);
5057 
5058  // Since SemaOpenCLBuiltinEnqueueKernel allows fifth and sixth arguments
5059  // to be a null pointer constant (including `0` literal), we can take it
5060  // into account and emit null pointer directly.
5061  llvm::Value *EventWaitList = nullptr;
5062  if (E->getArg(4)->isNullPointerConstant(
5063  getContext(), Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
5064  EventWaitList = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(EventPtrTy);
5065  } else {
5066  EventWaitList = E->getArg(4)->getType()->isArrayType()
5067  ? EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E->getArg(4)).getPointer()
5068  : EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(4));
5069  // Convert to generic address space.
5070  EventWaitList = Builder.CreatePointerCast(EventWaitList, EventPtrTy);
5071  }
5072  llvm::Value *EventRet = nullptr;
5073  if (E->getArg(5)->isNullPointerConstant(
5074  getContext(), Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
5075  EventRet = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(EventPtrTy);
5076  } else {
5077  EventRet =
5078  Builder.CreatePointerCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(5)), EventPtrTy);
5079  }
5080 
5081  auto Info =
5082  CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().emitOpenCLEnqueuedBlock(*this, E->getArg(6));
5083  llvm::Value *Kernel =
5084  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.Kernel, GenericVoidPtrTy);
5085  llvm::Value *Block =
5086  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.BlockArg, GenericVoidPtrTy);
5087 
5088  std::vector<llvm::Type *> ArgTys = {
5089  QueueTy, Int32Ty, RangeTy, Int32Ty,
5090  EventPtrTy, EventPtrTy, GenericVoidPtrTy, GenericVoidPtrTy};
5091 
5092  std::vector<llvm::Value *> Args = {Queue, Flags, Range,
5093  NumEvents, EventWaitList, EventRet,
5094  Kernel, Block};
5095 
5096  if (NumArgs == 7) {
5097  // Has events but no variadics.
5098  Name = "__enqueue_kernel_basic_events";
5099  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
5100  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);
5101  return RValue::get(
5102  EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name),
5103  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value *>(Args)));
5104  }
5105  // Has event info and variadics
5106  // Pass the number of variadics to the runtime function too.
5107  Args.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, NumArgs - 7));
5108  ArgTys.push_back(Int32Ty);
5109  Name = "__enqueue_kernel_events_varargs";
5110 
5111  llvm::Value *ElemPtr, *TmpSize, *TmpPtr;
5112  std::tie(ElemPtr, TmpSize, TmpPtr) = CreateArrayForSizeVar(7);
5113  Args.push_back(ElemPtr);
5114  ArgTys.push_back(ElemPtr->getType());
5115 
5116  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
5117  Int32Ty, llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type *>(ArgTys), false);
5118  auto Call =
5119  RValue::get(EmitRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name),
5120  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value *>(Args)));
5121  if (TmpSize)
5122  EmitLifetimeEnd(TmpSize, TmpPtr);
5123  return Call;
5124  }
5125  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5126  }
5127  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.17.6 - Kernel query functions need bitcast of block
5128  // parameter.

5224  case Builtin::BI__xray_customevent: {
5225  if (!ShouldXRayInstrumentFunction())
5226  return RValue::getIgnored();
5227

5229  XRayInstrKind::Custom))
5230  return RValue::getIgnored();

5232  if (const auto *XRayAttr = CurFuncDecl->getAttr<XRayInstrumentAttr>())
5233  if (XRayAttr->neverXRayInstrument() && !AlwaysEmitXRayCustomEvents())
5234  return RValue::getIgnored();

5299  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ms_va_copy: {
5300  // Lower this manually. We can't reliably determine whether or not any
5301  // given va_copy() is for a Win64 va_list from the calling convention
5302  // alone, because it's legal to do this from a System V ABI function.
5303  // With opaque pointer types, we won't have enough information in LLVM
5304  // IR to determine this from the argument types, either. Best to do it
5305  // now, while we have enough information.
5306  Address DestAddr = EmitMSVAListRef(E->getArg(0));

5312  Int8PtrTy, DestAddr.getAlignment());

5314  Int8PtrTy, SrcAddr.getAlignment());

5338  // If this is an alias for a lib function (e.g. __builtin_sin), emit
5339  // the call using the normal call path, but using the unmangled
5340  // version of the function name.
5341  if (getContext().BuiltinInfo.isLibFunction(BuiltinID))

5343  CGM.getBuiltinLibFunction(FD, BuiltinID));
5344

5349  cast<llvm::Constant>(EmitScalarExpr(E->getCallee())));

5351  // Check that a call to a target specific builtin has the correct target
5352  // features.
5353  // This is down here to avoid non-target specific builtins, however, if
5354  // generic builtins start to require generic target features then we
5355  // can move this up to the beginning of the function.
5356  checkTargetFeatures(E, FD);
5357 
5358  if (unsigned VectorWidth = getContext().BuiltinInfo.getRequiredVectorWidth(BuiltinID))
5359  LargestVectorWidth = std::max(LargestVectorWidth, VectorWidth);
5360 
5361  // See if we have a target specific intrinsic.
5362  const char *Name = getContext().BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinID);
5363  Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
5364  StringRef Prefix =
5365  llvm::Triple::getArchTypePrefix(getTarget().getTriple().getArch());
5366  if (!Prefix.empty()) {
5367  IntrinsicID = Intrinsic::getIntrinsicForGCCBuiltin(Prefix.data(), Name);
5368  // NOTE we don't need to perform a compatibility flag check here since the
5369  // intrinsics are declared in Builtins*.def via LANGBUILTIN which filter the
5370  // MS builtins via ALL_MS_LANGUAGES and are filtered earlier.
5371  if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::not_intrinsic)
5372  IntrinsicID = Intrinsic::getIntrinsicForMSBuiltin(Prefix.data(), Name);
5373  }
5374 
5375  if (IntrinsicID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
5376  SmallVector<Value*, 16> Args;
5377 
5378  // Find out if any arguments are required to be integer constant
5379  // expressions.
5380  unsigned ICEArguments = 0;
5381  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error;
5382  getContext().GetBuiltinType(BuiltinID, Error, &ICEArguments);
5383  assert(Error == ASTContext::GE_None && "Should not codegen an error");
5384 
5385  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID);
5386  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = F->getFunctionType();
5387 
5388  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
5389  Value *ArgValue;
5390  // If this is a normal argument, just emit it as a scalar.
5391  if ((ICEArguments & (1 << i)) == 0) {
5392  ArgValue = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i));
5393  } else {
5394  // If this is required to be a constant, constant fold it so that we
5395  // know that the generated intrinsic gets a ConstantInt.
5396  ArgValue = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5397  getLLVMContext(),
5398  *E->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext()));
5399  }
5400 
5401  // If the intrinsic arg type is different from the builtin arg type
5402  // we need to do a bit cast.
5403  llvm::Type *PTy = FTy->getParamType(i);
5404  if (PTy != ArgValue->getType()) {
5405  // XXX - vector of pointers?
5406  if (auto *PtrTy = dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(PTy)) {
5407  if (PtrTy->getAddressSpace() !=
5408  ArgValue->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
5409  ArgValue = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
5410  ArgValue,
5411  ArgValue->getType()->getPointerTo(PtrTy->getAddressSpace()));
5412  }
5413  }
5414 
5415  assert(PTy->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(FTy->getParamType(i)) &&
5416  "Must be able to losslessly bit cast to param");
5417  ArgValue = Builder.CreateBitCast(ArgValue, PTy);
5418  }
5419 
5420  Args.push_back(ArgValue);
5421  }
5422 
5423  Value *V = Builder.CreateCall(F, Args);
5424  QualType BuiltinRetType = E->getType();
5425 
5426  llvm::Type *RetTy = VoidTy;
5427  if (!BuiltinRetType->isVoidType())
5428  RetTy = ConvertType(BuiltinRetType);
5429 
5430  if (RetTy != V->getType()) {
5431  // XXX - vector of pointers?
5432  if (auto *PtrTy = dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(RetTy)) {
5433  if (PtrTy->getAddressSpace() != V->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
5434  V = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
5435  V, V->getType()->getPointerTo(PtrTy->getAddressSpace()));
5436  }
5437  }
5438 
5439  assert(V->getType()->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(RetTy) &&
5440  "Must be able to losslessly bit cast result type");
5441  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, RetTy);
5442  }
5443 
5444  return RValue::get(V);
5445  }
5446 
5447  // Some target-specific builtins can have aggregate return values, e.g.
5448  // __builtin_arm_mve_vld2q_u32. So if the result is an aggregate, force
5449  // ReturnValue to be non-null, so that the target-specific emission code can
5450  // always just emit into it.
5451  TypeEvaluationKind EvalKind = getEvaluationKind(E->getType());
5452  if (EvalKind == TEK_Aggregate && ReturnValue.isNull()) {
5453  Address DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(E->getType(), "agg.tmp");
5454  ReturnValue = ReturnValueSlot(DestPtr, false);
5455  }
5456 
5457  // Now see if we can emit a target-specific builtin.
5458  if (Value *V = EmitTargetBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue)) {
5459  switch (EvalKind) {
5460  case TEK_Scalar:
5461  return RValue::get(V);
5462  case TEK_Aggregate:
5463  return RValue::getAggregate(ReturnValue.getValue(),
5464  ReturnValue.isVolatile());
5465  case TEK_Complex:
5466  llvm_unreachable("No current target builtin returns complex");
5467  }
5468  llvm_unreachable("Bad evaluation kind in EmitBuiltinExpr");
5469  }
5470 
5471  ErrorUnsupported(E, "builtin function");
5472 
5473  // Unknown builtin, for now just dump it out and return undef.
5474  return GetUndefRValue(E->getType());
5475 }
5476 
5477 static Value *EmitTargetArchBuiltinExpr(CodeGenFunction *CGF,
5478  unsigned BuiltinID, const CallExpr *E,
5479  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
5480  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
5481  switch (Arch) {
5482  case llvm::Triple::arm:
5483  case llvm::Triple::armeb:
5484  case llvm::Triple::thumb:
5485  case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
5486  return CGF->EmitARMBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue, Arch);
5487  case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
5488  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_32:
5489  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
5490  return CGF->EmitAArch64BuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, Arch);
5491  case llvm::Triple::bpfeb:
5492  case llvm::Triple::bpfel:
5493  return CGF->EmitBPFBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5494  case llvm::Triple::x86:
5495  case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
5496  return CGF->EmitX86BuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5497  case llvm::Triple::ppc:
5498  case llvm::Triple::ppcle:
5499  case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
5500  case llvm::Triple::ppc64le:
5501  return CGF->EmitPPCBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5502  case llvm::Triple::r600:
5503  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
5504  return CGF->EmitAMDGPUBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5505  case llvm::Triple::systemz:
5506  return CGF->EmitSystemZBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5507  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
5508  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
5509  return CGF->EmitNVPTXBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5510  case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
5511  case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
5512  return CGF->EmitWebAssemblyBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5513  case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
5514  return CGF->EmitHexagonBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
5515  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
5516  case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
5517  return CGF->EmitRISCVBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue);
5518  default:
5519  return nullptr;
5520  }
5521 }
5522 
5523 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitTargetBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
5524  const CallExpr *E,
5525  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
5526  if (getContext().BuiltinInfo.isAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID)) {
5527  assert(getContext().getAuxTargetInfo() && "Missing aux target info");
5528  return EmitTargetArchBuiltinExpr(
5529  this, getContext().BuiltinInfo.getAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID), E,
5530  ReturnValue, getContext().getAuxTargetInfo()->getTriple().getArch());
5531  }
5532 
5533  return EmitTargetArchBuiltinExpr(this, BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue,
5534  getTarget().getTriple().getArch());
5535 }
5536 
5537 static llvm::FixedVectorType *GetNeonType(CodeGenFunction *CGF,
5538  NeonTypeFlags TypeFlags,
5539  bool HasLegalHalfType = true,
5540  bool V1Ty = false,
5541  bool AllowBFloatArgsAndRet = true) {
5542  int IsQuad = TypeFlags.isQuad();
5543  switch (TypeFlags.getEltType()) {
5544  case NeonTypeFlags::Int8:
5545  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly8:
5546  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int8Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (8 << IsQuad));
5547  case NeonTypeFlags::Int16:
5548  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly16:
5549  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int16Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (4 << IsQuad));
5550  case NeonTypeFlags::BFloat16:
5551  if (AllowBFloatArgsAndRet)
5552  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->BFloatTy, V1Ty ? 1 : (4 << IsQuad));
5553  else
5554  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int16Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (4 << IsQuad));
5555  case NeonTypeFlags::Float16:
5556  if (HasLegalHalfType)
5557  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->HalfTy, V1Ty ? 1 : (4 << IsQuad));
5558  else
5559  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int16Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (4 << IsQuad));
5560  case NeonTypeFlags::Int32:
5561  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int32Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (2 << IsQuad));
5562  case NeonTypeFlags::Int64:
5563  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly64:
5564  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int64Ty, V1Ty ? 1 : (1 << IsQuad));
5565  case NeonTypeFlags::Poly128:
5566  // FIXME: i128 and f128 doesn't get fully support in Clang and llvm.
5567  // There is a lot of i128 and f128 API missing.
5568  // so we use v16i8 to represent poly128 and get pattern matched.
5569  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->Int8Ty, 16);
5570  case NeonTypeFlags::Float32:
5571  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->FloatTy, V1Ty ? 1 : (2 << IsQuad));
5572  case NeonTypeFlags::Float64:
5573  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->DoubleTy, V1Ty ? 1 : (1 << IsQuad));
5574  }
5575  llvm_unreachable("Unknown vector element type!");
5576 }
5577 
5578 static llvm::VectorType *GetFloatNeonType(CodeGenFunction *CGF,
5579  NeonTypeFlags IntTypeFlags) {
5580  int IsQuad = IntTypeFlags.isQuad();
5581  switch (IntTypeFlags.getEltType()) {
5582  case NeonTypeFlags::Int16:
5583  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->HalfTy, (4 << IsQuad));
5584  case NeonTypeFlags::Int32:
5585  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->FloatTy, (2 << IsQuad));
5586  case NeonTypeFlags::Int64:
5587  return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF->DoubleTy, (1 << IsQuad));
5588  default:
5589  llvm_unreachable("Type can't be converted to floating-point!");
5590  }
5591 }
5592 
5593 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNeonSplat(Value *V, Constant *C,
5594  const ElementCount &Count) {
5595  Value *SV = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(Count, C);
5596  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, V, SV, "lane");
5597 }
5598 
5599 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNeonSplat(Value *V, Constant *C) {
5600  ElementCount EC = cast<llvm::VectorType>(V->getType())->getElementCount();
5601  return EmitNeonSplat(V, C, EC);
5602 }
5603 
5604 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNeonCall(Function *F, SmallVectorImpl<Value*> &Ops,
5605  const char *name,
5606  unsigned shift, bool rightshift) {
5607  unsigned j = 0;
5608  for (Function::const_arg_iterator ai = F->arg_begin(), ae = F->arg_end();
5609  ai != ae; ++ai, ++j) {
5610  if (F->isConstrainedFPIntrinsic())
5611  if (ai->getType()->isMetadataTy())
5612  continue;
5613  if (shift > 0 && shift == j)
5614  Ops[j] = EmitNeonShiftVector(Ops[j], ai->getType(), rightshift);
5615  else
5616  Ops[j] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[j], ai->getType(), name);
5617  }
5618 
5619  if (F->isConstrainedFPIntrinsic())
5620  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, Ops, name);
5621  else
5622  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, name);
5623 }
5624 
5625 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNeonShiftVector(Value *V, llvm::Type *Ty,
5626  bool neg) {
5627  int SV = cast<ConstantInt>(V)->getSExtValue();
5628  return ConstantInt::get(Ty, neg ? -SV : SV);
5629 }
5630 
5631 // Right-shift a vector by a constant.
5632 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNeonRShiftImm(Value *Vec, Value *Shift,
5633  llvm::Type *Ty, bool usgn,
5634  const char *name) {
5635  llvm::VectorType *VTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ty);
5636 
5637  int ShiftAmt = cast<ConstantInt>(Shift)->getSExtValue();
5638  int EltSize = VTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
5639 
5640  Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, Ty);
5641 
5642  // lshr/ashr are undefined when the shift amount is equal to the vector
5643  // element size.
5644  if (ShiftAmt == EltSize) {
5645  if (usgn) {
5646  // Right-shifting an unsigned value by its size yields 0.
5647  return llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(VTy);
5648  } else {
5649  // Right-shifting a signed value by its size is equivalent
5650  // to a shift of size-1.
5651  --ShiftAmt;
5652  Shift = ConstantInt::get(VTy->getElementType(), ShiftAmt);
5653  }
5654  }
5655 
5656  Shift = EmitNeonShiftVector(Shift, Ty, false);
5657  if (usgn)
5658  return Builder.CreateLShr(Vec, Shift, name);
5659  else
5660  return Builder.CreateAShr(Vec, Shift, name);
5661 }
5662 
5663 enum {
5664  AddRetType = (1 << 0),
5665  Add1ArgType = (1 << 1),
5666  Add2ArgTypes = (1 << 2),
5667 
5668  VectorizeRetType = (1 << 3),
5669  VectorizeArgTypes = (1 << 4),
5670 
5671  InventFloatType = (1 << 5),
5672  UnsignedAlts = (1 << 6),
5673 
5674  Use64BitVectors = (1 << 7),
5675  Use128BitVectors = (1 << 8),
5676 
5677  Vectorize1ArgType = Add1ArgType | VectorizeArgTypes,
5678  VectorRet = AddRetType | VectorizeRetType,
5679  VectorRetGetArgs01 =
5680  AddRetType | Add2ArgTypes | VectorizeRetType | VectorizeArgTypes,
5681  FpCmpzModifiers =
5682  AddRetType | VectorizeRetType | Add1ArgType | InventFloatType
5683 };

5688  unsigned BuiltinID;

5691  uint64_t TypeModifier;
5692 
5693  bool operator<(unsigned RHSBuiltinID) const {
5694  return BuiltinID < RHSBuiltinID;
5695  }
5696  bool operator<(const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo &TE) const {
5697  return BuiltinID < TE.BuiltinID;
5698  }
5699 };

6484  { \

6486  TypeModifier \

6491 static const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo AArch64SVEIntrinsicMap[] = {
6492 #define GET_SVE_LLVM_INTRINSIC_MAP
6493 #include "clang/Basic/arm_sve_builtin_cg.inc"
6494 #include "clang/Basic/BuiltinsAArch64NeonSVEBridge_cg.def"
6495 #undef GET_SVE_LLVM_INTRINSIC_MAP

6500 
6501 static bool NEONSIMDIntrinsicsProvenSorted = false;
6502 
6503 static bool AArch64SIMDIntrinsicsProvenSorted = false;
6504 static bool AArch64SISDIntrinsicsProvenSorted = false;
6505 static bool AArch64SVEIntrinsicsProvenSorted = false;
6506 
6507 static const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo *
6508 findARMVectorIntrinsicInMap(ArrayRef<ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo> IntrinsicMap,
6509  unsigned BuiltinID, bool &MapProvenSorted) {
6510 
6511 #ifndef NDEBUG
6512  if (!MapProvenSorted) {
6513  assert(llvm::is_sorted(IntrinsicMap));
6514  MapProvenSorted = true;
6515  }
6516 #endif
6517 
6518  const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo *Builtin =
6519  llvm::lower_bound(IntrinsicMap, BuiltinID);
6520 
6521  if (Builtin != IntrinsicMap.end() && Builtin->BuiltinID == BuiltinID)
6522  return Builtin;
6523 
6524  return nullptr;
6525 }
6526 
6527 Function *CodeGenFunction::LookupNeonLLVMIntrinsic(unsigned IntrinsicID,
6528  unsigned Modifier,
6529  llvm::Type *ArgType,
6530  const CallExpr *E) {
6531  int VectorSize = 0;
6532  if (Modifier & Use64BitVectors)
6533  VectorSize = 64;
6534  else if (Modifier & Use128BitVectors)
6535  VectorSize = 128;
6536 
6537  // Return type.
6538  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> Tys;
6539  if (Modifier & AddRetType) {
6540  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertType(E->getCallReturnType(getContext()));
6541  if (Modifier & VectorizeRetType)
6542  Ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
6543  Ty, VectorSize ? VectorSize / Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() : 1);
6544 
6545  Tys.push_back(Ty);
6546  }
6547 
6548  // Arguments.
6549  if (Modifier & VectorizeArgTypes) {
6550  int Elts = VectorSize ? VectorSize / ArgType->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() : 1;
6551  ArgType = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ArgType, Elts);
6552  }
6553 
6554  if (Modifier & (Add1ArgType | Add2ArgTypes))
6555  Tys.push_back(ArgType);
6556 
6557  if (Modifier & Add2ArgTypes)
6558  Tys.push_back(ArgType);
6559 
6560  if (Modifier & InventFloatType)
6561  Tys.push_back(FloatTy);
6562 
6563  return CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, Tys);
6564 }
6565 
6566 static Value *EmitCommonNeonSISDBuiltinExpr(
6567  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo &SISDInfo,
6568  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops, const CallExpr *E) {
6569  unsigned BuiltinID = SISDInfo.BuiltinID;
6570  unsigned int Int = SISDInfo.LLVMIntrinsic;
6571  unsigned Modifier = SISDInfo.TypeModifier;
6572  const char *s = SISDInfo.NameHint;
6573 
6574  switch (BuiltinID) {
6575  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcled_s64:
6576  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcled_u64:
6577  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcles_f32:
6578  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcled_f64:
6579  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcltd_s64:
6580  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcltd_u64:
6581  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vclts_f32:
6582  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcltd_f64:
6583  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcales_f32:
6584  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcaled_f64:
6585  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcalts_f32:
6586  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcaltd_f64:
6587  // Only one direction of comparisons actually exist, cmle is actually a cmge
6588  // with swapped operands. The table gives us the right intrinsic but we
6589  // still need to do the swap.
6590  std::swap(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
6591  break;
6592  }
6593 
6594  assert(Int && "Generic code assumes a valid intrinsic");
6595 
6596  // Determine the type(s) of this overloaded AArch64 intrinsic.
6597  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(0);
6598  llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGF.ConvertType(Arg->getType());
6599  Function *F = CGF.LookupNeonLLVMIntrinsic(Int, Modifier, ArgTy, E);
6600 
6601  int j = 0;
6602  ConstantInt *C0 = ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, 0);
6603  for (Function::const_arg_iterator ai = F->arg_begin(), ae = F->arg_end();
6604  ai != ae; ++ai, ++j) {
6605  llvm::Type *ArgTy = ai->getType();
6606  if (Ops[j]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() ==
6607  ArgTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits())
6608  continue;
6609 
6610  assert(ArgTy->isVectorTy() && !Ops[j]->getType()->isVectorTy());
6611  // The constant argument to an _n_ intrinsic always has Int32Ty, so truncate
6612  // it before inserting.
6613  Ops[j] = CGF.Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(
6614  Ops[j], cast<llvm::VectorType>(ArgTy)->getElementType());
6615  Ops[j] =
6616  CGF.Builder.CreateInsertElement(UndefValue::get(ArgTy), Ops[j], C0);
6617  }
6618 
6619  Value *Result = CGF.EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, s);
6620  llvm::Type *ResultType = CGF.ConvertType(E->getType());
6621  if (ResultType->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedSize() <
6622  Result->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedSize())
6623  return CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Result, C0);
6624 
6625  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Result, ResultType, s);
6626 }
6627 
6628 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCommonNeonBuiltinExpr(
6629  unsigned BuiltinID, unsigned LLVMIntrinsic, unsigned AltLLVMIntrinsic,
6630  const char *NameHint, unsigned Modifier, const CallExpr *E,
6631  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Value *> &Ops, Address PtrOp0, Address PtrOp1,
6632  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
6633  // Get the last argument, which specifies the vector type.
6634  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(E->getNumArgs() - 1);
6635  Optional<llvm::APSInt> NeonTypeConst =
6636  Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
6637  if (!NeonTypeConst)
6638  return nullptr;
6639 
6640  // Determine the type of this overloaded NEON intrinsic.
6641  NeonTypeFlags Type(NeonTypeConst->getZExtValue());
6642  bool Usgn = Type.isUnsigned();
6643  bool Quad = Type.isQuad();
6644  const bool HasLegalHalfType = getTarget().hasLegalHalfType();
6645  const bool AllowBFloatArgsAndRet =
6646  getTargetHooks().getABIInfo().allowBFloatArgsAndRet();
6647 
6648  llvm::FixedVectorType *VTy =
6649  GetNeonType(this, Type, HasLegalHalfType, false, AllowBFloatArgsAndRet);
6650  llvm::Type *Ty = VTy;
6651  if (!Ty)
6652  return nullptr;
6653 
6654  auto getAlignmentValue32 = [&](Address addr) -> Value* {
6655  return Builder.getInt32(addr.getAlignment().getQuantity());
6656  };
6657 
6658  unsigned Int = LLVMIntrinsic;
6659  if ((Modifier & UnsignedAlts) && !Usgn)
6660  Int = AltLLVMIntrinsic;
6661 
6662  switch (BuiltinID) {
6663  default: break;
6664  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splat_lane_v:
6665  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splat_laneq_v:
6666  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splatq_lane_v:
6667  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splatq_laneq_v: {
6668  auto NumElements = VTy->getElementCount();
6669  if (BuiltinID == NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splatq_lane_v)
6670  NumElements = NumElements * 2;
6671  if (BuiltinID == NEON::BI__builtin_neon_splat_laneq_v)
6672  NumElements = NumElements.divideCoefficientBy(2);
6673 
6674  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], VTy);
6675  return EmitNeonSplat(Ops[0], cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1]), NumElements);
6676  }
6677  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vpadd_v:
6678  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vpaddq_v:
6679  // We don't allow fp/int overloading of intrinsics.
6680  if (VTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy() &&
6681  Int == Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_addp)
6682  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_faddp;
6683  break;
6684  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vabs_v:
6685  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vabsq_v:
6686  if (VTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
6687  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, Ty), Ops, "vabs");
6688  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Ty), Ops, "vabs");
6689  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vadd_v:
6690  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vaddq_v: {
6691  llvm::Type *VTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int8Ty, Quad ? 16 : 8);
6692  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], VTy);
6693  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], VTy);
6694  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateXor(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
6695  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6696  }
6697  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vaddhn_v: {
6698  llvm::FixedVectorType *SrcTy =
6699  llvm::FixedVectorType::getExtendedElementVectorType(VTy);
6700 
6701  // %sum = add <4 x i32> %lhs, %rhs
6702  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], SrcTy);
6703  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], SrcTy);
6704  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateAdd(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vaddhn");
6705 
6706  // %high = lshr <4 x i32> %sum, <i32 16, i32 16, i32 16, i32 16>
6707  Constant *ShiftAmt =
6708  ConstantInt::get(SrcTy, SrcTy->getScalarSizeInBits() / 2);
6709  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateLShr(Ops[0], ShiftAmt, "vaddhn");
6710 
6711  // %res = trunc <4 x i32> %high to <4 x i16>
6712  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[0], VTy, "vaddhn");
6713  }
6714  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcale_v:
6715  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcaleq_v:
6716  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcalt_v:
6717  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcaltq_v:
6718  std::swap(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
6719  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
6720  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcage_v:
6721  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcageq_v:
6722  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcagt_v:
6723  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcagtq_v: {
6724  llvm::Type *Ty;
6725  switch (VTy->getScalarSizeInBits()) {
6726  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected type");
6727  case 32:
6728  Ty = FloatTy;
6729  break;
6730  case 64:
6731  Ty = DoubleTy;
6732  break;
6733  case 16:
6734  Ty = HalfTy;
6735  break;
6736  }
6737  auto *VecFlt = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Ty, VTy->getNumElements());
6738  llvm::Type *Tys[] = { VTy, VecFlt };
6739  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys);
6740  return EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, NameHint);
6741  }
6742  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vceqz_v:
6743  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vceqzq_v:
6744  return EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(Ops[0], Ty, ICmpInst::FCMP_OEQ,
6745  ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, "vceqz");
6746  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcgez_v:
6747  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcgezq_v:
6748  return EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(Ops[0], Ty, ICmpInst::FCMP_OGE,
6749  ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, "vcgez");
6750  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vclez_v:
6751  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vclezq_v:
6752  return EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(Ops[0], Ty, ICmpInst::FCMP_OLE,
6753  ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE, "vclez");
6754  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcgtz_v:
6755  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcgtzq_v:
6756  return EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(Ops[0], Ty, ICmpInst::FCMP_OGT,
6757  ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, "vcgtz");
6758  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcltz_v:
6759  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcltzq_v:
6760  return EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(Ops[0], Ty, ICmpInst::FCMP_OLT,
6761  ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, "vcltz");
6762  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vclz_v:
6763  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vclzq_v:
6764  // We generate target-independent intrinsic, which needs a second argument
6765  // for whether or not clz of zero is undefined; on ARM it isn't.
6766  Ops.push_back(Builder.getInt1(getTarget().isCLZForZeroUndef()));
6767  break;
6768  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_f32_v:
6769  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_f32_v:
6770  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6771  Ty = GetNeonType(this, NeonTypeFlags(NeonTypeFlags::Float32, false, Quad),
6772  HasLegalHalfType);
6773  return Usgn ? Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt")
6774  : Builder.CreateSIToFP(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt");
6775  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_f16_v:
6776  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_f16_v:
6777  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6778  Ty = GetNeonType(this, NeonTypeFlags(NeonTypeFlags::Float16, false, Quad),
6779  HasLegalHalfType);
6780  return Usgn ? Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt")
6781  : Builder.CreateSIToFP(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt");
6782  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_f16_v:
6783  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_f32_v:
6784  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_f64_v:
6785  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_f16_v:
6786  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_f32_v:
6787  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_f64_v: {
6788  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { GetFloatNeonType(this, Type), Ty };
6789  Int = Usgn ? LLVMIntrinsic : AltLLVMIntrinsic;
6790  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Tys);
6791  return EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, "vcvt_n");
6792  }
6793  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_s16_v:
6794  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_s32_v:
6795  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_u16_v:
6796  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_u32_v:
6797  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_s64_v:
6798  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_n_u64_v:
6799  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_s16_v:
6800  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_s32_v:
6801  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_u16_v:
6802  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_u32_v:
6803  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_s64_v:
6804  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_n_u64_v: {
6805  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { Ty, GetFloatNeonType(this, Type) };
6806  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys);
6807  return EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, "vcvt_n");
6808  }
6809  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_s32_v:
6810  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_u32_v:
6811  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_s64_v:
6812  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_u64_v:
6813  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_s16_v:
6814  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvt_u16_v:
6815  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_s32_v:
6816  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_u32_v:
6817  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_s64_v:
6818  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_u64_v:
6819  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_s16_v:
6820  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtq_u16_v: {
6821  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], GetFloatNeonType(this, Type));
6822  return Usgn ? Builder.CreateFPToUI(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt")
6823  : Builder.CreateFPToSI(Ops[0], Ty, "vcvt");
6824  }
6825  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_s16_v:
6826  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_s32_v:
6827  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_s64_v:
6828  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_u16_v:
6829  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_u32_v:
6830  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvta_u64_v:
6831  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_s16_v:
6832  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_s32_v:
6833  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_s64_v:
6834  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_u16_v:
6835  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_u32_v:
6836  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtaq_u64_v:
6837  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_s16_v:
6838  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_s32_v:
6839  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_s64_v:
6840  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_u16_v:
6841  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_u32_v:
6842  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtn_u64_v:
6843  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_s16_v:
6844  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_s32_v:
6845  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_s64_v:
6846  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_u16_v:
6847  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_u32_v:
6848  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnq_u64_v:
6849  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_s16_v:
6850  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_s32_v:
6851  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_s64_v:
6852  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_u16_v:
6853  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_u32_v:
6854  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtp_u64_v:
6855  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_s16_v:
6856  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_s32_v:
6857  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_s64_v:
6858  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_u16_v:
6859  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_u32_v:
6860  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtpq_u64_v:
6861  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_s16_v:
6862  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_s32_v:
6863  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_s64_v:
6864  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_u16_v:
6865  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_u32_v:
6866  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtm_u64_v:
6867  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_s16_v:
6868  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_s32_v:
6869  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_s64_v:
6870  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_u16_v:
6871  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_u32_v:
6872  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmq_u64_v: {
6873  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { Ty, GetFloatNeonType(this, Type) };
6874  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys), Ops, NameHint);
6875  }
6876  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtx_f32_v: {
6877  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy->getTruncatedElementVectorType(VTy), Ty};
6878  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys), Ops, NameHint);
6879 
6880  }
6881  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vext_v:
6882  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vextq_v: {
6883  int CV = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getSExtValue();
6884  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
6885  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
6886  Indices.push_back(i+CV);
6887 
6888  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6889  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
6890  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[1], Indices, "vext");
6891  }
6892  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfma_v:
6893  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfmaq_v: {
6894  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6895  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
6896  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
6897 
6898  // NEON intrinsic puts accumulator first, unlike the LLVM fma.
6899  return emitCallMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
6900  *this, Intrinsic::fma, Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, Ty,
6901  {Ops[1], Ops[2], Ops[0]});
6902  }
6903  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_v:
6904  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_v: {
6905  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Ty, Int8PtrTy};
6906  Ops.push_back(getAlignmentValue32(PtrOp0));
6907  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys), Ops, "vld1");
6908  }
6909  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_x2_v:
6910  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_x2_v:
6911  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_x3_v:
6912  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_x3_v:
6913  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_x4_v:
6914  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_x4_v: {
6915  llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
6916  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
6917  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
6918  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys);
6919  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[1], "vld1xN");
6920  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
6921  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6922  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
6923  }
6924  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_v:
6925  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_v:
6926  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_v:
6927  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_v:
6928  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_v:
6929  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_v:
6930  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_dup_v:
6931  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_dup_v:
6932  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_dup_v:
6933  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_dup_v:
6934  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_dup_v:
6935  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_dup_v: {
6936  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Ty, Int8PtrTy};
6937  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys);
6938  Value *Align = getAlignmentValue32(PtrOp1);
6939  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[1], Align}, NameHint);
6940  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
6941  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6942  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
6943  }
6944  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_dup_v:
6945  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_dup_v: {
6946  Value *V = UndefValue::get(Ty);
6947  PtrOp0 = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(PtrOp0, VTy->getElementType());
6948  LoadInst *Ld = Builder.CreateLoad(PtrOp0);
6949  llvm::Constant *CI = ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0);
6950  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Ld, CI);
6951  return EmitNeonSplat(Ops[0], CI);
6952  }
6953  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_lane_v:
6954  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_lane_v:
6955  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_lane_v:
6956  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_lane_v:
6957  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_lane_v:
6958  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_lane_v: {
6959  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Ty, Int8PtrTy};
6960  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(LLVMIntrinsic, Tys);
6961  for (unsigned I = 2; I < Ops.size() - 1; ++I)
6962  Ops[I] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[I], Ty);
6963  Ops.push_back(getAlignmentValue32(PtrOp1));
6964  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1), NameHint);
6965  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
6966  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
6967  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
6968  }
6969  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vmovl_v: {
6970  llvm::FixedVectorType *DTy =
6971  llvm::FixedVectorType::getTruncatedElementVectorType(VTy);
6972  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], DTy);
6973  if (Usgn)
6974  return Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[0], Ty, "vmovl");
6975  return Builder.CreateSExt(Ops[0], Ty, "vmovl");
6976  }
6977  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vmovn_v: {
6978  llvm::FixedVectorType *QTy =
6979  llvm::FixedVectorType::getExtendedElementVectorType(VTy);
6980  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], QTy);
6981  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[0], Ty, "vmovn");
6982  }
6983  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vmull_v:
6984  // FIXME: the integer vmull operations could be emitted in terms of pure
6985  // LLVM IR (2 exts followed by a mul). Unfortunately LLVM has a habit of
6986  // hoisting the exts outside loops. Until global ISel comes along that can
6987  // see through such movement this leads to bad CodeGen. So we need an
6988  // intrinsic for now.
6989  Int = Usgn ? Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmullu : Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmulls;
6990  Int = Type.isPoly() ? (unsigned)Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmullp : Int;
6991  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "vmull");
6992  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vpadal_v:
6993  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vpadalq_v: {
6994  // The source operand type has twice as many elements of half the size.
6995  unsigned EltBits = VTy->getElementType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
6996  llvm::Type *EltTy =
6997  llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), EltBits / 2);
6998  auto *NarrowTy =
6999  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(EltTy, VTy->getNumElements() * 2);
7000  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { Ty, NarrowTy };

7002  }
