7163  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], SrcTy);
7164  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateSub(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vsubhn");
7165 
7166  // %high = lshr <4 x i32> %sum, <i32 16, i32 16, i32 16, i32 16>
7167  Constant *ShiftAmt =
7168  ConstantInt::get(SrcTy, SrcTy->getScalarSizeInBits() / 2);
7169  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateLShr(Ops[0], ShiftAmt, "vsubhn");
7170 
7171  // %res = trunc <4 x i32> %high to <4 x i16>
7172  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[0], VTy, "vsubhn");
7173  }
7174  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtrn_v:
7175  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtrnq_v: {
7176  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
7177  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
7178  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
7179  Value *SV = nullptr;
7180 
7181  for (unsigned vi = 0; vi != 2; ++vi) {
7182  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
7183  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; i += 2) {
7184  Indices.push_back(i+vi);
7185  Indices.push_back(i+e+vi);

7188  SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[2], Indices, "vtrn");
7189  SV = Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(SV, Addr);

7192  }

7195  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);

7197  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateAnd(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
7198  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Ops[0],
7199  ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty));
7200  return Builder.CreateSExt(Ops[0], Ty, "vtst");

7208

7212  Indices.push_back(2*i+vi);

7221  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Int);
7222  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[2], Int64Ty);
7223  return EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, "");
7224  }
7225  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vzip_v:
7226  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vzipq_v: {
7227  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
7228  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
7229  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
7230  Value *SV = nullptr;

7232  for (unsigned vi = 0; vi != 2; ++vi) {

7234  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; i += 2) {
7235  Indices.push_back((i + vi*e) >> 1);
7236  Indices.push_back(((i + vi*e) >> 1)+e);

7239  SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[2], Indices, "vzip");
7240  SV = Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(SV, Addr);

7249  Int = Usgn ? LLVMIntrinsic : AltLLVMIntrinsic;

7299  }

7302  llvm::Type *InputTy =

7304  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { Ty, InputTy };
7305  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Tys), Ops, "vbfdot");
7306  }
7307  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon___a32_vcvt_bf16_v: {
7308  llvm::Type *Tys[1] = { Ty };
7309  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Tys);
7310  return EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, "vcvtfp2bf");
7311  }
7312 
7313  }
7314 
7315  assert(Int && "Expected valid intrinsic number");
7316 
7317  // Determine the type(s) of this overloaded AArch64 intrinsic.
7318  Function *F = LookupNeonLLVMIntrinsic(Int, Modifier, Ty, E);
7319 
7320  Value *Result = EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, NameHint);
7321  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
7322  // AArch64 intrinsic one-element vector type cast to
7323  // scalar type expected by the builtin
7324  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Result, ResultType, NameHint);
7325 }
7326 
7327 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitAArch64CompareBuiltinExpr(
7328  Value *Op, llvm::Type *Ty, const CmpInst::Predicate Fp,
7329  const CmpInst::Predicate Ip, const Twine &Name) {
7330  llvm::Type *OTy = Op->getType();
7331 
7332  // FIXME: this is utterly horrific. We should not be looking at previous
7333  // codegen context to find out what needs doing. Unfortunately TableGen
7334  // currently gives us exactly the same calls for vceqz_f32 and vceqz_s32
7335  // (etc).
7336  if (BitCastInst *BI = dyn_cast<BitCastInst>(Op))
7337  OTy = BI->getOperand(0)->getType();
7338 
7339  Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, OTy);
7340  if (OTy->getScalarType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
7341  if (Fp == CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ)
7342  Op = Builder.CreateFCmp(Fp, Op, Constant::getNullValue(OTy));
7343  else
7344  Op = Builder.CreateFCmpS(Fp, Op, Constant::getNullValue(OTy));
7345  } else {
7346  Op = Builder.CreateICmp(Ip, Op, Constant::getNullValue(OTy));
7347  }
7348  return Builder.CreateSExt(Op, Ty, Name);
7349 }
7350 
7351 static Value *packTBLDVectorList(CodeGenFunction &CGF, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
7352  Value *ExtOp, Value *IndexOp,
7353  llvm::Type *ResTy, unsigned IntID,
7354  const char *Name) {
7355  SmallVector<Value *, 2> TblOps;
7356  if (ExtOp)
7357  TblOps.push_back(ExtOp);
7358 
7359  // Build a vector containing sequential number like (0, 1, 2, ..., 15)
7360  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
7361  auto *TblTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType());
7362  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TblTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
7363  Indices.push_back(2*i);
7364  Indices.push_back(2*i+1);
7365  }
7366 
7367  int PairPos = 0, End = Ops.size() - 1;
7368  while (PairPos < End) {
7369  TblOps.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[PairPos],
7370  Ops[PairPos+1], Indices,
7371  Name));
7372  PairPos += 2;
7373  }
7374 
7375  // If there's an odd number of 64-bit lookup table, fill the high 64-bit
7376  // of the 128-bit lookup table with zero.
7377  if (PairPos == End) {
7378  Value *ZeroTbl = ConstantAggregateZero::get(TblTy);
7379  TblOps.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[PairPos],
7380  ZeroTbl, Indices, Name));
7381  }
7382 
7383  Function *TblF;
7384  TblOps.push_back(IndexOp);
7385  TblF = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, ResTy);
7386 
7387  return CGF.EmitNeonCall(TblF, TblOps, Name);
7388 }
7389 
7390 Value *CodeGenFunction::GetValueForARMHint(unsigned BuiltinID) {
7391  unsigned Value;
7392  switch (BuiltinID) {
7393  default:
7394  return nullptr;
7395  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_nop:
7396  Value = 0;
7397  break;
7398  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_yield:
7399  case ARM::BI__yield:
7400  Value = 1;
7401  break;
7402  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wfe:
7403  case ARM::BI__wfe:
7404  Value = 2;
7405  break;
7406  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wfi:
7407  case ARM::BI__wfi:
7408  Value = 3;
7409  break;
7410  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_sev:
7411  case ARM::BI__sev:
7412  Value = 4;
7413  break;
7414  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_sevl:
7415  case ARM::BI__sevl:
7416  Value = 5;
7417  break;
7418  }
7419 
7420  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_hint),
7421  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Value));
7422 }
7423 
7424 enum SpecialRegisterAccessKind {
7425  NormalRead,
7426  VolatileRead,
7427  Write,
7428 };
7429 
7430 // Generates the IR for the read/write special register builtin,
7431 // ValueType is the type of the value that is to be written or read,
7432 // RegisterType is the type of the register being written to or read from.
7433 static Value *EmitSpecialRegisterBuiltin(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7434  const CallExpr *E,
7435  llvm::Type *RegisterType,
7436  llvm::Type *ValueType,
7437  SpecialRegisterAccessKind AccessKind,
7438  StringRef SysReg = "") {
7439  // write and register intrinsics only support 32 and 64 bit operations.
7440  assert((RegisterType->isIntegerTy(32) || RegisterType->isIntegerTy(64))
7441  && "Unsupported size for register.");
7442 
7443  CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
7444  CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM = CGF.CGM;
7445  LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
7446 
7447  if (SysReg.empty()) {
7448  const Expr *SysRegStrExpr = E->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
7449  SysReg = cast<clang::StringLiteral>(SysRegStrExpr)->getString();
7450  }
7451 
7452  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = { llvm::MDString::get(Context, SysReg) };
7453  llvm::MDNode *RegName = llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Ops);
7454  llvm::Value *Metadata = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Context, RegName);
7455 
7456  llvm::Type *Types[] = { RegisterType };
7457 
7458  bool MixedTypes = RegisterType->isIntegerTy(64) && ValueType->isIntegerTy(32);
7459  assert(!(RegisterType->isIntegerTy(32) && ValueType->isIntegerTy(64))
7460  && "Can't fit 64-bit value in 32-bit register");
7461 
7462  if (AccessKind != Write) {
7463  assert(AccessKind == NormalRead || AccessKind == VolatileRead);
7464  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(
7465  AccessKind == VolatileRead ? llvm::Intrinsic::read_volatile_register
7466  : llvm::Intrinsic::read_register,
7467  Types);
7468  llvm::Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, Metadata);
7469 
7470  if (MixedTypes)
7471  // Read into 64 bit register and then truncate result to 32 bit.
7472  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Call, ValueType);
7473 
7474  if (ValueType->isPointerTy())
7475  // Have i32/i64 result (Call) but want to return a VoidPtrTy (i8*).
7476  return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Call, ValueType);
7477 
7478  return Call;
7479  }
7480 
7481  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::write_register, Types);
7482  llvm::Value *ArgValue = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7483  if (MixedTypes) {
7484  // Extend 32 bit write value to 64 bit to pass to write.
7485  ArgValue = Builder.CreateZExt(ArgValue, RegisterType);
7486  return Builder.CreateCall(F, { Metadata, ArgValue });
7487  }
7488 
7489  if (ValueType->isPointerTy()) {
7490  // Have VoidPtrTy ArgValue but want to return an i32/i64.
7491  ArgValue = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(ArgValue, RegisterType);
7492  return Builder.CreateCall(F, { Metadata, ArgValue });
7493  }
7494 
7495  return Builder.CreateCall(F, { Metadata, ArgValue });
7496 }
7497 
7498 /// Return true if BuiltinID is an overloaded Neon intrinsic with an extra
7499 /// argument that specifies the vector type.
7500 static bool HasExtraNeonArgument(unsigned BuiltinID) {
7501  switch (BuiltinID) {
7502  default: break;
7503  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i8:
7504  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i16:
7505  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_bf16:
7506  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i32:
7507  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i64:
7508  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_f32:
7509  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i8:
7510  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i16:
7511  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_bf16:
7512  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i32:
7513  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i64:
7514  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_f32:
7515  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vduph_lane_bf16:
7516  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vduph_laneq_bf16:
7517  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i8:
7518  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i16:
7519  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_bf16:
7520  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i32:
7521  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i64:
7522  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_f32:
7523  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i8:
7524  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i16:
7525  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_bf16:
7526  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i32:
7527  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i64:
7528  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_f32:
7529  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1h_u32:
7530  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1cq_u32:
7531  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1pq_u32:
7532  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1mq_u32:
7533  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_bf16_f32:
7534  case clang::ARM::BI_MoveToCoprocessor:
7535  case clang::ARM::BI_MoveToCoprocessor2:
7536  return false;
7537  }
7538  return true;
7539 }
7540 
7541 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARMBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
7542  const CallExpr *E,
7543  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
7544  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
7545  if (auto Hint = GetValueForARMHint(BuiltinID))
7546  return Hint;
7547 
7548  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__emit) {
7549  bool IsThumb = getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::thumb;
7550  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
7551  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, /*Variadic=*/false);
7552 
7553  Expr::EvalResult Result;
7554  if (!E->getArg(0)->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGM.getContext()))
7555  llvm_unreachable("Sema will ensure that the parameter is constant");
7556 
7557  llvm::APSInt Value = Result.Val.getInt();
7558  uint64_t ZExtValue = Value.zextOrTrunc(IsThumb ? 16 : 32).getZExtValue();
7559 
7560  llvm::InlineAsm *Emit =
7561  IsThumb ? InlineAsm::get(FTy, ".inst.n 0x" + utohexstr(ZExtValue), "",
7562  /*hasSideEffects=*/true)
7563  : InlineAsm::get(FTy, ".inst 0x" + utohexstr(ZExtValue), "",
7564  /*hasSideEffects=*/true);
7565 
7566  return Builder.CreateCall(Emit);
7567  }
7568 
7569  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_dbg) {
7570  Value *Option = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7571  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_dbg), Option);
7572  }
7573 
7574  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_prefetch) {
7575  Value *Address = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7576  Value *RW = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7577  Value *IsData = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
7578 
7579  // Locality is not supported on ARM target
7580  Value *Locality = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 3);
7581 
7582  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::prefetch, Address->getType());
7583  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Address, RW, Locality, IsData});
7584  }
7585 
7586  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rbit) {
7587  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7588  return Builder.CreateCall(
7589  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bitreverse, Arg->getType()), Arg, "rbit");
7590  }
7591 
7592  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_cls) {
7593  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7594  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_cls), Arg, "cls");
7595  }
7596  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_cls64) {
7597  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7598  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_cls64), Arg,
7599  "cls");
7600  }
7601 
7602  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__clear_cache) {
7603  assert(E->getNumArgs() == 2 && "__clear_cache takes 2 arguments");
7604  const FunctionDecl *FD = E->getDirectCallee();
7605  Value *Ops[2];
7606  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 2; i++)
7607  Ops[i] = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i));
7608  llvm::Type *Ty = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(FD->getType());
7609  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = cast<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty);
7610  StringRef Name = FD->getName();
7611  return EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name), Ops);
7612  }
7613 
7614  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr ||
7615  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr2) {
7616  Function *F;
7617 
7618  switch (BuiltinID) {
7619  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin");
7620  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr:
7621  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_mcrr);
7622  break;
7623  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mcrr2:
7624  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_mcrr2);
7625  break;
7626  }
7627 
7628  // MCRR{2} instruction has 5 operands but
7629  // the intrinsic has 4 because Rt and Rt2
7630  // are represented as a single unsigned 64
7631  // bit integer in the intrinsic definition
7632  // but internally it's represented as 2 32
7633  // bit integers.
7634 
7635  Value *Coproc = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7636  Value *Opc1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7637  Value *RtAndRt2 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
7638  Value *CRm = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3));
7639 
7640  Value *C1 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32);
7641  Value *Rt = Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(RtAndRt2, Int32Ty);
7642  Value *Rt2 = Builder.CreateLShr(RtAndRt2, C1);
7643  Rt2 = Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(Rt2, Int32Ty);
7644 
7645  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Coproc, Opc1, Rt, Rt2, CRm});
7646  }
7647 
7648  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc ||
7649  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc2) {
7650  Function *F;
7651 
7652  switch (BuiltinID) {
7653  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin");
7654  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc:
7655  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_mrrc);
7656  break;
7657  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_mrrc2:
7658  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_mrrc2);
7659  break;
7660  }
7661 
7662  Value *Coproc = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7663  Value *Opc1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7664  Value *CRm = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
7665  Value *RtAndRt2 = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Coproc, Opc1, CRm});
7666 
7667  // Returns an unsigned 64 bit integer, represented
7668  // as two 32 bit integers.
7669 
7670  Value *Rt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(RtAndRt2, 1);
7671  Value *Rt1 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(RtAndRt2, 0);
7672  Rt = Builder.CreateZExt(Rt, Int64Ty);
7673  Rt1 = Builder.CreateZExt(Rt1, Int64Ty);
7674 
7675  Value *ShiftCast = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32);
7676  RtAndRt2 = Builder.CreateShl(Rt, ShiftCast, "shl", true);
7677  RtAndRt2 = Builder.CreateOr(RtAndRt2, Rt1);
7678 
7679  return Builder.CreateBitCast(RtAndRt2, ConvertType(E->getType()));
7680  }
7681 
7682  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrexd ||
7683  ((BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
7684  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex) &&
7685  getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()) == 64) ||
7686  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__ldrexd) {
7687  Function *F;
7688 
7689  switch (BuiltinID) {
7690  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin");
7691  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex:
7692  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_ldaexd);
7693  break;
7694  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrexd:
7695  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex:
7696  case ARM::BI__ldrexd:
7697  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_ldrexd);
7698  break;
7699  }
7700 
7701  Value *LdPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7702  Value *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F, Builder.CreateBitCast(LdPtr, Int8PtrTy),
7703  "ldrexd");
7704 
7705  Value *Val0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 1);
7706  Value *Val1 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 0);
7707  Val0 = Builder.CreateZExt(Val0, Int64Ty);
7708  Val1 = Builder.CreateZExt(Val1, Int64Ty);
7709 
7710  Value *ShiftCst = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32);
7711  Val = Builder.CreateShl(Val0, ShiftCst, "shl", true /* nuw */);
7712  Val = Builder.CreateOr(Val, Val1);
7713  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, ConvertType(E->getType()));
7714  }
7715 
7716  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
7717  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex) {
7718  Value *LoadAddr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7719 
7720  QualType Ty = E->getType();
7721  llvm::Type *RealResTy = ConvertType(Ty);
7722  llvm::Type *IntTy =
7723  llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), getContext().getTypeSize(Ty));
7724  llvm::Type *PtrTy = IntTy->getPointerTo();
7725  LoadAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(LoadAddr, PtrTy);
7726 
7727  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex
7728  ? Intrinsic::arm_ldaex
7729  : Intrinsic::arm_ldrex,
7730  PtrTy);
7731  CallInst *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F, LoadAddr, "ldrex");
7732  Val->addParamAttr(
7733  0, Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), Attribute::ElementType, IntTy));
7734 
7735  if (RealResTy->isPointerTy())
7736  return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, RealResTy);
7737  else {
7738  llvm::Type *IntResTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(
7739  getLLVMContext(), CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(RealResTy));
7740  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(Val, IntResTy),
7741  RealResTy);
7742  }
7743  }
7744 
7745  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_strexd ||
7746  ((BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex ||
7747  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_strex) &&
7748  getContext().getTypeSize(E->getArg(0)->getType()) == 64)) {
7749  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex
7750  ? Intrinsic::arm_stlexd
7751  : Intrinsic::arm_strexd);
7752  llvm::Type *STy = llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, Int32Ty);
7753 
7754  Address Tmp = CreateMemTemp(E->getArg(0)->getType());
7755  Value *Val = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7756  Builder.CreateStore(Val, Tmp);
7757 
7758  Address LdPtr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Tmp, STy);
7759  Val = Builder.CreateLoad(LdPtr);
7760 
7761  Value *Arg0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 0);
7762  Value *Arg1 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 1);
7763  Value *StPtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)), Int8PtrTy);
7764  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg0, Arg1, StPtr}, "strexd");
7765  }
7766 
7767  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
7768  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) {
7769  Value *StoreVal = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7770  Value *StoreAddr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7771 
7772  QualType Ty = E->getArg(0)->getType();
7773  llvm::Type *StoreTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(),
7774  getContext().getTypeSize(Ty));
7775  StoreAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(StoreAddr, StoreTy->getPointerTo());
7776 
7777  if (StoreVal->getType()->isPointerTy())
7778  StoreVal = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(StoreVal, Int32Ty);
7779  else {
7780  llvm::Type *IntTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(
7781  getLLVMContext(),
7782  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(StoreVal->getType()));
7783  StoreVal = Builder.CreateBitCast(StoreVal, IntTy);
7784  StoreVal = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(StoreVal, Int32Ty);
7785  }
7786 
7787  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_stlex
7788  ? Intrinsic::arm_stlex
7789  : Intrinsic::arm_strex,
7790  StoreAddr->getType());
7791 
7792  CallInst *CI = Builder.CreateCall(F, {StoreVal, StoreAddr}, "strex");
7793  CI->addParamAttr(
7794  1, Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), Attribute::ElementType, StoreTy));
7795  return CI;
7796  }
7797 
7798  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_clrex) {
7799  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_clrex);
7800  return Builder.CreateCall(F);
7801  }
7802 
7803  // CRC32
7804  Intrinsic::ID CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
7805  switch (BuiltinID) {
7806  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32b:
7807  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32b; break;
7808  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cb:
7809  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32cb; break;
7810  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32h:
7811  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32h; break;
7812  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32ch:
7813  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32ch; break;
7814  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32w:
7815  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32d:
7816  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32w; break;
7817  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cw:
7818  case ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cd:
7819  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::arm_crc32cw; break;
7820  }
7821 
7822  if (CRCIntrinsicID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
7823  Value *Arg0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
7824  Value *Arg1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
7825 
7826  // crc32{c,}d intrinsics are implemnted as two calls to crc32{c,}w
7827  // intrinsics, hence we need different codegen for these cases.
7828  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32d ||
7829  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cd) {
7830  Value *C1 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32);
7831  Value *Arg1a = Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(Arg1, Int32Ty);
7832  Value *Arg1b = Builder.CreateLShr(Arg1, C1);
7833  Arg1b = Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(Arg1b, Int32Ty);
7834 
7835  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CRCIntrinsicID);
7836  Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg0, Arg1a});
7837  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Res, Arg1b});
7838  } else {
7839  Arg1 = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(Arg1, Int32Ty);
7840 
7841  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CRCIntrinsicID);
7842  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg0, Arg1});
7843  }
7844  }
7845 
7846  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
7847  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
7848  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
7849  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
7850  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64 ||
7851  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp) {
7852 
7853  SpecialRegisterAccessKind AccessKind = Write;
7854  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
7855  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
7856  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp)
7857  AccessKind = VolatileRead;
7858 
7859  bool IsPointerBuiltin = BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
7860  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp;
7861 
7862  bool Is64Bit = BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
7863  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64;
7864 
7865  llvm::Type *ValueType;
7866  llvm::Type *RegisterType;
7867  if (IsPointerBuiltin) {
7868  ValueType = VoidPtrTy;
7869  RegisterType = Int32Ty;
7870  } else if (Is64Bit) {
7871  ValueType = RegisterType = Int64Ty;
7872  } else {
7873  ValueType = RegisterType = Int32Ty;
7874  }
7875 
7876  return EmitSpecialRegisterBuiltin(*this, E, RegisterType, ValueType,
7877  AccessKind);
7878  }
7879 
7880  // Handle MSVC intrinsics before argument evaluation to prevent double
7881  // evaluation.
7882  if (Optional<MSVCIntrin> MsvcIntId = translateArmToMsvcIntrin(BuiltinID))
7883  return EmitMSVCBuiltinExpr(*MsvcIntId, E);
7884 
7885  // Deal with MVE builtins
7886  if (Value *Result = EmitARMMVEBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue, Arch))
7887  return Result;
7888  // Handle CDE builtins
7889  if (Value *Result = EmitARMCDEBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E, ReturnValue, Arch))
7890  return Result;
7891 
7892  // Find out if any arguments are required to be integer constant
7893  // expressions.
7894  unsigned ICEArguments = 0;
7895  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error;
7896  getContext().GetBuiltinType(BuiltinID, Error, &ICEArguments);
7897  assert(Error == ASTContext::GE_None && "Should not codegen an error");
7898 
7899  auto getAlignmentValue32 = [&](Address addr) -> Value* {
7900  return Builder.getInt32(addr.getAlignment().getQuantity());
7901  };
7902 
7903  Address PtrOp0 = Address::invalid();
7904  Address PtrOp1 = Address::invalid();
7905  SmallVector<Value*, 4> Ops;
7906  bool HasExtraArg = HasExtraNeonArgument(BuiltinID);
7907  unsigned NumArgs = E->getNumArgs() - (HasExtraArg ? 1 : 0);
7908  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumArgs; i != e; i++) {
7909  if (i == 0) {
7910  switch (BuiltinID) {
7911  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_v:
7912  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_v:
7913  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_lane_v:
7914  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_lane_v:
7915  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_dup_v:
7916  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_dup_v:
7917  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_v:
7918  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_v:
7919  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_lane_v:
7920  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_lane_v:
7921  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst2_v:
7922  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst2q_v:
7923  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst2_lane_v:
7924  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst2q_lane_v:
7925  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3_v:
7926  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3q_v:
7927  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3_lane_v:
7928  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3q_lane_v:
7929  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4_v:
7930  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4q_v:
7931  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4_lane_v:
7932  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4q_lane_v:
7933  // Get the alignment for the argument in addition to the value;
7934  // we'll use it later.
7935  PtrOp0 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
7936  Ops.push_back(PtrOp0.getPointer());
7937  continue;
7938  }
7939  }
7940  if (i == 1) {
7941  switch (BuiltinID) {
7942  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_v:
7943  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_v:
7944  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_v:
7945  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_v:
7946  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_v:
7947  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_v:
7948  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_lane_v:
7949  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_lane_v:
7950  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_lane_v:
7951  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_lane_v:
7952  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_lane_v:
7953  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_lane_v:
7954  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_dup_v:
7955  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_dup_v:
7956  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_dup_v:
7957  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_dup_v:
7958  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_dup_v:
7959  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_dup_v:
7960  // Get the alignment for the argument in addition to the value;
7961  // we'll use it later.
7962  PtrOp1 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(1));
7963  Ops.push_back(PtrOp1.getPointer());
7964  continue;
7965  }
7966  }
7967 
7968  if ((ICEArguments & (1 << i)) == 0) {
7969  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
7970  } else {
7971  // If this is required to be a constant, constant fold it so that we know
7972  // that the generated intrinsic gets a ConstantInt.
7973  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
7974  getLLVMContext(),
7975  *E->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext())));
7976  }
7977  }
7978 
7979  switch (BuiltinID) {
7980  default: break;
7981 
7982  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i8:
7983  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i16:
7984  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i32:
7985  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_i64:
7986  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_bf16:
7987  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vget_lane_f32:
7988  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i8:
7989  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i16:
7990  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i32:
7991  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_i64:
7992  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_bf16:
7993  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vgetq_lane_f32:
7994  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vduph_lane_bf16:
7995  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vduph_laneq_bf16:
7996  return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vget_lane");
7997 
7998  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrndns_f32: {
7999  Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
8000  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Arg->getType()};
8001  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vrintn, Tys);
8002  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg}, "vrndn"); }
8003 
8004  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i8:
8005  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i16:
8006  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i32:
8007  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_i64:
8008  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_bf16:
8009  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vset_lane_f32:
8010  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i8:
8011  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i16:
8012  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i32:
8013  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_i64:
8014  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_bf16:
8015  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsetq_lane_f32:
8016  return Builder.CreateInsertElement(Ops[1], Ops[0], Ops[2], "vset_lane");
8017 
8018  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1h_u32:
8019  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_sha1h), Ops,
8020  "vsha1h");
8021  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1cq_u32:
8022  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_sha1c), Ops,
8023  "vsha1h");
8024  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1pq_u32:
8025  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_sha1p), Ops,
8026  "vsha1h");
8027  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsha1mq_u32:
8028  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_sha1m), Ops,
8029  "vsha1h");
8030 
8031  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_bf16_f32: {
8032  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vcvtbfp2bf), Ops,
8033  "vcvtbfp2bf");
8034  }
8035 
8036  // The ARM _MoveToCoprocessor builtins put the input register value as
8037  // the first argument, but the LLVM intrinsic expects it as the third one.
8038  case ARM::BI_MoveToCoprocessor:
8039  case ARM::BI_MoveToCoprocessor2: {
8040  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == ARM::BI_MoveToCoprocessor ?
8041  Intrinsic::arm_mcr : Intrinsic::arm_mcr2);
8042  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[1], Ops[2], Ops[0],
8043  Ops[3], Ops[4], Ops[5]});
8044  }
8045  }
8046 
8047  // Get the last argument, which specifies the vector type.
8048  assert(HasExtraArg);
8049  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(E->getNumArgs()-1);
8050  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
8051  if (!Result)
8052  return nullptr;
8053 
8054  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_vcvtr_f ||
8055  BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_vcvtr_d) {
8056  // Determine the overloaded type of this builtin.
8057  llvm::Type *Ty;
8058  if (BuiltinID == ARM::BI__builtin_arm_vcvtr_f)
8059  Ty = FloatTy;
8060  else
8061  Ty = DoubleTy;
8062 
8063  // Determine whether this is an unsigned conversion or not.
8064  bool usgn = Result->getZExtValue() == 1;
8065  unsigned Int = usgn ? Intrinsic::arm_vcvtru : Intrinsic::arm_vcvtr;
8066 
8067  // Call the appropriate intrinsic.
8068  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty);
8069  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "vcvtr");
8070  }
8071 
8072  // Determine the type of this overloaded NEON intrinsic.
8073  NeonTypeFlags Type = Result->getZExtValue();
8074  bool usgn = Type.isUnsigned();
8075  bool rightShift = false;
8076 
8077  llvm::FixedVectorType *VTy =
8078  GetNeonType(this, Type, getTarget().hasLegalHalfType(), false,
8079  getTarget().hasBFloat16Type());
8080  llvm::Type *Ty = VTy;
8081  if (!Ty)
8082  return nullptr;
8083 
8084  // Many NEON builtins have identical semantics and uses in ARM and
8085  // AArch64. Emit these in a single function.
8086  auto IntrinsicMap = makeArrayRef(ARMSIMDIntrinsicMap);
8087  const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo *Builtin = findARMVectorIntrinsicInMap(
8088  IntrinsicMap, BuiltinID, NEONSIMDIntrinsicsProvenSorted);
8089  if (Builtin)
8090  return EmitCommonNeonBuiltinExpr(
8091  Builtin->BuiltinID, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic, Builtin->AltLLVMIntrinsic,
8092  Builtin->NameHint, Builtin->TypeModifier, E, Ops, PtrOp0, PtrOp1, Arch);
8093 
8094  unsigned Int;
8095  switch (BuiltinID) {
8096  default: return nullptr;
8097  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_lane_v:
8098  // Handle 64-bit integer elements as a special case. Use shuffles of
8099  // one-element vectors to avoid poor code for i64 in the backend.
8100  if (VTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(64)) {
8101  // Extract the other lane.
8102  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
8103  int Lane = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue();
8104  Value *SV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 1-Lane));
8105  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[1], SV);
8106  // Load the value as a one-element vector.
8107  Ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(), 1);
8108  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Ty, Int8PtrTy};
8109  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld1, Tys);
8110  Value *Align = getAlignmentValue32(PtrOp0);
8111  Value *Ld = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Align});
8112  // Combine them.
8113  int Indices[] = {1 - Lane, Lane};
8114  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ld, Indices, "vld1q_lane");
8115  }
8116  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8117  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_lane_v: {
8118  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
8119  PtrOp0 = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(PtrOp0, VTy->getElementType());
8120  Value *Ld = Builder.CreateLoad(PtrOp0);
8121  return Builder.CreateInsertElement(Ops[1], Ld, Ops[2], "vld1_lane");
8122  }
8123  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqrshrn_n_v:
8124  Int =
8125  usgn ? Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqrshiftnu : Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqrshiftns;
8126  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "vqrshrn_n",
8127  1, true);
8128  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqrshrun_n_v:
8129  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqrshiftnsu, Ty),
8130  Ops, "vqrshrun_n", 1, true);
8131  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqshrn_n_v:
8132  Int = usgn ? Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqshiftnu : Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqshiftns;
8133  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "vqshrn_n",
8134  1, true);
8135  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqshrun_n_v:
8136  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vqshiftnsu, Ty),
8137  Ops, "vqshrun_n", 1, true);
8138  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrecpe_v:
8139  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrecpeq_v:
8140  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vrecpe, Ty),
8141  Ops, "vrecpe");
8142  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrshrn_n_v:
8143  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vrshiftn, Ty),
8144  Ops, "vrshrn_n", 1, true);
8145  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrsra_n_v:
8146  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vrsraq_n_v:
8147  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
8148  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
8149  Ops[2] = EmitNeonShiftVector(Ops[2], Ty, true);
8150  Int = usgn ? Intrinsic::arm_neon_vrshiftu : Intrinsic::arm_neon_vrshifts;
8151  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), {Ops[1], Ops[2]});
8152  return Builder.CreateAdd(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vrsra_n");
8153  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsri_n_v:
8154  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsriq_n_v:
8155  rightShift = true;
8156  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8157  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsli_n_v:
8158  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsliq_n_v:
8159  Ops[2] = EmitNeonShiftVector(Ops[2], Ty, rightShift);
8160  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vshiftins, Ty),
8161  Ops, "vsli_n");
8162  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsra_n_v:
8163  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsraq_n_v:
8164  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
8165  Ops[1] = EmitNeonRShiftImm(Ops[1], Ops[2], Ty, usgn, "vsra_n");
8166  return Builder.CreateAdd(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
8167  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_lane_v:
8168  // Handle 64-bit integer elements as a special case. Use a shuffle to get
8169  // a one-element vector and avoid poor code for i64 in the backend.
8170  if (VTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(64)) {
8171  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
8172  Value *SV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(cast<llvm::Constant>(Ops[2]));
8173  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[1], SV);
8174  Ops[2] = getAlignmentValue32(PtrOp0);
8175  llvm::Type *Tys[] = {Int8PtrTy, Ops[1]->getType()};
8176  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst1,
8177  Tys), Ops);
8178  }
8179  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8180  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_lane_v: {
8181  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
8182  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[1], Ops[2]);
8183  auto St = Builder.CreateStore(
8184  Ops[1], Builder.CreateElementBitCast(PtrOp0, Ops[1]->getType()));
8185  return St;
8186  }
8187  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl1_v:
8188  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbl1),
8189  Ops, "vtbl1");
8190  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl2_v:
8191  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbl2),
8192  Ops, "vtbl2");
8193  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl3_v:
8194  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbl3),
8195  Ops, "vtbl3");
8196  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl4_v:
8197  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbl4),
8198  Ops, "vtbl4");
8199  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx1_v:
8200  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbx1),
8201  Ops, "vtbx1");
8202  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx2_v:
8203  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbx2),
8204  Ops, "vtbx2");
8205  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx3_v:
8206  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbx3),
8207  Ops, "vtbx3");
8208  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx4_v:
8209  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbx4),
8210  Ops, "vtbx4");
8211  }
8212 }

8214 template<typename Integer>
8215 static Integer GetIntegerConstantValue(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Context) {
8216  return E->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)->getExtValue();
8217 }
8218 
8219 static llvm::Value *SignOrZeroExtend(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *V,
8220  llvm::Type *T, bool Unsigned) {
8221  // Helper function called by Tablegen-constructed ARM MVE builtin codegen,
8222  // which finds it convenient to specify signed/unsigned as a boolean flag.
8223  return Unsigned ? Builder.CreateZExt(V, T) : Builder.CreateSExt(V, T);
8224 }
8225 
8226 static llvm::Value *MVEImmediateShr(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *V,
8227  uint32_t Shift, bool Unsigned) {
8228  // MVE helper function for integer shift right. This must handle signed vs
8229  // unsigned, and also deal specially with the case where the shift count is
8230  // equal to the lane size. In LLVM IR, an LShr with that parameter would be
8231  // undefined behavior, but in MVE it's legal, so we must convert it to code
8232  // that is not undefined in IR.
8233  unsigned LaneBits = cast<llvm::VectorType>(V->getType())
8234  ->getElementType()
8235  ->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
8236  if (Shift == LaneBits) {
8237  // An unsigned shift of the full lane size always generates zero, so we can
8238  // simply emit a zero vector. A signed shift of the full lane size does the
8239  // same thing as shifting by one bit fewer.
8240  if (Unsigned)
8241  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(V->getType());
8242  else
8243  --Shift;
8244  }
8245  return Unsigned ? Builder.CreateLShr(V, Shift) : Builder.CreateAShr(V, Shift);
8246 }
8247 
8248 static llvm::Value *ARMMVEVectorSplat(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *V) {
8249  // MVE-specific helper function for a vector splat, which infers the element
8250  // count of the output vector by knowing that MVE vectors are all 128 bits
8251  // wide.
8252  unsigned Elements = 128 / V->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
8253  return Builder.CreateVectorSplat(Elements, V);
8254 }
8255 
8256 static llvm::Value *ARMMVEVectorReinterpret(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
8257  CodeGenFunction *CGF,
8258  llvm::Value *V,
8259  llvm::Type *DestType) {
8260  // Convert one MVE vector type into another by reinterpreting its in-register
8261  // format.
8262  //
8263  // Little-endian, this is identical to a bitcast (which reinterprets the
8264  // memory format). But big-endian, they're not necessarily the same, because
8265  // the register and memory formats map to each other differently depending on
8266  // the lane size.
8267  //
8268  // We generate a bitcast whenever we can (if we're little-endian, or if the
8269  // lane sizes are the same anyway). Otherwise we fall back to an IR intrinsic
8270  // that performs the different kind of reinterpretation.
8271  if (CGF->getTarget().isBigEndian() &&
8272  V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() != DestType->getScalarSizeInBits()) {
8273  return Builder.CreateCall(
8274  CGF->CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::arm_mve_vreinterpretq,
8275  {DestType, V->getType()}),
8276  V);
8277  } else {
8278  return Builder.CreateBitCast(V, DestType);
8279  }
8280 }
8281 
8282 static llvm::Value *VectorUnzip(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *V, bool Odd) {
8283  // Make a shufflevector that extracts every other element of a vector (evens
8284  // or odds, as desired).
8285  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
8286  unsigned InputElements =
8287  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(V->getType())->getNumElements();
8288  for (unsigned i = 0; i < InputElements; i += 2)
8289  Indices.push_back(i + Odd);
8290  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, Indices);
8291 }
8292 
8293 static llvm::Value *VectorZip(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *V0,
8294  llvm::Value *V1) {
8295  // Make a shufflevector that interleaves two vectors element by element.
8296  assert(V0->getType() == V1->getType() && "Can't zip different vector types");
8297  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
8298  unsigned InputElements =
8299  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(V0->getType())->getNumElements();
8300  for (unsigned i = 0; i < InputElements; i++) {
8301  Indices.push_back(i);
8302  Indices.push_back(i + InputElements);
8303  }
8304  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V0, V1, Indices);
8305 }
8306 
8307 template<unsigned HighBit, unsigned OtherBits>
8308 static llvm::Value *ARMMVEConstantSplat(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Type *VT) {
8309  // MVE-specific helper function to make a vector splat of a constant such as
8310  // UINT_MAX or INT_MIN, in which all bits below the highest one are equal.
8311  llvm::Type *T = cast<llvm::VectorType>(VT)->getElementType();
8312  unsigned LaneBits = T->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
8313  uint32_t Value = HighBit << (LaneBits - 1);
8314  if (OtherBits)
8315  Value |= (1UL << (LaneBits - 1)) - 1;
8316  llvm::Value *Lane = llvm::ConstantInt::get(T, Value);
8317  return ARMMVEVectorSplat(Builder, Lane);
8318 }
8319 
8320 static llvm::Value *ARMMVEVectorElementReverse(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
8321  llvm::Value *V,
8322  unsigned ReverseWidth) {
8323  // MVE-specific helper function which reverses the elements of a
8324  // vector within every (ReverseWidth)-bit collection of lanes.
8325  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
8326  unsigned LaneSize = V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
8327  unsigned Elements = 128 / LaneSize;
8328  unsigned Mask = ReverseWidth / LaneSize - 1;
8329  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Elements; i++)
8330  Indices.push_back(i ^ Mask);
8331  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, Indices);
8332 }
8333 
8334 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARMMVEBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
8335  const CallExpr *E,
8336  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
8337  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
8338  enum class CustomCodeGen { VLD24, VST24 } CustomCodeGenType;
8339  Intrinsic::ID IRIntr;
8340  unsigned NumVectors;
8341 
8342  // Code autogenerated by Tablegen will handle all the simple builtins.
8343  switch (BuiltinID) {
8344  #include "clang/Basic/arm_mve_builtin_cg.inc"
8345 
8346  // If we didn't match an MVE builtin id at all, go back to the
8347  // main EmitARMBuiltinExpr.
8348  default:
8349  return nullptr;
8350  }
8351 
8352  // Anything that breaks from that switch is an MVE builtin that
8353  // needs handwritten code to generate.
8354 
8355  switch (CustomCodeGenType) {
8356 
8357  case CustomCodeGen::VLD24: {
8358  llvm::SmallVector<Value *, 4> Ops;
8359  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> Tys;
8360 
8361  auto MvecCType = E->getType();
8362  auto MvecLType = ConvertType(MvecCType);
8363  assert(MvecLType->isStructTy() &&
8364  "Return type for vld[24]q should be a struct");
8365  assert(MvecLType->getStructNumElements() == 1 &&
8366  "Return-type struct for vld[24]q should have one element");
8367  auto MvecLTypeInner = MvecLType->getStructElementType(0);
8368  assert(MvecLTypeInner->isArrayTy() &&
8369  "Return-type struct for vld[24]q should contain an array");
8370  assert(MvecLTypeInner->getArrayNumElements() == NumVectors &&
8371  "Array member of return-type struct vld[24]q has wrong length");
8372  auto VecLType = MvecLTypeInner->getArrayElementType();
8373 
8374  Tys.push_back(VecLType);
8375 
8376  auto Addr = E->getArg(0);
8377  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(Addr));
8378  Tys.push_back(ConvertType(Addr->getType()));
8379 
8380  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IRIntr, makeArrayRef(Tys));
8381  Value *LoadResult = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
8382  Value *MvecOut = UndefValue::get(MvecLType);
8383  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVectors; ++i) {
8384  Value *Vec = Builder.CreateExtractValue(LoadResult, i);
8385  MvecOut = Builder.CreateInsertValue(MvecOut, Vec, {0, i});
8386  }
8387 
8388  if (ReturnValue.isNull())
8389  return MvecOut;
8390  else
8391  return Builder.CreateStore(MvecOut, ReturnValue.getValue());
8392  }
8393 
8394  case CustomCodeGen::VST24: {
8395  llvm::SmallVector<Value *, 4> Ops;
8396  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> Tys;
8397 
8398  auto Addr = E->getArg(0);
8399  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(Addr));
8400  Tys.push_back(ConvertType(Addr->getType()));
8401 
8402  auto MvecCType = E->getArg(1)->getType();
8403  auto MvecLType = ConvertType(MvecCType);
8404  assert(MvecLType->isStructTy() && "Data type for vst2q should be a struct");
8405  assert(MvecLType->getStructNumElements() == 1 &&
8406  "Data-type struct for vst2q should have one element");
8407  auto MvecLTypeInner = MvecLType->getStructElementType(0);
8408  assert(MvecLTypeInner->isArrayTy() &&
8409  "Data-type struct for vst2q should contain an array");
8410  assert(MvecLTypeInner->getArrayNumElements() == NumVectors &&
8411  "Array member of return-type struct vld[24]q has wrong length");
8412  auto VecLType = MvecLTypeInner->getArrayElementType();
8413 
8414  Tys.push_back(VecLType);
8415 
8416  AggValueSlot MvecSlot = CreateAggTemp(MvecCType);
8417  EmitAggExpr(E->getArg(1), MvecSlot);
8418  auto Mvec = Builder.CreateLoad(MvecSlot.getAddress());
8419  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVectors; i++)
8420  Ops.push_back(Builder.CreateExtractValue(Mvec, {0, i}));
8421 
8422  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IRIntr, makeArrayRef(Tys));
8423  Value *ToReturn = nullptr;
8424  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVectors; i++) {
8425  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, i));
8426  ToReturn = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
8427  Ops.pop_back();
8428  }
8429  return ToReturn;
8430  }
8431  }
8432  llvm_unreachable("unknown custom codegen type.");
8433 }

8435 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitARMCDEBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
8436  const CallExpr *E,
8437  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
8438  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
8439  switch (BuiltinID) {
8440  default:
8441  return nullptr;
8442 #include "clang/Basic/arm_cde_builtin_cg.inc"
8443  }
8444 }

8446 static Value *EmitAArch64TblBuiltinExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, unsigned BuiltinID,
8447  const CallExpr *E,
8448  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
8449  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
8450  unsigned int Int = 0;
8451  const char *s = nullptr;
8452 
8453  switch (BuiltinID) {
8454  default:
8455  return nullptr;
8456  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl1_v:
8457  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl1_v:
8458  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl1q_v:
8459  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl2_v:
8460  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl2_v:
8461  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl2q_v:
8462  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl3_v:
8463  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl3_v:
8464  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl3q_v:
8465  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl4_v:
8466  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl4_v:
8467  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl4q_v:
8468  break;
8469  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx1_v:
8470  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx1_v:
8471  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx1q_v:
8472  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx2_v:
8473  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx2_v:
8474  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx2q_v:
8475  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx3_v:
8476  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx3_v:
8477  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx3q_v:
8478  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx4_v:
8479  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx4_v:
8480  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx4q_v:
8481  break;
8482  }
8483 
8484  assert(E->getNumArgs() >= 3);
8485 
8486  // Get the last argument, which specifies the vector type.
8487  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(E->getNumArgs() - 1);
8488  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext());
8489  if (!Result)
8490  return nullptr;
8491 
8492  // Determine the type of this overloaded NEON intrinsic.
8493  NeonTypeFlags Type = Result->getZExtValue();
8494  llvm::FixedVectorType *Ty = GetNeonType(&CGF, Type);
8495  if (!Ty)
8496  return nullptr;
8497 
8498  CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
8499 
8500  // AArch64 scalar builtins are not overloaded, they do not have an extra
8501  // argument that specifies the vector type, need to handle each case.
8502  switch (BuiltinID) {
8503  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl1_v: {
8504  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(0, 1), nullptr,
8505  Ops[1], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl1,
8506  "vtbl1");
8507  }
8508  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl2_v: {
8509  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(0, 2), nullptr,
8510  Ops[2], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl1,
8511  "vtbl1");
8512  }
8513  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl3_v: {
8514  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(0, 3), nullptr,
8515  Ops[3], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl2,
8516  "vtbl2");
8517  }
8518  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbl4_v: {
8519  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(0, 4), nullptr,
8520  Ops[4], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl2,
8521  "vtbl2");
8522  }
8523  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx1_v: {
8524  Value *TblRes =
8525  packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1, 1), nullptr, Ops[2],
8526  Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl1, "vtbl1");
8527 
8528  llvm::Constant *EightV = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 8);
8529  Value *CmpRes = Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, Ops[2], EightV);
8530  CmpRes = Builder.CreateSExt(CmpRes, Ty);
8531 
8532  Value *EltsFromInput = Builder.CreateAnd(CmpRes, Ops[0]);
8533  Value *EltsFromTbl = Builder.CreateAnd(Builder.CreateNot(CmpRes), TblRes);
8534  return Builder.CreateOr(EltsFromInput, EltsFromTbl, "vtbx");
8535  }
8536  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx2_v: {
8537  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1, 2), Ops[0],
8538  Ops[3], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx1,
8539  "vtbx1");
8540  }
8541  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx3_v: {
8542  Value *TblRes =
8543  packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1, 3), nullptr, Ops[4],
8544  Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl2, "vtbl2");
8545 
8546  llvm::Constant *TwentyFourV = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 24);
8547  Value *CmpRes = Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, Ops[4],
8548  TwentyFourV);
8549  CmpRes = Builder.CreateSExt(CmpRes, Ty);
8550 
8551  Value *EltsFromInput = Builder.CreateAnd(CmpRes, Ops[0]);
8552  Value *EltsFromTbl = Builder.CreateAnd(Builder.CreateNot(CmpRes), TblRes);
8553  return Builder.CreateOr(EltsFromInput, EltsFromTbl, "vtbx");
8554  }
8555  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtbx4_v: {
8556  return packTBLDVectorList(CGF, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1, 4), Ops[0],
8557  Ops[5], Ty, Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx2,
8558  "vtbx2");
8559  }
8560  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl1_v:
8561  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl1q_v:
8562  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl1; s = "vtbl1"; break;
8563  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl2_v:
8564  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl2q_v: {
8565  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl2; s = "vtbl2"; break;
8566  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl3_v:
8567  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl3q_v:
8568  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl3; s = "vtbl3"; break;
8569  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl4_v:
8570  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl4q_v:
8571  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl4; s = "vtbl4"; break;
8572  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx1_v:
8573  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx1q_v:
8574  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx1; s = "vtbx1"; break;
8575  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx2_v:
8576  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx2q_v:
8577  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx2; s = "vtbx2"; break;
8578  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx3_v:
8579  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx3q_v:
8580  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx3; s = "vtbx3"; break;
8581  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx4_v:
8582  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx4q_v:
8583  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx4; s = "vtbx4"; break;
8584  }
8585  }
8586 
8587  if (!Int)
8588  return nullptr;
8589 
8590  Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty);
8591  return CGF.EmitNeonCall(F, Ops, s);
8592 }

8594 Value *CodeGenFunction::vectorWrapScalar16(Value *Op) {
8595  auto *VTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int16Ty, 4);
8596  Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, Int16Ty);

8598  llvm::Constant *CI = ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0);
8599  Op = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Op, CI);
8600  return Op;

8733 constexpr unsigned SVEBitsPerBlock = 128;
8734 
8735 static llvm::ScalableVectorType *getSVEVectorForElementType(llvm::Type *EltTy) {
8736  unsigned NumElts = SVEBitsPerBlock / EltTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
8737  return llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(EltTy, NumElts);
