8739 
8740 // Reinterpret the input predicate so that it can be used to correctly isolate
8741 // the elements of the specified datatype.
8742 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEPredicateCast(Value *Pred,
8743  llvm::ScalableVectorType *VTy) {
8744  auto *RTy = llvm::VectorType::get(IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 1), VTy);
8745  if (Pred->getType() == RTy)
8746  return Pred;
8747 
8748  unsigned IntID;
8749  llvm::Type *IntrinsicTy;
8750  switch (VTy->getMinNumElements()) {
8751  default:
8752  llvm_unreachable("unsupported element count!");
8753  case 2:
8754  case 4:
8755  case 8:
8756  IntID = Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_convert_from_svbool;
8757  IntrinsicTy = RTy;
8758  break;
8759  case 16:
8760  IntID = Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_convert_to_svbool;
8761  IntrinsicTy = Pred->getType();
8762  break;
8763  }
8764 
8765  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, IntrinsicTy);
8766  Value *C = Builder.CreateCall(F, Pred);
8767  assert(C->getType() == RTy && "Unexpected return type!");
8768  return C;
8769 }
8770 
8771 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEGatherLoad(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8772  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
8773  unsigned IntID) {
8774  auto *ResultTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
8775  auto *OverloadedTy =
8776  llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(SVEBuiltinMemEltTy(TypeFlags), ResultTy);
8777 
8778  // At the ACLE level there's only one predicate type, svbool_t, which is
8779  // mapped to <n x 16 x i1>. However, this might be incompatible with the
8780  // actual type being loaded. For example, when loading doubles (i64) the
8781  // predicated should be <n x 2 x i1> instead. At the IR level the type of
8782  // the predicate and the data being loaded must match. Cast accordingly.
8783  Ops[0] = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], OverloadedTy);
8784 
8785  Function *F = nullptr;
8786  if (Ops[1]->getType()->isVectorTy())
8787  // This is the "vector base, scalar offset" case. In order to uniquely
8788  // map this built-in to an LLVM IR intrinsic, we need both the return type
8789  // and the type of the vector base.
8790  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, {OverloadedTy, Ops[1]->getType()});
8791  else
8792  // This is the "scalar base, vector offset case". The type of the offset
8793  // is encoded in the name of the intrinsic. We only need to specify the
8794  // return type in order to uniquely map this built-in to an LLVM IR
8795  // intrinsic.
8796  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, OverloadedTy);
8797 
8798  // Pass 0 when the offset is missing. This can only be applied when using
8799  // the "vector base" addressing mode for which ACLE allows no offset. The
8800  // corresponding LLVM IR always requires an offset.
8801  if (Ops.size() == 2) {
8802  assert(Ops[1]->getType()->isVectorTy() && "Scalar base requires an offset");
8803  Ops.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 0));
8804  }
8805 
8806  // For "vector base, scalar index" scale the index so that it becomes a
8807  // scalar offset.
8808  if (!TypeFlags.isByteIndexed() && Ops[1]->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
8809  unsigned BytesPerElt =
8810  OverloadedTy->getElementType()->getScalarSizeInBits() / 8;
8811  Value *Scale = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, BytesPerElt);
8812  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateMul(Ops[2], Scale);
8813  }
8814 
8815  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
8816 
8817  // The following sext/zext is only needed when ResultTy != OverloadedTy. In
8818  // other cases it's folded into a nop.
8819  return TypeFlags.isZExtReturn() ? Builder.CreateZExt(Call, ResultTy)
8820  : Builder.CreateSExt(Call, ResultTy);
8821 }
8822 
8823 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEScatterStore(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8824  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
8825  unsigned IntID) {
8826  auto *SrcDataTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
8827  auto *OverloadedTy =
8828  llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(SVEBuiltinMemEltTy(TypeFlags), SrcDataTy);
8829 
8830  // In ACLE the source data is passed in the last argument, whereas in LLVM IR
8831  // it's the first argument. Move it accordingly.
8832  Ops.insert(Ops.begin(), Ops.pop_back_val());
8833 
8834  Function *F = nullptr;
8835  if (Ops[2]->getType()->isVectorTy())
8836  // This is the "vector base, scalar offset" case. In order to uniquely
8837  // map this built-in to an LLVM IR intrinsic, we need both the return type
8838  // and the type of the vector base.
8839  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, {OverloadedTy, Ops[2]->getType()});
8840  else
8841  // This is the "scalar base, vector offset case". The type of the offset
8842  // is encoded in the name of the intrinsic. We only need to specify the
8843  // return type in order to uniquely map this built-in to an LLVM IR
8844  // intrinsic.
8845  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, OverloadedTy);
8846 
8847  // Pass 0 when the offset is missing. This can only be applied when using
8848  // the "vector base" addressing mode for which ACLE allows no offset. The
8849  // corresponding LLVM IR always requires an offset.
8850  if (Ops.size() == 3) {
8851  assert(Ops[1]->getType()->isVectorTy() && "Scalar base requires an offset");
8852  Ops.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 0));
8853  }
8854 
8855  // Truncation is needed when SrcDataTy != OverloadedTy. In other cases it's
8856  // folded into a nop.
8857  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[0], OverloadedTy);
8858 
8859  // At the ACLE level there's only one predicate type, svbool_t, which is
8860  // mapped to <n x 16 x i1>. However, this might be incompatible with the
8861  // actual type being stored. For example, when storing doubles (i64) the
8862  // predicated should be <n x 2 x i1> instead. At the IR level the type of
8863  // the predicate and the data being stored must match. Cast accordingly.
8864  Ops[1] = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[1], OverloadedTy);
8865 
8866  // For "vector base, scalar index" scale the index so that it becomes a
8867  // scalar offset.
8868  if (!TypeFlags.isByteIndexed() && Ops[2]->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
8869  unsigned BytesPerElt =
8870  OverloadedTy->getElementType()->getScalarSizeInBits() / 8;
8871  Value *Scale = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, BytesPerElt);
8872  Ops[3] = Builder.CreateMul(Ops[3], Scale);
8873  }
8874 
8875  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
8876 }
8877 
8878 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEGatherPrefetch(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8879  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
8880  unsigned IntID) {
8881  // The gather prefetches are overloaded on the vector input - this can either
8882  // be the vector of base addresses or vector of offsets.
8883  auto *OverloadedTy = dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ops[1]->getType());
8884  if (!OverloadedTy)
8885  OverloadedTy = cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ops[2]->getType());
8886 
8887  // Cast the predicate from svbool_t to the right number of elements.
8888  Ops[0] = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], OverloadedTy);
8889 
8890  // vector + imm addressing modes
8891  if (Ops[1]->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
8892  if (Ops.size() == 3) {
8893  // Pass 0 for 'vector+imm' when the index is omitted.
8894  Ops.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 0));
8895 
8896  // The sv_prfop is the last operand in the builtin and IR intrinsic.
8897  std::swap(Ops[2], Ops[3]);
8898  } else {
8899  // Index needs to be passed as scaled offset.
8900  llvm::Type *MemEltTy = SVEBuiltinMemEltTy(TypeFlags);
8901  unsigned BytesPerElt = MemEltTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() / 8;
8902  Value *Scale = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, BytesPerElt);
8903  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateMul(Ops[2], Scale);
8904  }
8905  }
8906 
8907  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, OverloadedTy);
8908  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
8909 }
8910 
8911 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEStructLoad(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8912  SmallVectorImpl<Value*> &Ops,
8913  unsigned IntID) {
8914  llvm::ScalableVectorType *VTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
8915  auto VecPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy);
8916  auto EltPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
8917 
8918  unsigned N;
8919  switch (IntID) {
8920  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld2:
8921  N = 2;
8922  break;
8923  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld3:
8924  N = 3;
8925  break;
8926  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld4:
8927  N = 4;
8928  break;
8929  default:
8930  llvm_unreachable("unknown intrinsic!");
8931  }
8932  auto RetTy = llvm::VectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(),
8933  VTy->getElementCount() * N);
8934 
8935  Value *Predicate = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], VTy);
8936  Value *BasePtr= Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], VecPtrTy);
8937  Value *Offset = Ops.size() > 2 ? Ops[2] : Builder.getInt32(0);
8938  BasePtr = Builder.CreateGEP(VTy, BasePtr, Offset);
8939  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, EltPtrTy);
8940 
8941  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, {RetTy, Predicate->getType()});
8942  return Builder.CreateCall(F, { Predicate, BasePtr });
8943 }
8944 
8945 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEStructStore(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8946  SmallVectorImpl<Value*> &Ops,
8947  unsigned IntID) {
8948  llvm::ScalableVectorType *VTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
8949  auto VecPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy);
8950  auto EltPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
8951 
8952  unsigned N;
8953  switch (IntID) {
8954  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_st2:
8955  N = 2;
8956  break;
8957  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_st3:
8958  N = 3;
8959  break;
8960  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_st4:
8961  N = 4;
8962  break;
8963  default:
8964  llvm_unreachable("unknown intrinsic!");
8965  }
8966  auto TupleTy =
8967  llvm::VectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(), VTy->getElementCount() * N);
8968 
8969  Value *Predicate = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], VTy);
8970  Value *BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], VecPtrTy);
8971  Value *Offset = Ops.size() > 3 ? Ops[2] : Builder.getInt32(0);
8972  Value *Val = Ops.back();
8973  BasePtr = Builder.CreateGEP(VTy, BasePtr, Offset);
8974  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, EltPtrTy);
8975 
8976  // The llvm.aarch64.sve.st2/3/4 intrinsics take legal part vectors, so we
8977  // need to break up the tuple vector.
8978  SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 5> Operands;
8979  Function *FExtr =
8980  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_tuple_get, {VTy, TupleTy});
8981  for (unsigned I = 0; I < N; ++I)
8982  Operands.push_back(Builder.CreateCall(FExtr, {Val, Builder.getInt32(I)}));
8983  Operands.append({Predicate, BasePtr});
8984 
8985  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID, { VTy });
8986  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Operands);
8987 }
8988 
8989 // SVE2's svpmullb and svpmullt builtins are similar to the svpmullb_pair and
8990 // svpmullt_pair intrinsics, with the exception that their results are bitcast
8991 // to a wider type.
8992 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEPMull(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
8993  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
8994  unsigned BuiltinID) {
8995  // Splat scalar operand to vector (intrinsics with _n infix)
8996  if (TypeFlags.hasSplatOperand()) {
8997  unsigned OpNo = TypeFlags.getSplatOperand();
8998  Ops[OpNo] = EmitSVEDupX(Ops[OpNo]);
8999  }
9000 
9001  // The pair-wise function has a narrower overloaded type.
9002  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID, Ops[0]->getType());
9003  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[1]});
9004 
9005  // Now bitcast to the wider result type.
9006  llvm::ScalableVectorType *Ty = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9007  return EmitSVEReinterpret(Call, Ty);
9008 }
9009 
9010 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEMovl(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
9011  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops, unsigned BuiltinID) {
9012  llvm::Type *OverloadedTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9013  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID, OverloadedTy);
9014  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Builder.getInt32(0)});
9015 }
9016 
9017 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEPrefetchLoad(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
9018  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
9019  unsigned BuiltinID) {
9020  auto *MemEltTy = SVEBuiltinMemEltTy(TypeFlags);
9021  auto *VectorTy = getSVEVectorForElementType(MemEltTy);
9022  auto *MemoryTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(MemEltTy, VectorTy);
9023 
9024  Value *Predicate = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], MemoryTy);
9025  Value *BasePtr = Ops[1];
9026 
9027  // Implement the index operand if not omitted.
9028  if (Ops.size() > 3) {
9029  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, MemoryTy->getPointerTo());
9030  BasePtr = Builder.CreateGEP(MemoryTy, BasePtr, Ops[2]);
9031  }
9032 
9033  // Prefetch intriniscs always expect an i8*
9034  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Int8Ty));
9035  Value *PrfOp = Ops.back();
9036 
9037  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID, Predicate->getType());
9038  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Predicate, BasePtr, PrfOp});
9039 }
9040 
9041 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEMaskedLoad(const CallExpr *E,
9042  llvm::Type *ReturnTy,
9043  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
9044  unsigned BuiltinID,
9045  bool IsZExtReturn) {
9046  QualType LangPTy = E->getArg(1)->getType();
9047  llvm::Type *MemEltTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(
9048  LangPTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType());
9049 
9050  // The vector type that is returned may be different from the
9051  // eventual type loaded from memory.
9052  auto VectorTy = cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(ReturnTy);
9053  auto MemoryTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(MemEltTy, VectorTy);
9054 
9055  Value *Predicate = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], MemoryTy);
9056  Value *BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], MemoryTy->getPointerTo());
9057  Value *Offset = Ops.size() > 2 ? Ops[2] : Builder.getInt32(0);
9058  BasePtr = Builder.CreateGEP(MemoryTy, BasePtr, Offset);
9059 
9060  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, MemEltTy->getPointerTo());
9061  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID, MemoryTy);
9062  auto *Load =
9063  cast<llvm::Instruction>(Builder.CreateCall(F, {Predicate, BasePtr}));
9064  auto TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(LangPTy->getPointeeType());
9065  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, TBAAInfo);
9066 
9067  return IsZExtReturn ? Builder.CreateZExt(Load, VectorTy)
9068  : Builder.CreateSExt(Load, VectorTy);
9069 }
9070 
9071 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEMaskedStore(const CallExpr *E,
9072  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops,
9073  unsigned BuiltinID) {
9074  QualType LangPTy = E->getArg(1)->getType();
9075  llvm::Type *MemEltTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(
9076  LangPTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType());
9077 
9078  // The vector type that is stored may be different from the
9079  // eventual type stored to memory.
9080  auto VectorTy = cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ops.back()->getType());
9081  auto MemoryTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(MemEltTy, VectorTy);
9082 
9083  Value *Predicate = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[0], MemoryTy);
9084  Value *BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], MemoryTy->getPointerTo());
9085  Value *Offset = Ops.size() == 4 ? Ops[2] : Builder.getInt32(0);
9086  BasePtr = Builder.CreateGEP(MemoryTy, BasePtr, Offset);
9087 
9088  // Last value is always the data
9089  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops.back(), MemoryTy);
9090 
9091  BasePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(BasePtr, MemEltTy->getPointerTo());
9092  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID, MemoryTy);
9093  auto *Store =
9094  cast<llvm::Instruction>(Builder.CreateCall(F, {Val, Predicate, BasePtr}));
9095  auto TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(LangPTy->getPointeeType());
9096  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Store, TBAAInfo);
9097  return Store;
9098 }
9099 
9100 // Limit the usage of scalable llvm IR generated by the ACLE by using the
9101 // sve dup.x intrinsic instead of IRBuilder::CreateVectorSplat.
9102 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEDupX(Value *Scalar, llvm::Type *Ty) {
9103  auto F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_dup_x, Ty);
9104  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Scalar);
9105 }
9106 
9107 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEDupX(Value* Scalar) {
9108  return EmitSVEDupX(Scalar, getSVEVectorForElementType(Scalar->getType()));
9109 }
9110 
9111 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSVEReinterpret(Value *Val, llvm::Type *Ty) {
9112  // FIXME: For big endian this needs an additional REV, or needs a separate
9113  // intrinsic that is code-generated as a no-op, because the LLVM bitcast
9114  // instruction is defined as 'bitwise' equivalent from memory point of
9115  // view (when storing/reloading), whereas the svreinterpret builtin
9116  // implements bitwise equivalent cast from register point of view.
9117  // LLVM CodeGen for a bitcast must add an explicit REV for big-endian.
9118  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, Ty);
9119 }
9120 
9121 static void InsertExplicitZeroOperand(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Type *Ty,
9122  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops) {
9123  auto *SplatZero = Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
9124  Ops.insert(Ops.begin(), SplatZero);
9125 }
9126 
9127 static void InsertExplicitUndefOperand(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Type *Ty,
9128  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Ops) {
9129  auto *SplatUndef = UndefValue::get(Ty);
9130  Ops.insert(Ops.begin(), SplatUndef);
9131 }
9132 
9133 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2>
9134 CodeGenFunction::getSVEOverloadTypes(const SVETypeFlags &TypeFlags,
9135  llvm::Type *ResultType,
9136  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
9137  if (TypeFlags.isOverloadNone())
9138  return {};
9139 
9140  llvm::Type *DefaultType = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9141 
9142  if (TypeFlags.isOverloadWhile())
9143  return {DefaultType, Ops[1]->getType()};
9144 
9145  if (TypeFlags.isOverloadWhileRW())
9146  return {getSVEPredType(TypeFlags), Ops[0]->getType()};
9147 
9148  if (TypeFlags.isOverloadCvt() || TypeFlags.isTupleSet())
9149  return {Ops[0]->getType(), Ops.back()->getType()};
9150 
9151  if (TypeFlags.isTupleCreate() || TypeFlags.isTupleGet())
9152  return {ResultType, Ops[0]->getType()};
9153 
9154  assert(TypeFlags.isOverloadDefault() && "Unexpected value for overloads");
9155  return {DefaultType};
9156 }
9157 
9158 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitAArch64SVEBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
9159  const CallExpr *E) {
9160  // Find out if any arguments are required to be integer constant expressions.
9161  unsigned ICEArguments = 0;
9162  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error;
9163  getContext().GetBuiltinType(BuiltinID, Error, &ICEArguments);
9164  assert(Error == ASTContext::GE_None && "Should not codegen an error");
9165 
9166  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertType(E->getType());
9167  if (BuiltinID >= SVE::BI__builtin_sve_reinterpret_s8_s8 &&
9168  BuiltinID <= SVE::BI__builtin_sve_reinterpret_f64_f64) {
9169  Value *Val = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9170  return EmitSVEReinterpret(Val, Ty);
9171  }
9172 
9173  llvm::SmallVector<Value *, 4> Ops;
9174  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; i++) {
9175  if ((ICEArguments & (1 << i)) == 0)
9176  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
9177  else {
9178  // If this is required to be a constant, constant fold it so that we know
9179  // that the generated intrinsic gets a ConstantInt.
9180  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result =
9181  E->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
9182  assert(Result && "Expected argument to be a constant");
9183 
9184  // Immediates for SVE llvm intrinsics are always 32bit. We can safely
9185  // truncate because the immediate has been range checked and no valid
9186  // immediate requires more than a handful of bits.
9187  *Result = Result->extOrTrunc(32);
9188  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(getLLVMContext(), *Result));
9189  }
9190  }
9191 
9192  auto *Builtin = findARMVectorIntrinsicInMap(AArch64SVEIntrinsicMap, BuiltinID,
9193  AArch64SVEIntrinsicsProvenSorted);
9194  SVETypeFlags TypeFlags(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9195  if (TypeFlags.isLoad())
9196  return EmitSVEMaskedLoad(E, Ty, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic,
9197  TypeFlags.isZExtReturn());
9198  else if (TypeFlags.isStore())
9199  return EmitSVEMaskedStore(E, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9200  else if (TypeFlags.isGatherLoad())
9201  return EmitSVEGatherLoad(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9202  else if (TypeFlags.isScatterStore())
9203  return EmitSVEScatterStore(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9204  else if (TypeFlags.isPrefetch())
9205  return EmitSVEPrefetchLoad(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9206  else if (TypeFlags.isGatherPrefetch())
9207  return EmitSVEGatherPrefetch(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9208  else if (TypeFlags.isStructLoad())
9209  return EmitSVEStructLoad(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9210  else if (TypeFlags.isStructStore())
9211  return EmitSVEStructStore(TypeFlags, Ops, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic);
9212  else if (TypeFlags.isUndef())
9213  return UndefValue::get(Ty);
9214  else if (Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic != 0) {
9215  if (TypeFlags.getMergeType() == SVETypeFlags::MergeZeroExp)
9216  InsertExplicitZeroOperand(Builder, Ty, Ops);
9217 
9218  if (TypeFlags.getMergeType() == SVETypeFlags::MergeAnyExp)
9219  InsertExplicitUndefOperand(Builder, Ty, Ops);
9220 
9221  // Some ACLE builtins leave out the argument to specify the predicate
9222  // pattern, which is expected to be expanded to an SV_ALL pattern.
9223  if (TypeFlags.isAppendSVALL())
9224  Ops.push_back(Builder.getInt32(/*SV_ALL*/ 31));
9225  if (TypeFlags.isInsertOp1SVALL())
9226  Ops.insert(&Ops[1], Builder.getInt32(/*SV_ALL*/ 31));
9227 
9228  // Predicates must match the main datatype.
9229  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i)
9230  if (auto PredTy = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ops[i]->getType()))
9231  if (PredTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(1))
9232  Ops[i] = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Ops[i], getSVEType(TypeFlags));
9233 
9234  // Splat scalar operand to vector (intrinsics with _n infix)
9235  if (TypeFlags.hasSplatOperand()) {
9236  unsigned OpNo = TypeFlags.getSplatOperand();
9237  Ops[OpNo] = EmitSVEDupX(Ops[OpNo]);
9238  }
9239 
9240  if (TypeFlags.isReverseCompare())
9241  std::swap(Ops[1], Ops[2]);
9242 
9243  if (TypeFlags.isReverseUSDOT())
9244  std::swap(Ops[1], Ops[2]);
9245 
9246  // Predicated intrinsics with _z suffix need a select w/ zeroinitializer.
9247  if (TypeFlags.getMergeType() == SVETypeFlags::MergeZero) {
9248  llvm::Type *OpndTy = Ops[1]->getType();
9249  auto *SplatZero = Constant::getNullValue(OpndTy);
9250  Function *Sel = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_sel, OpndTy);
9251  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(Sel, {Ops[0], Ops[1], SplatZero});
9252  }
9253 
9254  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic,
9255  getSVEOverloadTypes(TypeFlags, Ty, Ops));
9256  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
9257 
9258  // Predicate results must be converted to svbool_t.
9259  if (auto PredTy = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Call->getType()))
9260  if (PredTy->getScalarType()->isIntegerTy(1))
9261  Call = EmitSVEPredicateCast(Call, cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ty));
9262 
9263  return Call;
9264  }
9265 
9266  switch (BuiltinID) {
9267  default:
9268  return nullptr;
9269 
9270  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmov_b_z: {
9271  // svmov_b_z(pg, op) <=> svand_b_z(pg, op, op)
9272  SVETypeFlags TypeFlags(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9273  llvm::Type* OverloadedTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9274  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_and_z, OverloadedTy);
9275  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[1]});
9276  }
9277 
9278  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svnot_b_z: {
9279  // svnot_b_z(pg, op) <=> sveor_b_z(pg, op, pg)
9280  SVETypeFlags TypeFlags(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9281  llvm::Type* OverloadedTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9282  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_eor_z, OverloadedTy);
9283  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[0]});
9284  }
9285 
9286  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_u16:
9287  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_u32:
9288  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_u64:
9289  return EmitSVEMovl(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ushllb);
9290 
9291  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_s16:
9292  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_s32:
9293  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlb_s64:
9294  return EmitSVEMovl(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_sshllb);
9295 
9296  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_u16:
9297  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_u32:
9298  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_u64:
9299  return EmitSVEMovl(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ushllt);
9300 
9301  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_s16:
9302  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_s32:
9303  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svmovlt_s64:
9304  return EmitSVEMovl(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_sshllt);
9305 
9306  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullt_u16:
9307  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullt_u64:
9308  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullt_n_u16:
9309  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullt_n_u64:
9310  return EmitSVEPMull(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_pmullt_pair);
9311 
9312  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullb_u16:
9313  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullb_u64:
9314  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullb_n_u16:
9315  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpmullb_n_u64:
9316  return EmitSVEPMull(TypeFlags, Ops, Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_pmullb_pair);
9317 
9318  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_n_b8:
9319  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_n_b16:
9320  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_n_b32:
9321  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_n_b64: {
9322  Value *CmpNE =
9323  Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops[0], Constant::getNullValue(Ops[0]->getType()));
9324  llvm::ScalableVectorType *OverloadedTy = getSVEType(TypeFlags);
9325  Value *Dup = EmitSVEDupX(CmpNE, OverloadedTy);
9326  return EmitSVEPredicateCast(Dup, cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ty));
9327  }
9328 
9329  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_b8:
9330  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_b16:
9331  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_b32:
9332  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_b64:
9333  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_u8:
9334  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_s8:
9335  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_u64:
9336  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_f64:
9337  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_s64:
9338  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_u16:
9339  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_f16:
9340  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_bf16:
9341  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_s16:
9342  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_u32:
9343  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_f32:
9344  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdupq_n_s32: {
9345  // These builtins are implemented by storing each element to an array and using
9346  // ld1rq to materialize a vector.
9347  unsigned NumOpnds = Ops.size();
9348 
9349  bool IsBoolTy =
9350  cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ty)->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(1);
9351 
9352  // For svdupq_n_b* the element type of is an integer of type 128/numelts,
9353  // so that the compare can use the width that is natural for the expected
9354  // number of predicate lanes.
9355  llvm::Type *EltTy = Ops[0]->getType();
9356  if (IsBoolTy)
9357  EltTy = IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), SVEBitsPerBlock / NumOpnds);
9358 
9359  SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> VecOps;
9360  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumOpnds; ++I)
9361  VecOps.push_back(Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[I], EltTy));
9362  Value *Vec = BuildVector(VecOps);
9363 
9364  SVETypeFlags TypeFlags(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9365  Value *Pred = EmitSVEAllTruePred(TypeFlags);
9366 
9367  llvm::Type *OverloadedTy = getSVEVectorForElementType(EltTy);
9368  Value *InsertSubVec = Builder.CreateInsertVector(
9369  OverloadedTy, UndefValue::get(OverloadedTy), Vec, Builder.getInt64(0));
9370 
9371  Function *F =
9372  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_dupq_lane, OverloadedTy);
9373  Value *DupQLane =
9374  Builder.CreateCall(F, {InsertSubVec, Builder.getInt64(0)});
9375 
9376  if (!IsBoolTy)
9377  return DupQLane;
9378 
9379  // For svdupq_n_b* we need to add an additional 'cmpne' with '0'.
9380  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(NumOpnds == 2 ? Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_cmpne
9381  : Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_cmpne_wide,
9382  OverloadedTy);
9383  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(
9384  F, {Pred, DupQLane, EmitSVEDupX(Builder.getInt64(0))});
9385  return EmitSVEPredicateCast(Call, cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ty));
9386  }
9387 
9388  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svpfalse_b:
9389  return ConstantInt::getFalse(Ty);
9390 
9391  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_bf16:
9392  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_f16:
9393  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_f32:
9394  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_f64:
9395  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_s8:
9396  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_s16:
9397  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_s32:
9398  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_s64:
9399  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_u8:
9400  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_u16:
9401  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_u32:
9402  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svlen_u64: {
9403  SVETypeFlags TF(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9404  auto VTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(getSVEType(TF));
9405  auto *NumEls =
9406  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ty, VTy->getElementCount().getKnownMinValue());
9407 
9408  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::vscale, Ty);
9409  return Builder.CreateMul(NumEls, Builder.CreateCall(F));
9410  }
9411 
9412  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_u8:
9413  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_s8:
9414  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_u16:
9415  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_s16:
9416  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_u32:
9417  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_s32:
9418  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_u64:
9419  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_s64:
9420  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_f16:
9421  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_bf16:
9422  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_f32:
9423  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svtbl2_f64: {
9424  SVETypeFlags TF(Builtin->TypeModifier);
9425  auto VTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(getSVEType(TF));
9426  auto TupleTy = llvm::VectorType::getDoubleElementsVectorType(VTy);
9427  Function *FExtr =
9428  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_tuple_get, {VTy, TupleTy});
9429  Value *V0 = Builder.CreateCall(FExtr, {Ops[0], Builder.getInt32(0)});
9430  Value *V1 = Builder.CreateCall(FExtr, {Ops[0], Builder.getInt32(1)});
9431  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_tbl2, VTy);
9432  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {V0, V1, Ops[1]});
9433  }
9434 
9435  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_s8:
9436  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_s16:
9437  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_s32:
9438  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_s64:
9439  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_u8:
9440  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_u16:
9441  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_u32:
9442  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_u64:
9443  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_f16:
9444  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_f32:
9445  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_f64:
9446  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svset_neonq_bf16: {
9447  return Builder.CreateInsertVector(Ty, Ops[0], Ops[1], Builder.getInt64(0));
9448  }
9449 
9450  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_s8:
9451  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_s16:
9452  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_s32:
9453  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_s64:
9454  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_u8:
9455  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_u16:
9456  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_u32:
9457  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_u64:
9458  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_f16:
9459  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_f32:
9460  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_f64:
9461  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svget_neonq_bf16: {
9462  return Builder.CreateExtractVector(Ty, Ops[0], Builder.getInt64(0));
9463  }
9464 
9465  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_s8:
9466  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_s16:
9467  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_s32:
9468  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_s64:
9469  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_u8:
9470  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_u16:
9471  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_u32:
9472  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_u64:
9473  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_f16:
9474  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_f32:
9475  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_f64:
9476  case SVE::BI__builtin_sve_svdup_neonq_bf16: {
9477  Value *Insert = Builder.CreateInsertVector(Ty, UndefValue::get(Ty), Ops[0],
9478  Builder.getInt64(0));
9479  return Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_dupq_lane, {Ty},
9480  {Insert, Builder.getInt64(0)});
9481  }
9482  }
9483 
9484  /// Should not happen
9485  return nullptr;
9486 }
9487 
9488 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitAArch64BuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
9489  const CallExpr *E,
9490  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch) {
9491  if (BuiltinID >= AArch64::FirstSVEBuiltin &&
9492  BuiltinID <= AArch64::LastSVEBuiltin)
9493  return EmitAArch64SVEBuiltinExpr(BuiltinID, E);
9494 
9495  unsigned HintID = static_cast<unsigned>(-1);
9496  switch (BuiltinID) {
9497  default: break;
9498  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_nop:
9499  HintID = 0;
9500  break;
9501  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_yield:
9502  case AArch64::BI__yield:
9503  HintID = 1;
9504  break;
9505  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wfe:
9506  case AArch64::BI__wfe:
9507  HintID = 2;
9508  break;
9509  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wfi:
9510  case AArch64::BI__wfi:
9511  HintID = 3;
9512  break;
9513  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_sev:
9514  case AArch64::BI__sev:
9515  HintID = 4;
9516  break;
9517  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_sevl:
9518  case AArch64::BI__sevl:
9519  HintID = 5;
9520  break;
9521  }
9522 
9523  if (HintID != static_cast<unsigned>(-1)) {
9524  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_hint);
9525  return Builder.CreateCall(F, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, HintID));
9526  }
9527 
9528  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_prefetch) {
9529  Value *Address = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9530  Value *RW = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9531  Value *CacheLevel = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
9532  Value *RetentionPolicy = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3));
9533  Value *IsData = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(4));
9534 
9535  Value *Locality = nullptr;
9536  if (cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RetentionPolicy)->isZero()) {
9537  // Temporal fetch, needs to convert cache level to locality.
9538  Locality = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty,
9539  -cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CacheLevel)->getValue() + 3);
9540  } else {
9541  // Streaming fetch.
9542  Locality = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0);
9543  }
9544 
9545  // FIXME: We need AArch64 specific LLVM intrinsic if we want to specify
9546  // PLDL3STRM or PLDL2STRM.
9547  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::prefetch, Address->getType());
9548  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Address, RW, Locality, IsData});
9549  }
9550 
9551  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rbit) {
9552  assert((getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()) == 32) &&
9553  "rbit of unusual size!");
9554  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9555  return Builder.CreateCall(
9556  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bitreverse, Arg->getType()), Arg, "rbit");
9557  }
9558  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rbit64) {
9559  assert((getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()) == 64) &&
9560  "rbit of unusual size!");
9561  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9562  return Builder.CreateCall(
9563  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bitreverse, Arg->getType()), Arg, "rbit");
9564  }
9565 
9566  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_cls) {
9567  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9568  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_cls), Arg,
9569  "cls");
9570  }
9571  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_cls64) {
9572  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9573  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_cls64), Arg,
9574  "cls");
9575  }
9576 
9577  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint32zf ||
9578  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint32z) {
9579  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9580  llvm::Type *Ty = Arg->getType();
9581  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_frint32z, Ty),
9582  Arg, "frint32z");
9583  }
9584 
9585  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint64zf ||
9586  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint64z) {
9587  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9588  llvm::Type *Ty = Arg->getType();
9589  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_frint64z, Ty),
9590  Arg, "frint64z");
9591  }
9592 
9593  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint32xf ||
9594  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint32x) {
9595  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9596  llvm::Type *Ty = Arg->getType();
9597  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_frint32x, Ty),
9598  Arg, "frint32x");
9599  }
9600 
9601  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint64xf ||
9602  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_frint64x) {
9603  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9604  llvm::Type *Ty = Arg->getType();
9605  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_frint64x, Ty),
9606  Arg, "frint64x");
9607  }
9608 
9609  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_jcvt) {
9610  assert((getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()) == 32) &&
9611  "__jcvt of unusual size!");
9612  llvm::Value *Arg = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9613  return Builder.CreateCall(
9614  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_fjcvtzs), Arg);
9615  }
9616 
9617  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ld64b ||
9618  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_st64b ||
9619  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_st64bv ||
9620  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_st64bv0) {
9621  llvm::Value *MemAddr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9622  llvm::Value *ValPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9623 
9624  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ld64b) {
9625  // Load from the address via an LLVM intrinsic, receiving a
9626  // tuple of 8 i64 words, and store each one to ValPtr.
9627  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_ld64b);
9628  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F, MemAddr);
9629  llvm::Value *ToRet;
9630  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
9631  llvm::Value *ValOffsetPtr =
9632  Builder.CreateGEP(Int64Ty, ValPtr, Builder.getInt32(i));
9633  Address Addr =
9634  Address(ValOffsetPtr, Int64Ty, CharUnits::fromQuantity(8));
9635  ToRet = Builder.CreateStore(Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, i), Addr);
9636  }
9637  return ToRet;
9638  } else {
9639  // Load 8 i64 words from ValPtr, and store them to the address
9640  // via an LLVM intrinsic.
9641  SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 9> Args;
9642  Args.push_back(MemAddr);
9643  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
9644  llvm::Value *ValOffsetPtr =
9645  Builder.CreateGEP(Int64Ty, ValPtr, Builder.getInt32(i));
9646  Address Addr =
9647  Address(ValOffsetPtr, Int64Ty, CharUnits::fromQuantity(8));
9648  Args.push_back(Builder.CreateLoad(Addr));
9649  }
9650 
9651  auto Intr = (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_st64b
9652  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_st64b
9653  : BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_st64bv
9654  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_st64bv
9655  : Intrinsic::aarch64_st64bv0);
9656  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intr);
9657  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Args);
9658  }
9659  }
9660 
9661  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rndr ||
9662  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rndrrs) {
9663 
9664  auto Intr = (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rndr
9665  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_rndr
9666  : Intrinsic::aarch64_rndrrs);
9667  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intr);
9668  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F);
9669  Value *RandomValue = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 0);
9670  Value *Status = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 1);
9671 
9672  Address MemAddress = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
9673  Builder.CreateStore(RandomValue, MemAddress);
9674  Status = Builder.CreateZExt(Status, Int32Ty);
9675  return Status;
9676  }
9677 
9678  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__clear_cache) {
9679  assert(E->getNumArgs() == 2 && "__clear_cache takes 2 arguments");
9680  const FunctionDecl *FD = E->getDirectCallee();
9681  Value *Ops[2];
9682  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 2; i++)
9683  Ops[i] = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i));
9684  llvm::Type *Ty = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(FD->getType());
9685  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = cast<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty);
9686  StringRef Name = FD->getName();
9687  return EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, Name), Ops);
9688  }
9689 
9690  if ((BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
9691  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex) &&
9692  getContext().getTypeSize(E->getType()) == 128) {
9693  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex
9694  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_ldaxp
9695  : Intrinsic::aarch64_ldxp);
9696 
9697  Value *LdPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9698  Value *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F, Builder.CreateBitCast(LdPtr, Int8PtrTy),
9699  "ldxp");
9700 
9701  Value *Val0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 1);
9702  Value *Val1 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 0);
9703  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 128);
9704  Val0 = Builder.CreateZExt(Val0, Int128Ty);
9705  Val1 = Builder.CreateZExt(Val1, Int128Ty);
9706 
9707  Value *ShiftCst = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int128Ty, 64);
9708  Val = Builder.CreateShl(Val0, ShiftCst, "shl", true /* nuw */);
9709  Val = Builder.CreateOr(Val, Val1);
9710  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, ConvertType(E->getType()));
9711  } else if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldrex ||
9712  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex) {
9713  Value *LoadAddr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9714 
9715  QualType Ty = E->getType();
9716  llvm::Type *RealResTy = ConvertType(Ty);
9717  llvm::Type *IntTy =
9718  llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), getContext().getTypeSize(Ty));
9719  llvm::Type *PtrTy = IntTy->getPointerTo();
9720  LoadAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(LoadAddr, PtrTy);
9721 
9722  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldaex
9723  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_ldaxr
9724  : Intrinsic::aarch64_ldxr,
9725  PtrTy);
9726  CallInst *Val = Builder.CreateCall(F, LoadAddr, "ldxr");
9727  Val->addParamAttr(
9728  0, Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), Attribute::ElementType, IntTy));
9729 
9730  if (RealResTy->isPointerTy())
9731  return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, RealResTy);
9732 
9733  llvm::Type *IntResTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(
9734  getLLVMContext(), CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(RealResTy));
9735  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(Val, IntResTy),
9736  RealResTy);
9737  }
9738 
9739  if ((BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
9740  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) &&
9741  getContext().getTypeSize(E->getArg(0)->getType()) == 128) {
9742  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex
9743  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_stlxp
9744  : Intrinsic::aarch64_stxp);
9745  llvm::Type *STy = llvm::StructType::get(Int64Ty, Int64Ty);
9746 
9747  Address Tmp = CreateMemTemp(E->getArg(0)->getType());
9748  EmitAnyExprToMem(E->getArg(0), Tmp, Qualifiers(), /*init*/ true);
9749 
9750  Tmp = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Tmp, STy);
9751  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateLoad(Tmp);
9752 
9753  Value *Arg0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 0);
9754  Value *Arg1 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, 1);
9755  Value *StPtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)),
9756  Int8PtrTy);
9757  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg0, Arg1, StPtr}, "stxp");
9758  }
9759 
9760  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_strex ||
9761  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex) {
9762  Value *StoreVal = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9763  Value *StoreAddr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9764 
9765  QualType Ty = E->getArg(0)->getType();
9766  llvm::Type *StoreTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(),
9767  getContext().getTypeSize(Ty));
9768  StoreAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(StoreAddr, StoreTy->getPointerTo());
9769 
9770  if (StoreVal->getType()->isPointerTy())
9771  StoreVal = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(StoreVal, Int64Ty);
9772  else {
9773  llvm::Type *IntTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(
9774  getLLVMContext(),
9775  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(StoreVal->getType()));
9776  StoreVal = Builder.CreateBitCast(StoreVal, IntTy);
9777  StoreVal = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(StoreVal, Int64Ty);
9778  }
9779 
9780  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stlex
9781  ? Intrinsic::aarch64_stlxr
9782  : Intrinsic::aarch64_stxr,
9783  StoreAddr->getType());
9784  CallInst *CI = Builder.CreateCall(F, {StoreVal, StoreAddr}, "stxr");
9785  CI->addParamAttr(
9786  1, Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), Attribute::ElementType, StoreTy));
9787  return CI;
9788  }
9789 
9790  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__getReg) {
9791  Expr::EvalResult Result;
9792  if (!E->getArg(0)->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGM.getContext()))
9793  llvm_unreachable("Sema will ensure that the parameter is constant");
9794 
9795  llvm::APSInt Value = Result.Val.getInt();
9796  LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
9797  std::string Reg = Value == 31 ? "sp" : "x" + toString(Value, 10);
9798 
9799  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {llvm::MDString::get(Context, Reg)};
9800  llvm::MDNode *RegName = llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Ops);
9801  llvm::Value *Metadata = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Context, RegName);
9802 
9803  llvm::Function *F =
9804  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::read_register, {Int64Ty});
9805  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Metadata);
9806  }
9807 
9808  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_clrex) {
9809  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_clrex);
9810  return Builder.CreateCall(F);
9811  }
9812 
9813  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_ReadWriteBarrier)
9814  return Builder.CreateFence(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent,
9815  llvm::SyncScope::SingleThread);
9816 
9817  // CRC32
9818  Intrinsic::ID CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
9819  switch (BuiltinID) {
9820  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32b:
9821  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32b; break;
9822  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cb:
9823  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32cb; break;
9824  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32h:
9825  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32h; break;
9826  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32ch:
9827  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32ch; break;
9828  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32w:
9829  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32w; break;
9830  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cw:
9831  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32cw; break;
9832  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32d:
9833  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32x; break;
9834  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_crc32cd:
9835  CRCIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_crc32cx; break;
9836  }
9837 
9838  if (CRCIntrinsicID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
9839  Value *Arg0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9840  Value *Arg1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9841  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CRCIntrinsicID);
9842 
9843  llvm::Type *DataTy = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(1);
9844  Arg1 = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(Arg1, DataTy);
9845 
9846  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Arg0, Arg1});
9847  }
9848 
9849  // Memory Operations (MOPS)
9850  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_mops_memset_tag) {
9851  Value *Dst = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9852  Value *Val = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9853  Value *Size = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
9854  Dst = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Dst, Int8PtrTy);
9855  Val = Builder.CreateTrunc(Val, Int8Ty);
9856  Size = Builder.CreateIntCast(Size, Int64Ty, false);
9857  return Builder.CreateCall(
9858  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_mops_memset_tag), {Dst, Val, Size});
9859  }
9860 
9861  // Memory Tagging Extensions (MTE) Intrinsics
9862  Intrinsic::ID MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
9863  switch (BuiltinID) {
9864  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_irg:
9865  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_irg; break;
9866  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_addg:
9867  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_addg; break;
9868  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_gmi:
9869  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_gmi; break;
9870  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_ldg:
9871  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_ldg; break;
9872  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_stg:
9873  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_stg; break;
9874  case AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_subp:
9875  MTEIntrinsicID = Intrinsic::aarch64_subp; break;
9876  }
9877 
9878  if (MTEIntrinsicID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
9879  llvm::Type *T = ConvertType(E->getType());
9880 
9881  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_irg) {
9882  Value *Pointer = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9883  Value *Mask = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9884 
9885  Pointer = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Pointer, Int8PtrTy);
9886  Mask = Builder.CreateZExt(Mask, Int64Ty);
9887  Value *RV = Builder.CreateCall(
9888  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {Pointer, Mask});
9889  return Builder.CreatePointerCast(RV, T);
9890  }
9891  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_addg) {
9892  Value *Pointer = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9893  Value *TagOffset = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9894 
9895  Pointer = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Pointer, Int8PtrTy);
9896  TagOffset = Builder.CreateZExt(TagOffset, Int64Ty);
9897  Value *RV = Builder.CreateCall(
9898  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {Pointer, TagOffset});
9899  return Builder.CreatePointerCast(RV, T);
9900  }
9901  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_gmi) {
9902  Value *Pointer = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9903  Value *ExcludedMask = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9904 
9905  ExcludedMask = Builder.CreateZExt(ExcludedMask, Int64Ty);
9906  Pointer = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Pointer, Int8PtrTy);
9907  return Builder.CreateCall(
9908  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {Pointer, ExcludedMask});
9909  }
9910  // Although it is possible to supply a different return
9911  // address (first arg) to this intrinsic, for now we set
9912  // return address same as input address.
9913  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_ldg) {
9914  Value *TagAddress = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9915  TagAddress = Builder.CreatePointerCast(TagAddress, Int8PtrTy);
9916  Value *RV = Builder.CreateCall(
9917  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {TagAddress, TagAddress});
9918  return Builder.CreatePointerCast(RV, T);
9919  }
9920  // Although it is possible to supply a different tag (to set)
9921  // to this intrinsic (as first arg), for now we supply
9922  // the tag that is in input address arg (common use case).
9923  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_stg) {
9924  Value *TagAddress = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9925  TagAddress = Builder.CreatePointerCast(TagAddress, Int8PtrTy);
9926  return Builder.CreateCall(
9927  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {TagAddress, TagAddress});
9928  }
9929  if (MTEIntrinsicID == Intrinsic::aarch64_subp) {
9930  Value *PointerA = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
9931  Value *PointerB = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
9932  PointerA = Builder.CreatePointerCast(PointerA, Int8PtrTy);
9933  PointerB = Builder.CreatePointerCast(PointerB, Int8PtrTy);
9934  return Builder.CreateCall(
9935  CGM.getIntrinsic(MTEIntrinsicID), {PointerA, PointerB});
9936  }
9937  }
9938 
9939  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
9940  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
9941  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
9942  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr ||
9943  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr64 ||
9944  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp) {
9945 
9946  SpecialRegisterAccessKind AccessKind = Write;
9947  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr ||
9948  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr64 ||
9949  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp)
9950  AccessKind = VolatileRead;
9951 
9952  bool IsPointerBuiltin = BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsrp ||
9953  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsrp;
9954 
9955  bool Is64Bit = BuiltinID != AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_rsr &&
9956  BuiltinID != AArch64::BI__builtin_arm_wsr;
9957 
9958  llvm::Type *ValueType;
9959  llvm::Type *RegisterType = Int64Ty;
9960  if (IsPointerBuiltin) {
9961  ValueType = VoidPtrTy;
9962  } else if (Is64Bit) {
9963  ValueType = Int64Ty;
9964  } else {
9965  ValueType = Int32Ty;
9966  }
9967 
9968  return EmitSpecialRegisterBuiltin(*this, E, RegisterType, ValueType,
9969  AccessKind);
9970  }
9971 
9972  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_ReadStatusReg ||
9973  BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_WriteStatusReg) {
9974  LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
9975 
9976  unsigned SysReg =
9977  E->getArg(0)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext()).getZExtValue();
9978 
9979  std::string SysRegStr;
9980  llvm::raw_string_ostream(SysRegStr) <<
9981  ((1 << 1) | ((SysReg >> 14) & 1)) << ":" <<
9982  ((SysReg >> 11) & 7) << ":" <<
9983  ((SysReg >> 7) & 15) << ":" <<
9984  ((SysReg >> 3) & 15) << ":" <<
9985  ( SysReg & 7);
9986 
9987  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = { llvm::MDString::get(Context, SysRegStr) };
9988  llvm::MDNode *RegName = llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Ops);
9989  llvm::Value *Metadata = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Context, RegName);
9990 
9991  llvm::Type *RegisterType = Int64Ty;
9992  llvm::Type *Types[] = { RegisterType };
9993 
9994  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_ReadStatusReg) {
9995  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::read_register, Types);
9996 
9997  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Metadata);
9998  }
9999 
10000  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::write_register, Types);
10001  llvm::Value *ArgValue = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
10002 
10003  return Builder.CreateCall(F, { Metadata, ArgValue });
10004  }
10005 
10006  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI_AddressOfReturnAddress) {
10007  llvm::Function *F =
10008  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::addressofreturnaddress, AllocaInt8PtrTy);
10009  return Builder.CreateCall(F);
10010  }
10011 
10012  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__builtin_sponentry) {
10013  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sponentry, AllocaInt8PtrTy);
10014  return Builder.CreateCall(F);
10015  }
10016 
10017  if (BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__mulh || BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__umulh) {
10018  llvm::Type *ResType = ConvertType(E->getType());
10019  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 128);
10020 
10021  bool IsSigned = BuiltinID == AArch64::BI__mulh;
10022  Value *LHS =
10023  Builder.CreateIntCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), Int128Ty, IsSigned);
10024  Value *RHS =
10025  Builder.CreateIntCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)), Int128Ty, IsSigned);
10026 
10027  Value *MulResult, *HigherBits;
10028  if (IsSigned) {
10029  MulResult = Builder.CreateNSWMul(LHS, RHS);
10030  HigherBits = Builder.CreateAShr(MulResult, 64);
10031  } else {
10032  MulResult = Builder.CreateNUWMul(LHS, RHS);
10033  HigherBits = Builder.CreateLShr(MulResult, 64);
10034  }
10035  HigherBits = Builder.CreateIntCast(HigherBits, ResType, IsSigned);
10036 
10037  return HigherBits;
10038  }
10039 
10040  // Handle MSVC intrinsics before argument evaluation to prevent double
10041  // evaluation.
10042  if (Optional<MSVCIntrin> MsvcIntId = translateAarch64ToMsvcIntrin(BuiltinID))
10043  return EmitMSVCBuiltinExpr(*MsvcIntId, E);
10044 
10045  // Find out if any arguments are required to be integer constant
10046  // expressions.
10047  unsigned ICEArguments = 0;
10048  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error;
10049  getContext().GetBuiltinType(BuiltinID, Error, &ICEArguments);
10050  assert(Error == ASTContext::GE_None && "Should not codegen an error");
10051 
10052  llvm::SmallVector<Value*, 4> Ops;
10053  Address PtrOp0 = Address::invalid();
10054  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs() - 1; i != e; i++) {
10055  if (i == 0) {
10056  switch (BuiltinID) {
10057  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_v:
10058  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_v:
10059  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_dup_v:
10060  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_dup_v:
10061  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_lane_v:
10062  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_lane_v:
10063  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_v:
10064  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_v:
10065  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_lane_v:
10066  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_lane_v:
10067  // Get the alignment for the argument in addition to the value;
10068  // we'll use it later.
10069  PtrOp0 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
10070  Ops.push_back(PtrOp0.getPointer());
10071  continue;
10072  }
10073  }
10074  if ((ICEArguments & (1 << i)) == 0) {
10075  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
10076  } else {
10077  // If this is required to be a constant, constant fold it so that we know
10078  // that the generated intrinsic gets a ConstantInt.
10079  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
10080  getLLVMContext(),
10081  *E->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext())));
10082  }
10083  }
10084 
10085  auto SISDMap = makeArrayRef(AArch64SISDIntrinsicMap);
10086  const ARMVectorIntrinsicInfo *Builtin = findARMVectorIntrinsicInMap(
10087  SISDMap, BuiltinID, AArch64SISDIntrinsicsProvenSorted);
10088 
10089  if (Builtin) {
10090  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(E->getNumArgs() - 1)));
10091  Value *Result = EmitCommonNeonSISDBuiltinExpr(*this, *Builtin, Ops, E);
10092  assert(Result && "SISD intrinsic should have been handled");
10093  return Result;
10094  }
10095 
10096  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(E->getNumArgs()-1);
10097  NeonTypeFlags Type(0);
10098  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Result = Arg->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext()))
10099  // Determine the type of this overloaded NEON intrinsic.
10100  Type = NeonTypeFlags(Result->getZExtValue());
10101 
10102  bool usgn = Type.isUnsigned();
10103  bool quad = Type.isQuad();
10104 
10105  // Handle non-overloaded intrinsics first.
10106  switch (BuiltinID) {
10107  default: break;
10108  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vabsh_f16:
10109  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)));
10110  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, HalfTy), Ops, "vabs");
10111  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vaddq_p128: {
10112  llvm::Type *Ty = GetNeonType(this, NeonTypeFlags::Poly128);
10113  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)));
10114  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
10115  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
10116  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateXor(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
10117  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(), 128);
10118  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Int128Ty);
10119  }
10120  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vldrq_p128: {
10121  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(), 128);
10122  llvm::Type *Int128PTy = llvm::PointerType::get(Int128Ty, 0);
10123  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), Int128PTy);
10124  return Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Int128Ty, Ptr,
10125  CharUnits::fromQuantity(16));
10126  }
10127  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vstrq_p128: {
10128  llvm::Type *Int128PTy = llvm::Type::getIntNPtrTy(getLLVMContext(), 128);
10129  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Int128PTy);
10130  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)), Ptr);
10131  }
10132  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvts_f32_u32:
10133  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtd_f64_u64:
10134  usgn = true;
10135  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
10136  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvts_f32_s32:
10137  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtd_f64_s64: {
10138  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)));
10139  bool Is64 = Ops[0]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 64;
10140  llvm::Type *InTy = Is64 ? Int64Ty : Int32Ty;
10141  llvm::Type *FTy = Is64 ? DoubleTy : FloatTy;
10142  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], InTy);
10143  if (usgn)
10144  return Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[0], FTy);
10145  return Builder.CreateSIToFP(Ops[0], FTy);
10146  }
10147  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_u16:
10148  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_u32:
10149  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_u64:
10150  usgn = true;
10151  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
10152  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_s16:
10153  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_s32:
10154  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_f16_s64: {
10155  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)));
10156  llvm::Type *FTy = HalfTy;
10157  llvm::Type *InTy;
10158  if (Ops[0]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 64)
10159  InTy = Int64Ty;
10160  else if (Ops[0]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 32)
10161  InTy = Int32Ty;
10162  else
10163  InTy = Int16Ty;
10164  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], InTy);
10165  if (usgn)
10166  return Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[0], FTy);
10167  return Builder.CreateSIToFP(Ops[0], FTy);
10168  }
10169  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtah_u16_f16:
10170  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmh_u16_f16:
10171  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnh_u16_f16:
10172  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtph_u16_f16:
10173  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_u16_f16:
10174  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtah_s16_f16:
10175  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtmh_s16_f16:
10176  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtnh_s16_f16:
10177  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtph_s16_f16:
10178  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvth_s16_f16: {
10179  unsigned Int;
10180  llvm::Type* InTy = Int32Ty;
10181  llvm::Type* FTy = HalfTy;
10182  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = {InTy, FTy};
10183  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)));
10184  switch (BuiltinID) {
10185  default: llvm_unreachable("missing builtin ID in switch!");
10186  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vcvtah_u16_f16:

10776  llvm::Type *Ty = VTy;
10777  if (!Ty)
10778  return nullptr;

10781  // defer to common code if it's been added to our special map.
10782  Builtin = findARMVectorIntrinsicInMap(AArch64SIMDIntrinsicMap, BuiltinID,
10783  AArch64SIMDIntrinsicsProvenSorted);
10784 
10785  if (Builtin)
10786  return EmitCommonNeonBuiltinExpr(
10787  Builtin->BuiltinID, Builtin->LLVMIntrinsic, Builtin->AltLLVMIntrinsic,
10788  Builtin->NameHint, Builtin->TypeModifier, E, Ops,
10789  /*never use addresses*/ Address::invalid(), Address::invalid(), Arch);
10790 
10791  if (Value *V = EmitAArch64TblBuiltinExpr(*this, BuiltinID, E, Ops, Arch))
10792  return V;
10793 
10794  unsigned Int;
10795  switch (BuiltinID) {
10796  default: return nullptr;
10797  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vbsl_v:
10798  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vbslq_v: {
10799  llvm::Type *BitTy = llvm::VectorType::getInteger(VTy);
10800  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], BitTy, "vbsl");
10801  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], BitTy, "vbsl");
10802  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], BitTy, "vbsl");
10803 
10804  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateAnd(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vbsl");
10805  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateAnd(Builder.CreateNot(Ops[0]), Ops[2], "vbsl");
10806  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateOr(Ops[1], Ops[2], "vbsl");
10807  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
10808  }
10809  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfma_lane_v:
10810  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfmaq_lane_v: { // Only used for FP types
10811  // The ARM builtins (and instructions) have the addend as the first
10812  // operand, but the 'fma' intrinsics have it last. Swap it around here.
10813  Value *Addend = Ops[0];
10814  Value *Multiplicand = Ops[1];
10815  Value *LaneSource = Ops[2];
10816  Ops[0] = Multiplicand;
10817  Ops[1] = LaneSource;
10818  Ops[2] = Addend;
10819 
10820  // Now adjust things to handle the lane access.
10821  auto *SourceTy = BuiltinID == NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfmaq_lane_v
10822  ? llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(),
10823  VTy->getNumElements() / 2)
10824  : VTy;

10826  Value *SV = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(VTy->getElementCount(), cst);
10827  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], SourceTy);
10828  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[1], SV, "lane");
10829 
10830  Ops.pop_back();
10831  Int = Builder.getIsFPConstrained() ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma
10832  : Intrinsic::fma;
10833  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "fmla");
10834  }
10835  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vfma_laneq_v: {
10836  auto *VTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ty);
10837  // v1f64 fma should be mapped to Neon scalar f64 fma
10838  if (VTy && VTy->getElementType() == DoubleTy) {
10839  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], DoubleTy);
10840  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], DoubleTy);
10841  llvm::FixedVectorType *VTy =
10842  GetNeonType(this, NeonTypeFlags(NeonTypeFlags::Float64, false, true));
10843  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], VTy);

10848  DoubleTy, {Ops[1], Ops[2], Ops[0]});

10860

11664  return Builder.CreateInsertElement(Ops[1], Ops[0], Ops[2], "vld1_lane");
11665  }
11666  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1_dup_v:
11667  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld1q_dup_v: {
11668  Value *V = UndefValue::get(Ty);
11669  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
11670  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
11671  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VTy->getElementType(), Ops[0],
11672  PtrOp0.getAlignment());
11673  llvm::Constant *CI = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0);
11674  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Ops[0], CI);
11675  return EmitNeonSplat(Ops[0], CI);
11676  }
11677  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1_lane_v:
11678  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst1q_lane_v:
11679  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11680  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[1], Ops[2]);
11681  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
11682  return Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Ops[1], Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty),
11683  PtrOp0.getAlignment());
11684  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_v:
11685  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_v: {
11686  llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy);
11687  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
11688  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
11689  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld2, Tys);
11690  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[1], "vld2");
11691  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
11692  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType()));
11693  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
11694  }
11695  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3_v:
11696  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld3q_v: {
11697  llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy);
11698  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
11699  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
11700  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld3, Tys);
11701  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[1], "vld3");
11702  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
11703  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType()));
11704  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
11705  }
11706  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4_v:
11707  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld4q_v: {
11708  llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy);
11709  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
11710  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
11711  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld4, Tys);
11712  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[1], "vld4");
11713  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
11714  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType()));
11715  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
11716  }
11717  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_dup_v:
11718  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_dup_v: {
11719  llvm::Type *PTy =
11720  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
11721  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
11722  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
11723  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld2r, Tys);
11724  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[1], "vld2");

11743  llvm::Type *PTy =
11744  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(VTy->getElementType());
11745  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], PTy);
11746  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, PTy };
11747  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld4r, Tys);

11751  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
11752  }
11753  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2_lane_v:
11754  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vld2q_lane_v: {
11755  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, Ops[1]->getType() };
11756  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld2lane, Tys);
11757  std::rotate(Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.begin() + 2, Ops.end());
11758  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11759  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
11760  Ops[3] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[3], Int64Ty);
11761  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1), "vld2_lane");
11762  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
11763  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);

11770  std::rotate(Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.begin() + 2, Ops.end());
11771  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11772  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
11773  Ops[3] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[3], Ty);
11774  Ops[4] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[4], Int64Ty);
11775  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateCall(F, makeArrayRef(Ops).slice(1), "vld3_lane");

11784  std::rotate(Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.begin() + 2, Ops.end());

11791  Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType());
11792  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
11793  return Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Ops[1], Ops[0]);
11794  }
11795  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst2_v:

11814  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_st3, Tys),
11815  Ops, "");
11816  }
11817  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3_lane_v:
11818  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst3q_lane_v: {

11820  Ops[3] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[3], Int64Ty);
11821  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, Ops[4]->getType() };
11822  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_st3lane, Tys),
11823  Ops, "");
11824  }
11825  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4_v:
11826  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4q_v: {
11827  std::rotate(Ops.begin(), Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.end());
11828  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, Ops[4]->getType() };
11829  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_st4, Tys),
11830  Ops, "");
11831  }
11832  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4_lane_v:
11833  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vst4q_lane_v: {
11834  std::rotate(Ops.begin(), Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.end());
11835  Ops[4] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[4], Int64Ty);
11836  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { VTy, Ops[5]->getType() };
11837  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_st4lane, Tys),
11838  Ops, "");
11839  }
11840  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtrn_v:
11841  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vtrnq_v: {
11842  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
11843  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11844  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
11845  Value *SV = nullptr;
11846 
11847  for (unsigned vi = 0; vi != 2; ++vi) {
11848  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
11849  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; i += 2) {
11850  Indices.push_back(i+vi);
11851  Indices.push_back(i+e+vi);
11852  }
11853  Value *Addr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(Ty, Ops[0], vi);
11854  SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[2], Indices, "vtrn");
11855  SV = Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(SV, Addr);
11856  }
11857  return SV;
11858  }
11859  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vuzp_v:
11860  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vuzpq_v: {
11861  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
11862  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11863  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
11864  Value *SV = nullptr;
11865 
11866  for (unsigned vi = 0; vi != 2; ++vi) {
11867  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
11868  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
11869  Indices.push_back(2*i+vi);
11870 
11871  Value *Addr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(Ty, Ops[0], vi);
11872  SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[2], Indices, "vuzp");
11873  SV = Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(SV, Addr);
11874  }
11875  return SV;
11876  }
11877  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vzip_v:
11878  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vzipq_v: {
11879  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
11880  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
11881  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Ty);
11882  Value *SV = nullptr;
11883 
11884  for (unsigned vi = 0; vi != 2; ++vi) {
11885  SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
11886  for (unsigned i = 0, e = VTy->getNumElements(); i != e; i += 2) {
11887  Indices.push_back((i + vi*e) >> 1);
11888  Indices.push_back(((i + vi*e) >> 1)+e);
11889  }
11890  Value *Addr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(Ty, Ops[0], vi);
11891  SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[2], Indices, "vzip");
11892  SV = Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(SV, Addr);
11893  }
11894  return SV;
11895  }
11896  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl1q_v: {
11897  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl1, Ty),
11898  Ops, "vtbl1");
11899  }
11900  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl2q_v: {
11901  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl2, Ty),
11902  Ops, "vtbl2");
11903  }
11904  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl3q_v: {
11905  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl3, Ty),
11906  Ops, "vtbl3");
11907  }
11908  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbl4q_v: {
11909  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbl4, Ty),
11910  Ops, "vtbl4");
11911  }
11912  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx1q_v: {
11913  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx1, Ty),
11914  Ops, "vtbx1");
11915  }
11916  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx2q_v: {
11917  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx2, Ty),
11918  Ops, "vtbx2");
11919  }
11920  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx3q_v: {
11921  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx3, Ty),
11922  Ops, "vtbx3");
11923  }
11924  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vqtbx4q_v: {
11925  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_tbx4, Ty),
11926  Ops, "vtbx4");
11927  }
11928  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsqadd_v:
11929  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vsqaddq_v: {
11930  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_usqadd;
11931  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "vsqadd");
11932  }
11933  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vuqadd_v:
11934  case NEON::BI__builtin_neon_vuqaddq_v: {
11935  Int = Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_suqadd;
11936  return EmitNeonCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Int, Ty), Ops, "vuqadd");
11937  }
11938  }
