11940 
11941 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitBPFBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
11942  const CallExpr *E) {
11943  assert((BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_field_info ||
11944  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id ||
11945  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_type_info ||
11946  BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_enum_value) &&
11947  "unexpected BPF builtin");
11948 
11949  // A sequence number, injected into IR builtin functions, to
11950  // prevent CSE given the only difference of the funciton
11951  // may just be the debuginfo metadata.
11952  static uint32_t BuiltinSeqNum;
11953 
11954  switch (BuiltinID) {
11955  default:
11956  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected BPF builtin");
11957  case BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_field_info: {
11958  const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(0);
11959  bool IsBitField = Arg->IgnoreParens()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField;
11960 
11961  if (!getDebugInfo()) {
11962  CGM.Error(E->getExprLoc(),
11963  "using __builtin_preserve_field_info() without -g");
11964  return IsBitField ? EmitLValue(Arg).getBitFieldPointer()
11965  : EmitLValue(Arg).getPointer(*this);
11966  }
11967 
11968  // Enable underlying preserve_*_access_index() generation.
11969  bool OldIsInPreservedAIRegion = IsInPreservedAIRegion;
11970  IsInPreservedAIRegion = true;
11971  Value *FieldAddr = IsBitField ? EmitLValue(Arg).getBitFieldPointer()
11972  : EmitLValue(Arg).getPointer(*this);
11973  IsInPreservedAIRegion = OldIsInPreservedAIRegion;
11974 
11975  ConstantInt *C = cast<ConstantInt>(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)));
11976  Value *InfoKind = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, C->getSExtValue());
11977 
11978  // Built the IR for the preserve_field_info intrinsic.
11979  llvm::Function *FnGetFieldInfo = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
11980  &CGM.getModule(), llvm::Intrinsic::bpf_preserve_field_info,
11981  {FieldAddr->getType()});
11982  return Builder.CreateCall(FnGetFieldInfo, {FieldAddr, InfoKind});
11983  }
11984  case BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id:
11985  case BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_type_info: {
11986  if (!getDebugInfo()) {
11987  CGM.Error(E->getExprLoc(), "using builtin function without -g");
11988  return nullptr;
11989  }
11990 
11991  const Expr *Arg0 = E->getArg(0);
11992  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(
11993  Arg0->getType(), Arg0->getExprLoc());
11994 
11995  ConstantInt *Flag = cast<ConstantInt>(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)));
11996  Value *FlagValue = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, Flag->getSExtValue());
11997  Value *SeqNumVal = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, BuiltinSeqNum++);
11998 
11999  llvm::Function *FnDecl;
12000  if (BuiltinID == BPF::BI__builtin_btf_type_id)
12001  FnDecl = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
12002  &CGM.getModule(), llvm::Intrinsic::bpf_btf_type_id, {});
12003  else
12004  FnDecl = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
12005  &CGM.getModule(), llvm::Intrinsic::bpf_preserve_type_info, {});
12006  CallInst *Fn = Builder.CreateCall(FnDecl, {SeqNumVal, FlagValue});
12007  Fn->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_preserve_access_index, DbgInfo);
12008  return Fn;
12009  }
12010  case BPF::BI__builtin_preserve_enum_value: {
12011  if (!getDebugInfo()) {
12012  CGM.Error(E->getExprLoc(), "using builtin function without -g");
12013  return nullptr;
12014  }
12015 
12016  const Expr *Arg0 = E->getArg(0);
12017  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(
12018  Arg0->getType(), Arg0->getExprLoc());
12019 
12020  // Find enumerator
12021  const auto *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(Arg0->IgnoreParens());
12022  const auto *CE = cast<CStyleCastExpr>(UO->getSubExpr());
12023  const auto *DR = cast<DeclRefExpr>(CE->getSubExpr());
12024  const auto *Enumerator = cast<EnumConstantDecl>(DR->getDecl());
12025 
12026  auto &InitVal = Enumerator->getInitVal();
12027  std::string InitValStr;
12028  if (InitVal.isNegative() || InitVal > uint64_t(INT64_MAX))
12029  InitValStr = std::to_string(InitVal.getSExtValue());
12030  else
12031  InitValStr = std::to_string(InitVal.getZExtValue());
12032  std::string EnumStr = Enumerator->getNameAsString() + ":" + InitValStr;
12033  Value *EnumStrVal = Builder.CreateGlobalStringPtr(EnumStr);
12034 
12035  ConstantInt *Flag = cast<ConstantInt>(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)));
12036  Value *FlagValue = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, Flag->getSExtValue());
12037  Value *SeqNumVal = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, BuiltinSeqNum++);
12038 
12039  llvm::Function *IntrinsicFn = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
12040  &CGM.getModule(), llvm::Intrinsic::bpf_preserve_enum_value, {});
12041  CallInst *Fn =
12042  Builder.CreateCall(IntrinsicFn, {SeqNumVal, EnumStrVal, FlagValue});
12043  Fn->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_preserve_access_index, DbgInfo);
12044  return Fn;
12045  }
12046  }
12047 }
12048 
12049 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::
12050 BuildVector(ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> Ops) {
12051  assert((Ops.size() & (Ops.size() - 1)) == 0 &&
12052  "Not a power-of-two sized vector!");
12053  bool AllConstants = true;
12054  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e && AllConstants; ++i)
12055  AllConstants &= isa<Constant>(Ops[i]);
12056 
12057  // If this is a constant vector, create a ConstantVector.
12058  if (AllConstants) {
12059  SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 16> CstOps;
12060  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i)
12061  CstOps.push_back(cast<Constant>(Ops[i]));
12062  return llvm::ConstantVector::get(CstOps);
12063  }
12064 
12065  // Otherwise, insertelement the values to build the vector.
12066  Value *Result = llvm::UndefValue::get(
12067  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Ops[0]->getType(), Ops.size()));
12068 
12069  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i)
12070  Result = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Result, Ops[i], Builder.getInt32(i));
12071 
12072  return Result;
12073 }
12074 
12075 // Convert the mask from an integer type to a vector of i1.
12076 static Value *getMaskVecValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Value *Mask,
12077  unsigned NumElts) {
12078 
12079  auto *MaskTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
12080  CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(),
12081  cast<IntegerType>(Mask->getType())->getBitWidth());
12082  Value *MaskVec = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy);
12083 
12084  // If we have less than 8 elements, then the starting mask was an i8 and
12085  // we need to extract down to the right number of elements.
12086  if (NumElts < 8) {
12087  int Indices[4];
12088  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
12089  Indices[i] = i;
12090  MaskVec = CGF.Builder.CreateShuffleVector(MaskVec, MaskVec,
12091  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
12092  "extract");
12093  }
12094  return MaskVec;
12095 }
12096 
12097 static Value *EmitX86MaskedStore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12098  Align Alignment) {
12099  // Cast the pointer to right type.
12100  Value *Ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
12101  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ops[1]->getType()));
12102 
12103  Value *MaskVec = getMaskVecValue(
12104  CGF, Ops[2],
12105  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[1]->getType())->getNumElements());
12106 
12107  return CGF.Builder.CreateMaskedStore(Ops[1], Ptr, Alignment, MaskVec);
12108 }
12109 
12110 static Value *EmitX86MaskedLoad(CodeGenFunction &CGF, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12111  Align Alignment) {
12112  // Cast the pointer to right type.
12113  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[1]->getType();
12114  Value *Ptr =
12115  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty));
12116 
12117  Value *MaskVec = getMaskVecValue(
12118  CGF, Ops[2], cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ty)->getNumElements());
12119 
12120  return CGF.Builder.CreateMaskedLoad(Ty, Ptr, Alignment, MaskVec, Ops[1]);
12121 }
12122 
12123 static Value *EmitX86ExpandLoad(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12124  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12125  auto *ResultTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ops[1]->getType());
12126  llvm::Type *PtrTy = ResultTy->getElementType();
12127 
12128  // Cast the pointer to element type.
12129  Value *Ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
12130  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(PtrTy));
12131 
12132  Value *MaskVec = getMaskVecValue(
12133  CGF, Ops[2], cast<FixedVectorType>(ResultTy)->getNumElements());
12134 
12135  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::masked_expandload,
12136  ResultTy);
12137  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, { Ptr, MaskVec, Ops[1] });
12138 }
12139 
12140 static Value *EmitX86CompressExpand(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12141  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12142  bool IsCompress) {
12143  auto *ResultTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[1]->getType());
12144 
12145  Value *MaskVec = getMaskVecValue(CGF, Ops[2], ResultTy->getNumElements());
12146 
12147  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsCompress ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_compress
12148  : Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_expand;
12149  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, ResultTy);
12150  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, { Ops[0], Ops[1], MaskVec });
12151 }
12152 
12153 static Value *EmitX86CompressStore(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12154  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12155  auto *ResultTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[1]->getType());
12156  llvm::Type *PtrTy = ResultTy->getElementType();
12157 
12158  // Cast the pointer to element type.
12159  Value *Ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0],
12160  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(PtrTy));
12161 
12162  Value *MaskVec = getMaskVecValue(CGF, Ops[2], ResultTy->getNumElements());
12163 
12164  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::masked_compressstore,
12165  ResultTy);
12166  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, { Ops[1], Ptr, MaskVec });
12167 }
12168 
12169 static Value *EmitX86MaskLogic(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Instruction::BinaryOps Opc,
12170  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12171  bool InvertLHS = false) {
12172  unsigned NumElts = Ops[0]->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth();
12173  Value *LHS = getMaskVecValue(CGF, Ops[0], NumElts);
12174  Value *RHS = getMaskVecValue(CGF, Ops[1], NumElts);
12175 
12176  if (InvertLHS)
12177  LHS = CGF.Builder.CreateNot(LHS);
12178 
12179  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(CGF.Builder.CreateBinOp(Opc, LHS, RHS),
12180  Ops[0]->getType());
12181 }
12182 
12183 static Value *EmitX86FunnelShift(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Value *Op0, Value *Op1,
12184  Value *Amt, bool IsRight) {
12185  llvm::Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
12186 
12187  // Amount may be scalar immediate, in which case create a splat vector.
12188  // Funnel shifts amounts are treated as modulo and types are all power-of-2 so
12189  // we only care about the lowest log2 bits anyway.
12190  if (Amt->getType() != Ty) {
12191  unsigned NumElts = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ty)->getNumElements();
12192  Amt = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Amt, Ty->getScalarType(), false);
12193  Amt = CGF.Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Amt);
12194  }
12195 
12196  unsigned IID = IsRight ? Intrinsic::fshr : Intrinsic::fshl;
12197  Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, Ty);
12198  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, {Op0, Op1, Amt});
12199 }
12200 
12201 static Value *EmitX86vpcom(CodeGenFunction &CGF, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12202  bool IsSigned) {
12203  Value *Op0 = Ops[0];
12204  Value *Op1 = Ops[1];
12205  llvm::Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
12206  uint64_t Imm = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue() & 0x7;
12207 
12208  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
12209  switch (Imm) {
12210  case 0x0:
12211  Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
12212  break;
12213  case 0x1:
12214  Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE;
12215  break;
12216  case 0x2:
12217  Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
12218  break;
12219  case 0x3:
12220  Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE;
12221  break;
12222  case 0x4:
12223  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
12224  break;
12225  case 0x5:
12226  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
12227  break;
12228  case 0x6:
12229  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Ty); // FALSE
12230  case 0x7:
12231  return llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty); // TRUE
12232  default:
12233  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected XOP vpcom/vpcomu predicate");
12234  }
12235 
12236  Value *Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Op0, Op1);
12237  Value *Res = CGF.Builder.CreateSExt(Cmp, Ty);
12238  return Res;
12239 }
12240 
12241 static Value *EmitX86Select(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12242  Value *Mask, Value *Op0, Value *Op1) {
12243 
12244  // If the mask is all ones just return first argument.
12245  if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
12246  if (C->isAllOnesValue())
12247  return Op0;
12248 
12249  Mask = getMaskVecValue(
12250  CGF, Mask, cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Op0->getType())->getNumElements());
12251 
12252  return CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1);
12253 }
12254 
12255 static Value *EmitX86ScalarSelect(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12256  Value *Mask, Value *Op0, Value *Op1) {
12257  // If the mask is all ones just return first argument.
12258  if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
12259  if (C->isAllOnesValue())
12260  return Op0;
12261 
12262  auto *MaskTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
12263  CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(), Mask->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth());
12264  Mask = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy);
12265  Mask = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Mask, (uint64_t)0);
12266  return CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1);
12267 }
12268 
12269 static Value *EmitX86MaskedCompareResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Value *Cmp,
12270  unsigned NumElts, Value *MaskIn) {
12271  if (MaskIn) {
12272  const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(MaskIn);
12273  if (!C || !C->isAllOnesValue())
12274  Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(Cmp, getMaskVecValue(CGF, MaskIn, NumElts));
12275  }
12276 
12277  if (NumElts < 8) {
12278  int Indices[8];
12279  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
12280  Indices[i] = i;
12281  for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != 8; ++i)
12282  Indices[i] = i % NumElts + NumElts;
12283  Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
12284  Cmp, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Cmp->getType()), Indices);
12285  }
12286 
12287  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Cmp,
12288  IntegerType::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(),
12289  std::max(NumElts, 8U)));
12290 }
12291 
12292 static Value *EmitX86MaskedCompare(CodeGenFunction &CGF, unsigned CC,
12293  bool Signed, ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12294  assert((Ops.size() == 2 || Ops.size() == 4) &&
12295  "Unexpected number of arguments");
12296  unsigned NumElts =
12297  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
12298  Value *Cmp;
12299 
12300  if (CC == 3) {
12301  Cmp = Constant::getNullValue(
12302  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts));
12303  } else if (CC == 7) {
12304  Cmp = Constant::getAllOnesValue(
12305  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts));
12306  } else {
12307  ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
12308  switch (CC) {
12309  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown condition code");
12310  case 0: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ; break;
12311  case 1: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT; break;
12312  case 2: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE; break;
12313  case 4: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE; break;
12314  case 5: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE; break;
12315  case 6: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT; break;
12316  }
12317  Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
12318  }
12319 
12320  Value *MaskIn = nullptr;
12321  if (Ops.size() == 4)
12322  MaskIn = Ops[3];
12323 
12324  return EmitX86MaskedCompareResult(CGF, Cmp, NumElts, MaskIn);
12325 }
12326 
12327 static Value *EmitX86ConvertToMask(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Value *In) {
12328  Value *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(In->getType());
12329  return EmitX86MaskedCompare(CGF, 1, true, { In, Zero });
12330 }
12331 
12332 static Value *EmitX86ConvertIntToFp(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CallExpr *E,
12333  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops, bool IsSigned) {
12334  unsigned Rnd = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[3])->getZExtValue();
12335  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[1]->getType();
12336 
12337  Value *Res;
12338  if (Rnd != 4) {
12339  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsSigned ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512_sitofp_round
12340  : Intrinsic::x86_avx512_uitofp_round;
12341  Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, { Ty, Ops[0]->getType() });
12342  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, { Ops[0], Ops[3] });
12343  } else {
12344  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, E);
12345  Res = IsSigned ? CGF.Builder.CreateSIToFP(Ops[0], Ty)
12346  : CGF.Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[0], Ty);
12347  }
12348 
12349  return EmitX86Select(CGF, Ops[2], Res, Ops[1]);
12350 }
12351 
12352 // Lowers X86 FMA intrinsics to IR.
12353 static Value *EmitX86FMAExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CallExpr *E,
12354  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops, unsigned BuiltinID,
12355  bool IsAddSub) {
12356 
12357  bool Subtract = false;
12358  Intrinsic::ID IID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
12359  switch (BuiltinID) {
12360  default: break;
12361  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubph512_mask3:
12362  Subtract = true;
12363  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12364  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_mask:
12365  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_maskz:
12366  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_mask3:
12367  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_vfmadd_ph_512;
12368  break;
12369  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddph512_mask3:
12370  Subtract = true;
12371  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12372  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_mask:
12373  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_maskz:
12374  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_mask3:
12375  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_vfmaddsub_ph_512;
12376  break;
12377  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubps512_mask3:
12378  Subtract = true;
12379  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12380  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_mask:
12381  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_maskz:
12382  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_mask3:
12383  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmadd_ps_512; break;
12384  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubpd512_mask3:
12385  Subtract = true;
12386  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12387  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_mask:
12388  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_maskz:
12389  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_mask3:
12390  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmadd_pd_512; break;
12391  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddps512_mask3:
12392  Subtract = true;
12393  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12394  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_mask:
12395  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_maskz:
12396  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_mask3:
12397  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmaddsub_ps_512;
12398  break;
12399  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddpd512_mask3:
12400  Subtract = true;
12401  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12402  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_mask:
12403  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_maskz:
12404  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_mask3:
12405  IID = llvm::Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmaddsub_pd_512;
12406  break;
12407  }
12408 
12409  Value *A = Ops[0];
12410  Value *B = Ops[1];
12411  Value *C = Ops[2];
12412 
12413  if (Subtract)
12414  C = CGF.Builder.CreateFNeg(C);
12415 
12416  Value *Res;
12417 
12418  // Only handle in case of _MM_FROUND_CUR_DIRECTION/4 (no rounding).
12419  if (IID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic &&
12420  (cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops.back())->getZExtValue() != (uint64_t)4 ||
12421  IsAddSub)) {
12422  Function *Intr = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID);
12423  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(Intr, {A, B, C, Ops.back() });
12424  } else {
12425  llvm::Type *Ty = A->getType();
12426  Function *FMA;
12427  if (CGF.Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
12428  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, E);
12429  FMA = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, Ty);
12430  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(FMA, {A, B, C});
12431  } else {
12432  FMA = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, Ty);
12433  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(FMA, {A, B, C});
12434  }
12435  }
12436 
12437  // Handle any required masking.
12438  Value *MaskFalseVal = nullptr;
12439  switch (BuiltinID) {
12440  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_mask:
12441  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_mask:
12442  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_mask:
12443  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_mask:
12444  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_mask:
12445  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_mask:
12446  MaskFalseVal = Ops[0];
12447  break;
12448  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_maskz:
12449  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_maskz:
12450  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_maskz:
12451  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_maskz:
12452  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_maskz:
12453  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_maskz:
12454  MaskFalseVal = Constant::getNullValue(Ops[0]->getType());
12455  break;
12456  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubph512_mask3:
12457  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddph512_mask3:
12458  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubps512_mask3:
12459  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddps512_mask3:
12460  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubpd512_mask3:
12461  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddpd512_mask3:
12462  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddph512_mask3:
12463  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubph512_mask3:
12464  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddps512_mask3:
12465  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubps512_mask3:
12466  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmsubaddpd512_mask3:
12467  case clang::X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddsubpd512_mask3:
12468  MaskFalseVal = Ops[2];
12469  break;
12470  }
12471 
12472  if (MaskFalseVal)
12473  return EmitX86Select(CGF, Ops[3], Res, MaskFalseVal);
12474 
12475  return Res;
12476 }
12477 
12478 static Value *EmitScalarFMAExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CallExpr *E,
12479  MutableArrayRef<Value *> Ops, Value *Upper,
12480  bool ZeroMask = false, unsigned PTIdx = 0,
12481  bool NegAcc = false) {
12482  unsigned Rnd = 4;
12483  if (Ops.size() > 4)
12484  Rnd = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[4])->getZExtValue();
12485 
12486  if (NegAcc)
12487  Ops[2] = CGF.Builder.CreateFNeg(Ops[2]);
12488 
12489  Ops[0] = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[0], (uint64_t)0);
12490  Ops[1] = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[1], (uint64_t)0);
12491  Ops[2] = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[2], (uint64_t)0);
12492  Value *Res;
12493  if (Rnd != 4) {
12494  Intrinsic::ID IID;
12495 
12496  switch (Ops[0]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits()) {
12497  case 16:
12498  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_vfmadd_f16;
12499  break;
12500  case 32:
12501  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmadd_f32;
12502  break;
12503  case 64:
12504  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vfmadd_f64;
12505  break;
12506  default:
12507  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size");
12508  }
12509  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID),
12510  {Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2], Ops[4]});
12511  } else if (CGF.Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
12512  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, E);
12513  Function *FMA = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(
12514  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, Ops[0]->getType());
12515  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(FMA, Ops.slice(0, 3));
12516  } else {
12517  Function *FMA = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, Ops[0]->getType());
12518  Res = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(FMA, Ops.slice(0, 3));
12519  }
12520  // If we have more than 3 arguments, we need to do masking.
12521  if (Ops.size() > 3) {
12522  Value *PassThru = ZeroMask ? Constant::getNullValue(Res->getType())
12523  : Ops[PTIdx];
12524 
12525  // If we negated the accumulator and the its the PassThru value we need to
12526  // bypass the negate. Conveniently Upper should be the same thing in this
12527  // case.
12528  if (NegAcc && PTIdx == 2)
12529  PassThru = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractElement(Upper, (uint64_t)0);
12530 
12531  Res = EmitX86ScalarSelect(CGF, Ops[3], Res, PassThru);
12532  }
12533  return CGF.Builder.CreateInsertElement(Upper, Res, (uint64_t)0);
12534 }
12535 
12536 static Value *EmitX86Muldq(CodeGenFunction &CGF, bool IsSigned,
12537  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12538  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[0]->getType();
12539  // Arguments have a vXi32 type so cast to vXi64.
12540  Ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(CGF.Int64Ty,
12541  Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() / 64);
12542  Value *LHS = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ty);
12543  Value *RHS = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Ty);
12544 
12545  if (IsSigned) {
12546  // Shift left then arithmetic shift right.
12547  Constant *ShiftAmt = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 32);
12548  LHS = CGF.Builder.CreateShl(LHS, ShiftAmt);
12549  LHS = CGF.Builder.CreateAShr(LHS, ShiftAmt);
12550  RHS = CGF.Builder.CreateShl(RHS, ShiftAmt);
12551  RHS = CGF.Builder.CreateAShr(RHS, ShiftAmt);
12552  } else {
12553  // Clear the upper bits.
12554  Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0xffffffff);
12555  LHS = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, Mask);
12556  RHS = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, Mask);
12557  }
12558 
12559  return CGF.Builder.CreateMul(LHS, RHS);
12560 }
12561 
12562 // Emit a masked pternlog intrinsic. This only exists because the header has to
12563 // use a macro and we aren't able to pass the input argument to a pternlog
12564 // builtin and a select builtin without evaluating it twice.
12565 static Value *EmitX86Ternlog(CodeGenFunction &CGF, bool ZeroMask,
12566  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12567  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[0]->getType();
12568 
12569  unsigned VecWidth = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
12570  unsigned EltWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
12571  Intrinsic::ID IID;
12572  if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32)
12573  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_d_128;
12574  else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32)
12575  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_d_256;
12576  else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 32)
12577  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_d_512;
12578  else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64)
12579  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_q_128;
12580  else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64)
12581  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_q_256;
12582  else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 64)
12583  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pternlog_q_512;
12584  else
12585  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic");
12586 
12587  Value *Ternlog = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID),
12588  Ops.drop_back());
12589  Value *PassThru = ZeroMask ? ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty) : Ops[0];
12590  return EmitX86Select(CGF, Ops[4], Ternlog, PassThru);
12591 }
12592 
12593 static Value *EmitX86SExtMask(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Value *Op,
12594  llvm::Type *DstTy) {
12595  unsigned NumberOfElements =
12596  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)->getNumElements();
12597  Value *Mask = getMaskVecValue(CGF, Op, NumberOfElements);
12598  return CGF.Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, DstTy, "vpmovm2");
12599 }
12600 
12601 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuIs(const CallExpr *E) {
12602  const Expr *CPUExpr = E->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
12603  StringRef CPUStr = cast<clang::StringLiteral>(CPUExpr)->getString();
12604  return EmitX86CpuIs(CPUStr);
12605 }
12606 
12607 // Convert F16 halfs to floats.
12608 static Value *EmitX86CvtF16ToFloatExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12609  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops,
12610  llvm::Type *DstTy) {
12611  assert((Ops.size() == 1 || Ops.size() == 3 || Ops.size() == 4) &&
12612  "Unknown cvtph2ps intrinsic");
12613 
12614  // If the SAE intrinsic doesn't use default rounding then we can't upgrade.
12615  if (Ops.size() == 4 && cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[3])->getZExtValue() != 4) {
12616  Function *F =
12617  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_vcvtph2ps_512);
12618  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2], Ops[3]});
12619  }
12620 
12621  unsigned NumDstElts = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)->getNumElements();
12622  Value *Src = Ops[0];
12623 
12624  // Extract the subvector.
12625  if (NumDstElts !=
12626  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Src->getType())->getNumElements()) {
12627  assert(NumDstElts == 4 && "Unexpected vector size");
12628  Src = CGF.Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Src, ArrayRef<int>{0, 1, 2, 3});
12629  }
12630 
12631  // Bitcast from vXi16 to vXf16.
12632  auto *HalfTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
12633  llvm::Type::getHalfTy(CGF.getLLVMContext()), NumDstElts);
12634  Src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, HalfTy);
12635 
12636  // Perform the fp-extension.
12637  Value *Res = CGF.Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, DstTy, "cvtph2ps");
12638 
12639  if (Ops.size() >= 3)
12640  Res = EmitX86Select(CGF, Ops[2], Res, Ops[1]);
12641  return Res;
12642 }
12643 
12644 // Convert a BF16 to a float.
12645 static Value *EmitX86CvtBF16ToFloatExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
12646  const CallExpr *E,
12647  ArrayRef<Value *> Ops) {
12648  llvm::Type *Int32Ty = CGF.Builder.getInt32Ty();
12649  Value *ZeroExt = CGF.Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[0], Int32Ty);
12650  Value *Shl = CGF.Builder.CreateShl(ZeroExt, 16);
12651  llvm::Type *ResultType = CGF.ConvertType(E->getType());
12652  Value *BitCast = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Shl, ResultType);
12653  return BitCast;
12654 }
12655 
12656 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuIs(StringRef CPUStr) {
12657 
12658  llvm::Type *Int32Ty = Builder.getInt32Ty();
12659 
12660  // Matching the struct layout from the compiler-rt/libgcc structure that is
12661  // filled in:
12662  // unsigned int __cpu_vendor;
12663  // unsigned int __cpu_type;
12664  // unsigned int __cpu_subtype;
12665  // unsigned int __cpu_features[1];
12666  llvm::Type *STy = llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty,
12667  llvm::ArrayType::get(Int32Ty, 1));
12668 
12669  // Grab the global __cpu_model.
12670  llvm::Constant *CpuModel = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(STy, "__cpu_model");
12671  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CpuModel)->setDSOLocal(true);
12672 
12673  // Calculate the index needed to access the correct field based on the
12674  // range. Also adjust the expected value.
12675  unsigned Index;
12676  unsigned Value;
12677  std::tie(Index, Value) = StringSwitch<std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>>(CPUStr)
12678 #define X86_VENDOR(ENUM, STRING) \
12679  .Case(STRING, {0u, static_cast<unsigned>(llvm::X86::ENUM)})
12680 #define X86_CPU_TYPE_ALIAS(ENUM, ALIAS) \
12681  .Case(ALIAS, {1u, static_cast<unsigned>(llvm::X86::ENUM)})
12682 #define X86_CPU_TYPE(ENUM, STR) \
12683  .Case(STR, {1u, static_cast<unsigned>(llvm::X86::ENUM)})
12684 #define X86_CPU_SUBTYPE(ENUM, STR) \
12685  .Case(STR, {2u, static_cast<unsigned>(llvm::X86::ENUM)})
12686 #include "llvm/Support/X86TargetParser.def"
12687  .Default({0, 0});
12688  assert(Value != 0 && "Invalid CPUStr passed to CpuIs");
12689 
12690  // Grab the appropriate field from __cpu_model.
12691  llvm::Value *Idxs[] = {ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0),
12692  ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Index)};
12693  llvm::Value *CpuValue = Builder.CreateGEP(STy, CpuModel, Idxs);
12694  CpuValue = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Int32Ty, CpuValue,
12695  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
12696 
12697  // Check the value of the field against the requested value.
12698  return Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CpuValue,
12699  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Value));
12700 }
12701 
12702 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuSupports(const CallExpr *E) {
12703  const Expr *FeatureExpr = E->getArg(0)->IgnoreParenCasts();
12704  StringRef FeatureStr = cast<StringLiteral>(FeatureExpr)->getString();
12705  return EmitX86CpuSupports(FeatureStr);
12706 }
12707 
12708 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuSupports(ArrayRef<StringRef> FeatureStrs) {
12709  return EmitX86CpuSupports(llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(FeatureStrs));
12710 }
12711 
12712 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuSupports(uint64_t FeaturesMask) {
12713  uint32_t Features1 = Lo_32(FeaturesMask);
12714  uint32_t Features2 = Hi_32(FeaturesMask);
12715 
12716  Value *Result = Builder.getTrue();
12717 
12718  if (Features1 != 0) {
12719  // Matching the struct layout from the compiler-rt/libgcc structure that is
12720  // filled in:
12721  // unsigned int __cpu_vendor;
12722  // unsigned int __cpu_type;
12723  // unsigned int __cpu_subtype;
12724  // unsigned int __cpu_features[1];
12725  llvm::Type *STy = llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty,
12726  llvm::ArrayType::get(Int32Ty, 1));
12727 
12728  // Grab the global __cpu_model.
12729  llvm::Constant *CpuModel = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(STy, "__cpu_model");
12730  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CpuModel)->setDSOLocal(true);
12731 
12732  // Grab the first (0th) element from the field __cpu_features off of the
12733  // global in the struct STy.
12734  Value *Idxs[] = {Builder.getInt32(0), Builder.getInt32(3),
12735  Builder.getInt32(0)};
12736  Value *CpuFeatures = Builder.CreateGEP(STy, CpuModel, Idxs);
12737  Value *Features = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Int32Ty, CpuFeatures,
12738  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
12739 
12740  // Check the value of the bit corresponding to the feature requested.
12741  Value *Mask = Builder.getInt32(Features1);
12742  Value *Bitset = Builder.CreateAnd(Features, Mask);
12743  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Bitset, Mask);
12744  Result = Builder.CreateAnd(Result, Cmp);
12745  }
12746 
12747  if (Features2 != 0) {
12748  llvm::Constant *CpuFeatures2 = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(Int32Ty,
12749  "__cpu_features2");
12750  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CpuFeatures2)->setDSOLocal(true);
12751 
12752  Value *Features = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Int32Ty, CpuFeatures2,
12753  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
12754 
12755  // Check the value of the bit corresponding to the feature requested.
12756  Value *Mask = Builder.getInt32(Features2);
12757  Value *Bitset = Builder.CreateAnd(Features, Mask);
12758  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Bitset, Mask);
12759  Result = Builder.CreateAnd(Result, Cmp);
12760  }
12761 
12762  return Result;
12763 }
12764 
12765 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86CpuInit() {
12766  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy,
12767  /*Variadic*/ false);
12768  llvm::FunctionCallee Func =
12769  CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cpu_indicator_init");
12770  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Func.getCallee())->setDSOLocal(true);
12771  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Func.getCallee())
12772  ->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
12773  return Builder.CreateCall(Func);
12774 }
12775 
12776 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitX86BuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
12777  const CallExpr *E) {
12778  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__builtin_cpu_is)
12779  return EmitX86CpuIs(E);
12780  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__builtin_cpu_supports)
12781  return EmitX86CpuSupports(E);
12782  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__builtin_cpu_init)
12783  return EmitX86CpuInit();
12784 
12785  // Handle MSVC intrinsics before argument evaluation to prevent double
12786  // evaluation.
12787  if (Optional<MSVCIntrin> MsvcIntId = translateX86ToMsvcIntrin(BuiltinID))
12788  return EmitMSVCBuiltinExpr(*MsvcIntId, E);
12789 
12790  SmallVector<Value*, 4> Ops;
12791  bool IsMaskFCmp = false;
12792  bool IsConjFMA = false;
12793 
12794  // Find out if any arguments are required to be integer constant expressions.
12795  unsigned ICEArguments = 0;
12796  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError Error;
12797  getContext().GetBuiltinType(BuiltinID, Error, &ICEArguments);
12798  assert(Error == ASTContext::GE_None && "Should not codegen an error");
12799 
12800  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; i++) {
12801  // If this is a normal argument, just emit it as a scalar.
12802  if ((ICEArguments & (1 << i)) == 0) {
12803  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
12804  continue;
12805  }
12806 
12807  // If this is required to be a constant, constant fold it so that we know
12808  // that the generated intrinsic gets a ConstantInt.
12809  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
12810  getLLVMContext(), *E->getArg(i)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext())));
12811  }
12812 
12813  // These exist so that the builtin that takes an immediate can be bounds
12814  // checked by clang to avoid passing bad immediates to the backend. Since
12815  // AVX has a larger immediate than SSE we would need separate builtins to
12816  // do the different bounds checking. Rather than create a clang specific
12817  // SSE only builtin, this implements eight separate builtins to match gcc
12818  // implementation.
12819  auto getCmpIntrinsicCall = [this, &Ops](Intrinsic::ID ID, unsigned Imm) {
12820  Ops.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Imm));
12821  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
12822  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
12823  };
12824 
12825  // For the vector forms of FP comparisons, translate the builtins directly to
12826  // IR.
12827  // TODO: The builtins could be removed if the SSE header files used vector
12828  // extension comparisons directly (vector ordered/unordered may need
12829  // additional support via __builtin_isnan()).
12830  auto getVectorFCmpIR = [this, &Ops, E](CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
12831  bool IsSignaling) {
12832  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
12833  Value *Cmp;
12834  if (IsSignaling)
12835  Cmp = Builder.CreateFCmpS(Pred, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
12836  else
12837  Cmp = Builder.CreateFCmp(Pred, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
12838  llvm::VectorType *FPVecTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ops[0]->getType());
12839  llvm::VectorType *IntVecTy = llvm::VectorType::getInteger(FPVecTy);
12840  Value *Sext = Builder.CreateSExt(Cmp, IntVecTy);
12841  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Sext, FPVecTy);
12842  };
12843 
12844  switch (BuiltinID) {
12845  default: return nullptr;
12846  case X86::BI_mm_prefetch: {
12847  Value *Address = Ops[0];
12848  ConstantInt *C = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1]);
12849  Value *RW = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, (C->getZExtValue() >> 2) & 0x1);
12850  Value *Locality = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, C->getZExtValue() & 0x3);
12851  Value *Data = ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 1);
12852  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::prefetch, Address->getType());
12853  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Address, RW, Locality, Data});
12854  }
12855  case X86::BI_mm_clflush: {
12856  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_clflush),
12857  Ops[0]);
12858  }
12859  case X86::BI_mm_lfence: {
12860  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_lfence));
12861  }
12862  case X86::BI_mm_mfence: {
12863  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_mfence));
12864  }
12865  case X86::BI_mm_sfence: {
12866  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse_sfence));
12867  }
12868  case X86::BI_mm_pause: {
12869  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_pause));
12870  }
12871  case X86::BI__rdtsc: {
12872  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_rdtsc));
12873  }
12874  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_rdtscp: {
12875  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_rdtscp));
12876  Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 1),
12877  Ops[0]);
12878  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
12879  }
12880  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_lzcnt_u16:
12881  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_lzcnt_u32:
12882  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_lzcnt_u64: {
12883  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctlz, Ops[0]->getType());
12884  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Builder.getInt1(false)});
12885  }
12886  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tzcnt_u16:
12887  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tzcnt_u32:
12888  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_tzcnt_u64: {
12889  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cttz, Ops[0]->getType());
12890  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Builder.getInt1(false)});
12891  }
12892  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_undef128:
12893  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_undef256:
12894  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_undef512:
12895  // The x86 definition of "undef" is not the same as the LLVM definition
12896  // (PR32176). We leave optimizing away an unnecessary zero constant to the
12897  // IR optimizer and backend.
12898  // TODO: If we had a "freeze" IR instruction to generate a fixed undef
12899  // value, we should use that here instead of a zero.
12900  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(E->getType()));
12901  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_init_v8qi:
12902  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_init_v4hi:
12903  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_init_v2si:
12904  return Builder.CreateBitCast(BuildVector(Ops),
12905  llvm::Type::getX86_MMXTy(getLLVMContext()));
12906  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v2si:
12907  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v16qi:
12908  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v8hi:
12909  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4si:
12910  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4sf:
12911  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v2di:
12912  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v32qi:
12913  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v16hi:
12914  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v8si:
12915  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_ext_v4di: {
12916  unsigned NumElts =
12917  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
12918  uint64_t Index = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1])->getZExtValue();
12919  Index &= NumElts - 1;
12920  // These builtins exist so we can ensure the index is an ICE and in range.
12921  // Otherwise we could just do this in the header file.
12922  return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Ops[0], Index);
12923  }
12924  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v16qi:
12925  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v8hi:
12926  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v4si:
12927  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v2di:
12928  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v32qi:
12929  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v16hi:
12930  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v8si:
12931  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vec_set_v4di: {
12932  unsigned NumElts =
12933  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
12934  unsigned Index = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue();
12935  Index &= NumElts - 1;
12936  // These builtins exist so we can ensure the index is an ICE and in range.
12937  // Otherwise we could just do this in the header file.
12938  return Builder.CreateInsertElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], Index);
12939  }
12940  case X86::BI_mm_setcsr:
12941  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_ldmxcsr: {
12942  Address Tmp = CreateMemTemp(E->getArg(0)->getType());
12943  Builder.CreateStore(Ops[0], Tmp);
12944  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse_ldmxcsr),
12945  Builder.CreateBitCast(Tmp.getPointer(), Int8PtrTy));
12946  }
12947  case X86::BI_mm_getcsr:
12948  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_stmxcsr: {
12949  Address Tmp = CreateMemTemp(E->getType());
12950  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::x86_sse_stmxcsr),
12951  Builder.CreateBitCast(Tmp.getPointer(), Int8PtrTy));
12952  return Builder.CreateLoad(Tmp, "stmxcsr");
12953  }
12954  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsave:
12955  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsave64:
12956  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xrstor:
12957  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xrstor64:
12958  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsaveopt:
12959  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsaveopt64:
12960  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xrstors:
12961  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xrstors64:
12962  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsavec:
12963  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsavec64:
12964  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsaves:
12965  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsaves64:
12966  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_xsetbv:
12967  case X86::BI_xsetbv: {
12968  Intrinsic::ID ID;
12969 #define INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(NAME) \
12970  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_##NAME: \
12971  ID = Intrinsic::x86_##NAME; \
12972  break
12973  switch (BuiltinID) {
12974  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported intrinsic!");
12975  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsave);
12976  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsave64);
12977  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xrstor);
12978  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xrstor64);
12979  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsaveopt);
12980  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsaveopt64);
12981  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xrstors);
12982  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xrstors64);
12983  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsavec);
12984  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsavec64);
12985  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsaves);
12986  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsaves64);
12987  INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID(xsetbv);
12988  case X86::BI_xsetbv:
12989  ID = Intrinsic::x86_xsetbv;
12990  break;
12991  }
12992 #undef INTRINSIC_X86_XSAVE_ID
12993  Value *Mhi = Builder.CreateTrunc(
12994  Builder.CreateLShr(Ops[1], ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32)), Int32Ty);
12995  Value *Mlo = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[1], Int32Ty);
12996  Ops[1] = Mhi;
12997  Ops.push_back(Mlo);
12998  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID), Ops);
12999  }

13765  // lanes, emit zero.

13780  for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) {

13782  if (Idx >= 16)
13783  Idx += NumElts - 16; // End of lane, switch operand.
13784  Indices[l + i] = Idx + l;
13785  }
13786  }
13787 
13788  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[1], Ops[0],
13789  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),

13811  "valign");
13812  }
13813  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_f32x4_256:
13814  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_f64x2_256:
13815  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_i32x4_256:
13816  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_i64x2_256:
13817  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_f32x4:
13818  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_f64x2:
13819  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_i32x4:
13820  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_shuf_i64x2: {
13821  unsigned Imm = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue();
13822  auto *Ty = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType());
13823  unsigned NumElts = Ty->getNumElements();
13824  unsigned NumLanes = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 512 ? 4 : 2;
13825  unsigned NumLaneElts = NumElts / NumLanes;
13826 
13827  int Indices[16];
13828  for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += NumLaneElts) {
13829  unsigned Index = (Imm % NumLanes) * NumLaneElts;
13830  Imm /= NumLanes; // Discard the bits we just used.
13831  if (l >= (NumElts / 2))
13832  Index += NumElts; // Switch to other source.
13833  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumLaneElts; ++i) {
13834  Indices[l + i] = Index + i;
13835  }
13836  }
13837 
13838  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[1],
13839  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
13840  "shuf");
13841  }
13842 
13843  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vperm2f128_pd256:
13844  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vperm2f128_ps256:
13845  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vperm2f128_si256:
13846  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_permti256: {
13847  unsigned Imm = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue();
13848  unsigned NumElts =
13849  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
13850 
13851  // This takes a very simple approach since there are two lanes and a
13852  // shuffle can have 2 inputs. So we reserve the first input for the first
13853  // lane and the second input for the second lane. This may result in
13854  // duplicate sources, but this can be dealt with in the backend.
13855 
13856  Value *OutOps[2];
13857  int Indices[8];
13858  for (unsigned l = 0; l != 2; ++l) {
13859  // Determine the source for this lane.
13860  if (Imm & (1 << ((l * 4) + 3)))
13861  OutOps[l] = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ops[0]->getType());
13862  else if (Imm & (1 << ((l * 4) + 1)))
13863  OutOps[l] = Ops[1];
13864  else
13865  OutOps[l] = Ops[0];
13866 
13867  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts/2; ++i) {
13868  // Start with ith element of the source for this lane.
13869  unsigned Idx = (l * NumElts) + i;
13870  // If bit 0 of the immediate half is set, switch to the high half of
13871  // the source.
13872  if (Imm & (1 << (l * 4)))
13873  Idx += NumElts/2;
13874  Indices[(l * (NumElts/2)) + i] = Idx;
13875  }
13876  }
13877 
13878  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(OutOps[0], OutOps[1],
13879  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
13880  "vperm");
13881  }

13883  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_pslldqi128_byteshift:
13884  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_pslldqi256_byteshift:
13885  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_pslldqi512_byteshift: {
13886  unsigned ShiftVal = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[1])->getZExtValue() & 0xff;
13887  auto *ResultType = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType());
13888  // Builtin type is vXi64 so multiply by 8 to get bytes.
13889  unsigned NumElts = ResultType->getNumElements() * 8;
13890 
13891  // If pslldq is shifting the vector more than 15 bytes, emit zero.
13892  if (ShiftVal >= 16)
13893  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResultType);
13894 
13895  int Indices[64];
13896  // 256/512-bit pslldq operates on 128-bit lanes so we need to handle that
13897  for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += 16) {
13898  for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) {
13899  unsigned Idx = NumElts + i - ShiftVal;
13900  if (Idx < NumElts) Idx -= NumElts - 16; // end of lane, switch operand.
13901  Indices[l + i] = Idx + l;
13902  }
13903  }
13904 
13905  auto *VecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int8Ty, NumElts);
13906  Value *Cast = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], VecTy, "cast");
13907  Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
13908  Value *SV = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Zero, Cast,
13909  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
13910  "pslldq");
13911  return Builder.CreateBitCast(SV, Ops[0]->getType(), "cast");
13912  }

14255  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_kunpckdi:
14256  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_kunpcksi:
14257  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_kunpckhi: {
14258  unsigned NumElts = Ops[0]->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth();
14259  Value *LHS = getMaskVecValue(*this, Ops[0], NumElts);
14260  Value *RHS = getMaskVecValue(*this, Ops[1], NumElts);
14261  int Indices[64];
14262  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
14263  Indices[i] = i;
14264 
14265  // First extract half of each vector. This gives better codegen than
14266  // doing it in a single shuffle.
14267  LHS = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(LHS, LHS,
14268  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts / 2));
14269  RHS = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(RHS, RHS,
14270  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts / 2));
14271  // Concat the vectors.
14272  // NOTE: Operands are swapped to match the intrinsic definition.
14273  Value *Res = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(RHS, LHS,
14274  makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts));
14275  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, Ops[0]->getType());
14276  }
