14673  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpmultishiftqb256:
14674  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpmultishiftqb512: {
14675  Intrinsic::ID ID;
14676  switch (BuiltinID) {
14677  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported intrinsic!");
14678  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpmultishiftqb128:
14679  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pmultishift_qb_128;
14680  break;
14681  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpmultishiftqb256:
14682  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pmultishift_qb_256;
14683  break;
14684  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpmultishiftqb512:
14685  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_pmultishift_qb_512;
14686  break;
14687  }
14688 
14689  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID), Ops);
14690  }
14691 
14692  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb128_mask:
14693  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb256_mask:
14694  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb512_mask: {
14695  unsigned NumElts =
14696  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
14697  Value *MaskIn = Ops[2];
14698  Ops.erase(&Ops[2]);
14699 
14700  Intrinsic::ID ID;
14701  switch (BuiltinID) {
14702  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported intrinsic!");
14703  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb128_mask:
14704  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpshufbitqmb_128;
14705  break;
14706  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb256_mask:
14707  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpshufbitqmb_256;
14708  break;
14709  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vpshufbitqmb512_mask:
14710  ID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpshufbitqmb_512;
14711  break;
14712  }
14713 
14714  Value *Shufbit = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID), Ops);
14715  return EmitX86MaskedCompareResult(*this, Shufbit, NumElts, MaskIn);
14716  }
14717 
14718  // packed comparison intrinsics
14719  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpeqps:
14720  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpeqpd:
14721  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ, /*IsSignaling*/false);
14722  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpltps:
14723  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpltpd:
14724  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_OLT, /*IsSignaling*/true);
14725  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpleps:
14726  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmplepd:
14727  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_OLE, /*IsSignaling*/true);
14728  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpunordps:
14729  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpunordpd:
14730  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_UNO, /*IsSignaling*/false);
14731  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpneqps:
14732  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpneqpd:
14733  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, /*IsSignaling*/false);
14734  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnltps:
14735  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnltpd:
14736  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_UGE, /*IsSignaling*/true);
14737  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnleps:
14738  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnlepd:
14739  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_UGT, /*IsSignaling*/true);
14740  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpordps:
14741  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpordpd:
14742  return getVectorFCmpIR(CmpInst::FCMP_ORD, /*IsSignaling*/false);
14743  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpph128_mask:
14744  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpph256_mask:
14745  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpph512_mask:
14746  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps128_mask:
14747  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps256_mask:
14748  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps512_mask:
14749  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd128_mask:
14750  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd256_mask:
14751  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd512_mask:
14752  IsMaskFCmp = true;
14753  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
14754  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps:
14755  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps256:
14756  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd:
14757  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd256: {
14758  // Lowering vector comparisons to fcmp instructions, while
14759  // ignoring signalling behaviour requested
14760  // ignoring rounding mode requested
14761  // This is only possible if fp-model is not strict and FENV_ACCESS is off.
14762 
14763  // The third argument is the comparison condition, and integer in the
14764  // range [0, 31]
14765  unsigned CC = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Ops[2])->getZExtValue() & 0x1f;
14766 
14767  // Lowering to IR fcmp instruction.
14768  // Ignoring requested signaling behaviour,
14769  // e.g. both _CMP_GT_OS & _CMP_GT_OQ are translated to FCMP_OGT.
14770  FCmpInst::Predicate Pred;
14771  bool IsSignaling;
14772  // Predicates for 16-31 repeat the 0-15 predicates. Only the signalling
14773  // behavior is inverted. We'll handle that after the switch.
14774  switch (CC & 0xf) {
14775  case 0x00: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ; IsSignaling = false; break;
14776  case 0x01: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT; IsSignaling = true; break;
14777  case 0x02: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE; IsSignaling = true; break;
14778  case 0x03: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO; IsSignaling = false; break;
14779  case 0x04: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE; IsSignaling = false; break;
14780  case 0x05: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE; IsSignaling = true; break;
14781  case 0x06: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT; IsSignaling = true; break;
14782  case 0x07: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD; IsSignaling = false; break;
14783  case 0x08: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ; IsSignaling = false; break;
14784  case 0x09: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT; IsSignaling = true; break;
14785  case 0x0a: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE; IsSignaling = true; break;
14786  case 0x0b: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_FALSE; IsSignaling = false; break;
14787  case 0x0c: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE; IsSignaling = false; break;
14788  case 0x0d: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE; IsSignaling = true; break;
14789  case 0x0e: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT; IsSignaling = true; break;
14790  case 0x0f: Pred = FCmpInst::FCMP_TRUE; IsSignaling = false; break;
14791  default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled CC");
14792  }
14793 
14794  // Invert the signalling behavior for 16-31.
14795  if (CC & 0x10)
14796  IsSignaling = !IsSignaling;
14797 
14798  // If the predicate is true or false and we're using constrained intrinsics,
14799  // we don't have a compare intrinsic we can use. Just use the legacy X86
14800  // specific intrinsic.
14801  // If the intrinsic is mask enabled and we're using constrained intrinsics,
14802  // use the legacy X86 specific intrinsic.
14803  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained() &&
14804  (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_TRUE || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_FALSE ||
14805  IsMaskFCmp)) {
14806 
14807  Intrinsic::ID IID;
14808  switch (BuiltinID) {
14809  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected builtin");
14810  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps:
14811  IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ps;
14812  break;
14813  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps256:
14814  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_cmp_ps_256;
14815  break;
14816  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd:
14817  IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_pd;
14818  break;
14819  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd256:
14820  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_cmp_pd_256;
14821  break;
14822  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps512_mask:
14823  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_512;
14824  break;
14825  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd512_mask:
14826  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_512;
14827  break;
14828  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps128_mask:
14829  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_128;
14830  break;
14831  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpps256_mask:
14832  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_256;
14833  break;
14834  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd128_mask:
14835  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_128;
14836  break;
14837  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmppd256_mask:
14838  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_256;
14839  break;
14840  }
14841 
14842  Function *Intr = CGM.getIntrinsic(IID);
14843  if (IsMaskFCmp) {
14844  unsigned NumElts =
14845  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
14846  Ops[3] = getMaskVecValue(*this, Ops[3], NumElts);
14847  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateCall(Intr, Ops);
14848  return EmitX86MaskedCompareResult(*this, Cmp, NumElts, nullptr);
14849  }
14850 
14851  return Builder.CreateCall(Intr, Ops);
14852  }
14853 
14854  // Builtins without the _mask suffix return a vector of integers
14855  // of the same width as the input vectors
14856  if (IsMaskFCmp) {
14857  // We ignore SAE if strict FP is disabled. We only keep precise
14858  // exception behavior under strict FP.
14859  // NOTE: If strict FP does ever go through here a CGFPOptionsRAII
14860  // object will be required.
14861  unsigned NumElts =
14862  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements();
14863  Value *Cmp;
14864  if (IsSignaling)
14865  Cmp = Builder.CreateFCmpS(Pred, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
14866  else
14867  Cmp = Builder.CreateFCmp(Pred, Ops[0], Ops[1]);
14868  return EmitX86MaskedCompareResult(*this, Cmp, NumElts, Ops[3]);
14869  }
14870 
14871  return getVectorFCmpIR(Pred, IsSignaling);
14872  }
14873 
14874  // SSE scalar comparison intrinsics
14875  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpeqss:
14876  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 0);
14877  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpltss:
14878  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 1);
14879  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpless:
14880  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 2);
14881  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpunordss:
14882  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 3);
14883  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpneqss:
14884  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 4);
14885  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnltss:
14886  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 5);
14887  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnless:
14888  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 6);
14889  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpordss:
14890  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse_cmp_ss, 7);
14891  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpeqsd:
14892  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 0);
14893  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpltsd:
14894  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 1);
14895  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmplesd:
14896  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 2);
14897  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpunordsd:
14898  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 3);
14899  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpneqsd:
14900  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 4);
14901  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnltsd:
14902  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 5);
14903  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpnlesd:
14904  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 6);
14905  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cmpordsd:
14906  return getCmpIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cmp_sd, 7);
14907 
14908  // f16c half2float intrinsics
14909  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vcvtph2ps:
14910  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vcvtph2ps256:
14911  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vcvtph2ps_mask:
14912  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vcvtph2ps256_mask:
14913  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vcvtph2ps512_mask: {
14914  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
14915  return EmitX86CvtF16ToFloatExpr(*this, Ops, ConvertType(E->getType()));
14916  }
14917 
14918 // AVX512 bf16 intrinsics
14919  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtneps2bf16_128_mask: {
14920  Ops[2] = getMaskVecValue(
14921  *this, Ops[2],
14922  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Ops[0]->getType())->getNumElements());
14923  Intrinsic::ID IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_mask_cvtneps2bf16_128;
14924  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), Ops);
14925  }
14926  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtsbf162ss_32:
14927  return EmitX86CvtBF16ToFloatExpr(*this, E, Ops);
14928 
14929  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtneps2bf16_256_mask:
14930  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtneps2bf16_512_mask: {
14931  Intrinsic::ID IID;
14932  switch (BuiltinID) {
14933  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported intrinsic!");
14934  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtneps2bf16_256_mask:
14935  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtneps2bf16_256;
14936  break;
14937  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_cvtneps2bf16_512_mask:
14938  IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtneps2bf16_512;
14939  break;
14940  }
14941  Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), Ops[0]);
14942  return EmitX86Select(*this, Ops[2], Res, Ops[1]);
14943  }
14944 
14945  case X86::BI__cpuid:
14946  case X86::BI__cpuidex: {
14947  Value *FuncId = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
14948  Value *SubFuncId = BuiltinID == X86::BI__cpuidex
14949  ? EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2))
14950  : llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0);
14951 
14952  llvm::StructType *CpuidRetTy =
14953  llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty);
14954  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
14955  llvm::FunctionType::get(CpuidRetTy, {Int32Ty, Int32Ty}, false);
14956 
14957  StringRef Asm, Constraints;
14958  if (getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86) {
14959  Asm = "cpuid";
14960  Constraints = "={ax},={bx},={cx},={dx},{ax},{cx}";
14961  } else {
14962  // x86-64 uses %rbx as the base register, so preserve it.
14963  Asm = "xchgq %rbx, ${1:q}\n"
14964  "cpuid\n"
14965  "xchgq %rbx, ${1:q}";
14966  Constraints = "={ax},=r,={cx},={dx},0,2";
14967  }
14968 
14969  llvm::InlineAsm *IA = llvm::InlineAsm::get(FTy, Asm, Constraints,
14970  /*hasSideEffects=*/false);
14971  Value *IACall = Builder.CreateCall(IA, {FuncId, SubFuncId});
14972  Value *BasePtr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
14973  Value *Store = nullptr;
14974  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
14975  Value *Extracted = Builder.CreateExtractValue(IACall, i);
14976  Value *StorePtr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(Int32Ty, BasePtr, i);
14977  Store = Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Extracted, StorePtr, getIntAlign());
14978  }
14979 
14980  // Return the last store instruction to signal that we have emitted the
14981  // the intrinsic.
14982  return Store;
14983  }
14984 
14985  case X86::BI__emul:
14986  case X86::BI__emulu: {
14987  llvm::Type *Int64Ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 64);
14988  bool isSigned = (BuiltinID == X86::BI__emul);
14989  Value *LHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Ops[0], Int64Ty, isSigned);
14990  Value *RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Ops[1], Int64Ty, isSigned);
14991  return Builder.CreateMul(LHS, RHS, "", !isSigned, isSigned);
14992  }
14993  case X86::BI__mulh:
14994  case X86::BI__umulh:
14995  case X86::BI_mul128:
14996  case X86::BI_umul128: {
14997  llvm::Type *ResType = ConvertType(E->getType());
14998  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 128);
14999 
15000  bool IsSigned = (BuiltinID == X86::BI__mulh || BuiltinID == X86::BI_mul128);
15001  Value *LHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Ops[0], Int128Ty, IsSigned);
15002  Value *RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Ops[1], Int128Ty, IsSigned);
15003 
15004  Value *MulResult, *HigherBits;
15005  if (IsSigned) {
15006  MulResult = Builder.CreateNSWMul(LHS, RHS);
15007  HigherBits = Builder.CreateAShr(MulResult, 64);
15008  } else {
15009  MulResult = Builder.CreateNUWMul(LHS, RHS);
15010  HigherBits = Builder.CreateLShr(MulResult, 64);
15011  }
15012  HigherBits = Builder.CreateIntCast(HigherBits, ResType, IsSigned);
15013 
15014  if (BuiltinID == X86::BI__mulh || BuiltinID == X86::BI__umulh)
15015  return HigherBits;
15016 
15017  Address HighBitsAddress = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(2));
15018  Builder.CreateStore(HigherBits, HighBitsAddress);
15019  return Builder.CreateIntCast(MulResult, ResType, IsSigned);
15020  }
15021 
15022  case X86::BI__faststorefence: {
15023  return Builder.CreateFence(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent,
15024  llvm::SyncScope::System);
15025  }
15026  case X86::BI__shiftleft128:
15027  case X86::BI__shiftright128: {
15028  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(
15029  BuiltinID == X86::BI__shiftleft128 ? Intrinsic::fshl : Intrinsic::fshr,
15030  Int64Ty);
15031  // Flip low/high ops and zero-extend amount to matching type.
15032  // shiftleft128(Low, High, Amt) -> fshl(High, Low, Amt)
15033  // shiftright128(Low, High, Amt) -> fshr(High, Low, Amt)
15034  std::swap(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
15035  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[2], Int64Ty);
15036  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15037  }
15038  case X86::BI_ReadWriteBarrier:
15039  case X86::BI_ReadBarrier:
15040  case X86::BI_WriteBarrier: {
15041  return Builder.CreateFence(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent,
15042  llvm::SyncScope::SingleThread);
15043  }
15044 
15045  case X86::BI_AddressOfReturnAddress: {
15046  Function *F =
15047  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::addressofreturnaddress, AllocaInt8PtrTy);
15048  return Builder.CreateCall(F);
15049  }
15050  case X86::BI__stosb: {
15051  // We treat __stosb as a volatile memset - it may not generate "rep stosb"
15052  // instruction, but it will create a memset that won't be optimized away.
15053  return Builder.CreateMemSet(Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2], Align(1), true);
15054  }
15055  case X86::BI__ud2:
15056  // llvm.trap makes a ud2a instruction on x86.
15057  return EmitTrapCall(Intrinsic::trap);
15058  case X86::BI__int2c: {
15059  // This syscall signals a driver assertion failure in x86 NT kernels.
15060  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
15061  llvm::InlineAsm *IA =
15062  llvm::InlineAsm::get(FTy, "int $$0x2c", "", /*hasSideEffects=*/true);
15063  llvm::AttributeList NoReturnAttr = llvm::AttributeList::get(
15064  getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
15065  llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
15066  llvm::CallInst *CI = Builder.CreateCall(IA);
15067  CI->setAttributes(NoReturnAttr);
15068  return CI;
15069  }
15070  case X86::BI__readfsbyte:
15071  case X86::BI__readfsword:
15072  case X86::BI__readfsdword:
15073  case X86::BI__readfsqword: {
15074  llvm::Type *IntTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
15075  Value *Ptr =
15076  Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::get(IntTy, 257));
15077  LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
15078  IntTy, Ptr, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(E->getType()));
15079  Load->setVolatile(true);
15080  return Load;
15081  }
15082  case X86::BI__readgsbyte:
15083  case X86::BI__readgsword:
15084  case X86::BI__readgsdword:
15085  case X86::BI__readgsqword: {
15086  llvm::Type *IntTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
15087  Value *Ptr =
15088  Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Ops[0], llvm::PointerType::get(IntTy, 256));
15089  LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
15090  IntTy, Ptr, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(E->getType()));
15091  Load->setVolatile(true);
15092  return Load;
15093  }
15094  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_encodekey128_u32: {
15095  Intrinsic::ID IID = Intrinsic::x86_encodekey128;
15096 
15097  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), {Ops[0], Ops[1]});
15098 
15099  for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
15100  Value *Extract = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, i + 1);
15101  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Int8Ty, Ops[2], i * 16);
15102  Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(
15103  Ptr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Extract->getType()));
15104  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Extract, Ptr, Align(1));
15105  }
15106 
15107  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15108  }
15109  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_encodekey256_u32: {
15110  Intrinsic::ID IID = Intrinsic::x86_encodekey256;
15111 
15112  Value *Call =
15113  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), {Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2]});
15114 
15115  for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
15116  Value *Extract = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, i + 1);
15117  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Int8Ty, Ops[3], i * 16);
15118  Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(
15119  Ptr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Extract->getType()));
15120  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Extract, Ptr, Align(1));
15121  }
15122 
15123  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15124  }
15125  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesenc128kl_u8:
15126  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdec128kl_u8:
15127  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesenc256kl_u8:
15128  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdec256kl_u8: {
15129  Intrinsic::ID IID;
15130  StringRef BlockName;
15131  switch (BuiltinID) {
15132  default:
15133  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected builtin");
15134  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesenc128kl_u8:
15135  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesenc128kl;
15136  BlockName = "aesenc128kl";
15137  break;
15138  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdec128kl_u8:
15139  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesdec128kl;
15140  BlockName = "aesdec128kl";
15141  break;
15142  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesenc256kl_u8:
15143  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesenc256kl;
15144  BlockName = "aesenc256kl";
15145  break;
15146  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdec256kl_u8:
15147  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesdec256kl;
15148  BlockName = "aesdec256kl";
15149  break;
15150  }
15151 
15152  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), {Ops[1], Ops[2]});
15153 
15154  BasicBlock *NoError =
15155  createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_no_error", this->CurFn);
15156  BasicBlock *Error = createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_error", this->CurFn);
15157  BasicBlock *End = createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_end", this->CurFn);
15158 
15159  Value *Ret = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15160  Value *Succ = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ret, Builder.getInt1Ty());
15161  Value *Out = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 1);
15162  Builder.CreateCondBr(Succ, NoError, Error);
15163 
15164  Builder.SetInsertPoint(NoError);
15165  Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Out, Ops[0]);
15166  Builder.CreateBr(End);
15167 
15168  Builder.SetInsertPoint(Error);
15169  Constant *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Out->getType());
15170  Builder.CreateDefaultAlignedStore(Zero, Ops[0]);
15171  Builder.CreateBr(End);
15172 
15173  Builder.SetInsertPoint(End);
15174  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15175  }
15176  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesencwide128kl_u8:
15177  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdecwide128kl_u8:
15178  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesencwide256kl_u8:
15179  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdecwide256kl_u8: {
15180  Intrinsic::ID IID;
15181  StringRef BlockName;
15182  switch (BuiltinID) {
15183  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesencwide128kl_u8:
15184  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesencwide128kl;
15185  BlockName = "aesencwide128kl";
15186  break;
15187  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdecwide128kl_u8:
15188  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesdecwide128kl;
15189  BlockName = "aesdecwide128kl";
15190  break;
15191  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesencwide256kl_u8:
15192  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesencwide256kl;
15193  BlockName = "aesencwide256kl";
15194  break;
15195  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_aesdecwide256kl_u8:
15196  IID = Intrinsic::x86_aesdecwide256kl;
15197  BlockName = "aesdecwide256kl";
15198  break;
15199  }
15200 
15201  llvm::Type *Ty = FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt64Ty(), 2);
15202  Value *InOps[9];
15203  InOps[0] = Ops[2];
15204  for (int i = 0; i != 8; ++i) {
15205  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Ty, Ops[1], i);
15206  InOps[i + 1] = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Ty, Ptr, Align(16));
15207  }
15208 
15209  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), InOps);
15210 
15211  BasicBlock *NoError =
15212  createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_no_error", this->CurFn);
15213  BasicBlock *Error = createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_error", this->CurFn);
15214  BasicBlock *End = createBasicBlock(BlockName + "_end", this->CurFn);
15215 
15216  Value *Ret = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15217  Value *Succ = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ret, Builder.getInt1Ty());
15218  Builder.CreateCondBr(Succ, NoError, Error);
15219 
15220  Builder.SetInsertPoint(NoError);
15221  for (int i = 0; i != 8; ++i) {
15222  Value *Extract = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, i + 1);
15223  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Extract->getType(), Ops[0], i);
15224  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Extract, Ptr, Align(16));
15225  }
15226  Builder.CreateBr(End);
15227 
15228  Builder.SetInsertPoint(Error);
15229  for (int i = 0; i != 8; ++i) {
15230  Value *Out = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, i + 1);
15231  Constant *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Out->getType());
15232  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Out->getType(), Ops[0], i);
15233  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Zero, Ptr, Align(16));
15234  }
15235  Builder.CreateBr(End);
15236 
15237  Builder.SetInsertPoint(End);
15238  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
15239  }
15240  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcph512_mask:
15241  IsConjFMA = true;
15242  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
15243  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddcph512_mask: {
15244  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsConjFMA
15245  ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfcmadd_cph_512
15246  : Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfmadd_cph_512;
15247  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), Ops);
15248  return EmitX86Select(*this, Ops[3], Call, Ops[0]);
15249  }
15250  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcsh_round_mask:
15251  IsConjFMA = true;
15252  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
15253  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddcsh_round_mask: {
15254  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsConjFMA ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfcmadd_csh
15255  : Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfmadd_csh;
15256  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), Ops);
15257  Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(Ops[3], llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, 1));
15258  return EmitX86Select(*this, And, Call, Ops[0]);
15259  }
15260  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfcmaddcsh_round_mask3:
15261  IsConjFMA = true;
15262  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
15263  case X86::BI__builtin_ia32_vfmaddcsh_round_mask3: {
15264  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsConjFMA ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfcmadd_csh
15265  : Intrinsic::x86_avx512fp16_mask_vfmadd_csh;
15266  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), Ops);
15267  static constexpr int Mask[] = {0, 5, 6, 7};
15268  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Call, Ops[2], Mask);
15269  }
15270  }
15271 }
15272 
15273 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitPPCBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
15274  const CallExpr *E) {
15275  SmallVector<Value*, 4> Ops;
15276 
15277  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; i++) {
15278  if (E->getArg(i)->getType()->isArrayType())
15279  Ops.push_back(EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E->getArg(i)).getPointer());
15280  else
15281  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
15282  }
15283 
15284  Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
15285 
15286  switch (BuiltinID) {
15287  default: return nullptr;
15288 
15289  // __builtin_ppc_get_timebase is GCC 4.8+'s PowerPC-specific name for what we
15290  // call __builtin_readcyclecounter.
15291  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_get_timebase:
15292  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::readcyclecounter));
15293 
15294  // vec_ld, vec_xl_be, vec_lvsl, vec_lvsr
15295  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvx:
15296  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvxl:
15297  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvebx:
15298  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvehx:
15299  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvewx:
15300  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvsl:
15301  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvsr:
15302  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvd2x:
15303  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvw4x:
15304  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvd2x_be:
15305  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvw4x_be:
15306  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvl:
15307  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvll:
15308  {
15309  if(BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvl ||
15310  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvll){
15311  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Int8PtrTy);
15312  }else {
15313  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Int8PtrTy);
15314  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Ops[1], Ops[0]);
15315  Ops.pop_back();
15316  }
15317 
15318  switch (BuiltinID) {
15319  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ld/lvsl/lvsr intrinsic!");
15320  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvx:
15321  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvx;
15322  break;
15323  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvxl:
15324  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvxl;
15325  break;
15326  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvebx:
15327  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvebx;
15328  break;
15329  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvehx:
15330  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvehx;
15331  break;
15332  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvewx:
15333  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvewx;
15334  break;
15335  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvsl:
15336  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvsl;
15337  break;
15338  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_lvsr:
15339  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvsr;
15340  break;
15341  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvd2x:
15342  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvd2x;
15343  break;
15344  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvw4x:
15345  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvw4x;
15346  break;
15347  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvd2x_be:
15348  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvd2x_be;
15349  break;
15350  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvw4x_be:
15351  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvw4x_be;
15352  break;
15353  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvl:
15354  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvl;
15355  break;
15356  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvll:
15357  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvll;
15358  break;
15359  }
15360  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
15361  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "");
15362  }
15363 
15364  // vec_st, vec_xst_be
15365  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvx:
15366  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvxl:
15367  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvebx:
15368  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvehx:
15369  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvewx:
15370  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvd2x:
15371  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvw4x:
15372  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvd2x_be:
15373  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvw4x_be:
15374  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvl:
15375  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvll:
15376  {
15377  if(BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvl ||
15378  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvll ){
15379  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Int8PtrTy);
15380  }else {
15381  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Int8PtrTy);
15382  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Ops[2], Ops[1]);
15383  Ops.pop_back();
15384  }
15385 
15386  switch (BuiltinID) {
15387  default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported st intrinsic!");
15388  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvx:
15389  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_stvx;
15390  break;
15391  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvxl:
15392  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_stvxl;
15393  break;
15394  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvebx:
15395  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_stvebx;
15396  break;
15397  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvehx:
15398  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_stvehx;
15399  break;
15400  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_stvewx:
15401  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_stvewx;
15402  break;
15403  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvd2x:
15404  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvd2x;
15405  break;
15406  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvw4x:
15407  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvw4x;
15408  break;
15409  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvd2x_be:
15410  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvd2x_be;
15411  break;
15412  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvw4x_be:
15413  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvw4x_be;
15414  break;
15415  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvl:
15416  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvl;
15417  break;
15418  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvll:
15419  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvll;
15420  break;
15421  }
15422  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
15423  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "");
15424  }
15425  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_ldrmb: {
15426  // Essentially boils down to performing an unaligned VMX load sequence so
15427  // as to avoid crossing a page boundary and then shuffling the elements
15428  // into the right side of the vector register.
15429  int64_t NumBytes = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1])->getZExtValue();
15430  llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
15431  bool IsLE = getTarget().isLittleEndian();
15432 
15433  // If the user wants the entire vector, just load the entire vector.
15434  if (NumBytes == 16) {
15435  Value *BC = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], ResTy->getPointerTo());
15436  Value *LD =
15437  Builder.CreateLoad(Address(BC, ResTy, CharUnits::fromQuantity(1)));
15438  if (!IsLE)
15439  return LD;
15440 
15441  // Reverse the bytes on LE.
15442  SmallVector<int, 16> RevMask;
15443  for (int Idx = 0; Idx < 16; Idx++)
15444  RevMask.push_back(15 - Idx);
15445  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(LD, LD, RevMask);
15446  }
15447 
15448  llvm::Function *Lvx = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvx);
15449  llvm::Function *Lvs = CGM.getIntrinsic(IsLE ? Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvsr
15450  : Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_lvsl);
15451  llvm::Function *Vperm = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vperm);
15452  Value *HiMem = Builder.CreateGEP(
15453  Int8Ty, Ops[0], ConstantInt::get(Ops[1]->getType(), NumBytes - 1));
15454  Value *LoLd = Builder.CreateCall(Lvx, Ops[0], "ld.lo");
15455  Value *HiLd = Builder.CreateCall(Lvx, HiMem, "ld.hi");
15456  Value *Mask1 = Builder.CreateCall(Lvs, Ops[0], "mask1");
15457 
15458  Ops.clear();
15459  Ops.push_back(IsLE ? HiLd : LoLd);
15460  Ops.push_back(IsLE ? LoLd : HiLd);
15461  Ops.push_back(Mask1);
15462  Value *AllElts = Builder.CreateCall(Vperm, Ops, "shuffle1");
15463  Constant *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(IsLE ? ResTy : AllElts->getType());
15464 
15465  if (IsLE) {
15466  SmallVector<int, 16> Consts;
15467  for (int Idx = 0; Idx < 16; Idx++) {
15468  int Val = (NumBytes - Idx - 1 >= 0) ? (NumBytes - Idx - 1)
15469  : 16 - (NumBytes - Idx);
15470  Consts.push_back(Val);
15471  }
15472  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Builder.CreateBitCast(AllElts, ResTy),
15473  Zero, Consts);
15474  }
15475  SmallVector<Constant *, 16> Consts;
15476  for (int Idx = 0; Idx < 16; Idx++)
15477  Consts.push_back(Builder.getInt8(NumBytes + Idx));
15478  Value *Mask2 = ConstantVector::get(Consts);
15479  return Builder.CreateBitCast(
15480  Builder.CreateCall(Vperm, {Zero, AllElts, Mask2}, "shuffle2"), ResTy);
15481  }
15482  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_strmb: {
15483  int64_t NumBytes = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1])->getZExtValue();
15484  bool IsLE = getTarget().isLittleEndian();
15485  auto StoreSubVec = [&](unsigned Width, unsigned Offset, unsigned EltNo) {
15486  // Storing the whole vector, simply store it on BE and reverse bytes and
15487  // store on LE.
15488  if (Width == 16) {
15489  Value *BC =
15490  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Ops[2]->getType()->getPointerTo());
15491  Value *StVec = Ops[2];
15492  if (IsLE) {
15493  SmallVector<int, 16> RevMask;
15494  for (int Idx = 0; Idx < 16; Idx++)
15495  RevMask.push_back(15 - Idx);
15496  StVec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[2], Ops[2], RevMask);
15497  }
15498  return Builder.CreateStore(
15499  StVec, Address(BC, Ops[2]->getType(), CharUnits::fromQuantity(1)));
15500  }
15501  auto *ConvTy = Int64Ty;
15502  unsigned NumElts = 0;
15503  switch (Width) {
15504  default:
15505  llvm_unreachable("width for stores must be a power of 2");
15506  case 8:
15507  ConvTy = Int64Ty;
15508  NumElts = 2;
15509  break;
15510  case 4:
15511  ConvTy = Int32Ty;
15512  NumElts = 4;
15513  break;
15514  case 2:
15515  ConvTy = Int16Ty;
15516  NumElts = 8;
15517  break;
15518  case 1:
15519  ConvTy = Int8Ty;
15520  NumElts = 16;
15521  break;
15522  }
15523  Value *Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(
15524  Ops[2], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ConvTy, NumElts));
15525  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Ops[0],
15526  ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, Offset));
15527  Value *PtrBC = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, ConvTy->getPointerTo());
15528  Value *Elt = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, EltNo);
15529  if (IsLE && Width > 1) {
15530  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bswap, ConvTy);
15531  Elt = Builder.CreateCall(F, Elt);
15532  }
15533  return Builder.CreateStore(
15534  Elt, Address(PtrBC, ConvTy, CharUnits::fromQuantity(1)));
15535  };
15536  unsigned Stored = 0;
15537  unsigned RemainingBytes = NumBytes;
15538  Value *Result;
15539  if (NumBytes == 16)
15540  return StoreSubVec(16, 0, 0);
15541  if (NumBytes >= 8) {
15542  Result = StoreSubVec(8, NumBytes - 8, IsLE ? 0 : 1);
15543  RemainingBytes -= 8;
15544  Stored += 8;
15545  }
15546  if (RemainingBytes >= 4) {
15547  Result = StoreSubVec(4, NumBytes - Stored - 4,
15548  IsLE ? (Stored >> 2) : 3 - (Stored >> 2));
15549  RemainingBytes -= 4;
15550  Stored += 4;
15551  }
15552  if (RemainingBytes >= 2) {
15553  Result = StoreSubVec(2, NumBytes - Stored - 2,
15554  IsLE ? (Stored >> 1) : 7 - (Stored >> 1));
15555  RemainingBytes -= 2;
15556  Stored += 2;
15557  }
15558  if (RemainingBytes)
15559  Result =
15560  StoreSubVec(1, NumBytes - Stored - 1, IsLE ? Stored : 15 - Stored);
15561  return Result;
15562  }
15563  // Square root
15564  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvsqrtsp:
15565  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvsqrtdp: {
15566  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15567  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15568  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
15569  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(
15570  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt, ResultType);
15571  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, X);
15572  } else {
15573  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sqrt, ResultType);
15574  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
15575  }
15576  }
15577  // Count leading zeros
15578  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vclzb:
15579  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vclzh:
15580  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vclzw:
15581  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vclzd: {
15582  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15583  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15584  Value *Undef = ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), false);
15585  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctlz, ResultType);
15586  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Undef});
15587  }
15588  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vctzb:
15589  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vctzh:
15590  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vctzw:
15591  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vctzd: {
15592  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15593  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15594  Value *Undef = ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), false);
15595  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cttz, ResultType);
15596  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Undef});
15597  }
15598  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_elt:
15599  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_unaligned: {
15600  // The third argument of vec_replace_elt and vec_replace_unaligned must
15601  // be a compile time constant and will be emitted either to the vinsw
15602  // or vinsd instruction.
15603  ConstantInt *ArgCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2]);
15604  assert(ArgCI &&
15605  "Third Arg to vinsw/vinsd intrinsic must be a constant integer!");
15606  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15607  llvm::Function *F = nullptr;
15608  Value *Call = nullptr;
15609  int64_t ConstArg = ArgCI->getSExtValue();
15610  unsigned ArgWidth = Ops[1]->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
15611  bool Is32Bit = false;
15612  assert((ArgWidth == 32 || ArgWidth == 64) && "Invalid argument width");
15613  // The input to vec_replace_elt is an element index, not a byte index.
15614  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_elt)
15615  ConstArg *= ArgWidth / 8;
15616  if (ArgWidth == 32) {
15617  Is32Bit = true;
15618  // When the second argument is 32 bits, it can either be an integer or
15619  // a float. The vinsw intrinsic is used in this case.
15620  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vinsw);
15621  // Fix the constant according to endianess.
15622  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian())
15623  ConstArg = 12 - ConstArg;
15624  } else {
15625  // When the second argument is 64 bits, it can either be a long long or
15626  // a double. The vinsd intrinsic is used in this case.
15627  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vinsd);
15628  // Fix the constant for little endian.
15629  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian())
15630  ConstArg = 8 - ConstArg;
15631  }
15632  Ops[2] = ConstantInt::getSigned(Int32Ty, ConstArg);
15633  // Depending on ArgWidth, the input vector could be a float or a double.
15634  // If the input vector is a float type, bitcast the inputs to integers. Or,
15635  // if the input vector is a double, bitcast the inputs to 64-bit integers.
15636  if (!Ops[1]->getType()->isIntegerTy(ArgWidth)) {
15637  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(
15638  Ops[0], Is32Bit ? llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int32Ty, 4)
15639  : llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15640  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Is32Bit ? Int32Ty : Int64Ty);
15641  }
15642  // Emit the call to vinsw or vinsd.
15643  Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15644  // Depending on the builtin, bitcast to the approriate result type.
15645  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_elt &&
15646  !Ops[1]->getType()->isIntegerTy())
15647  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Call, ResultType);
15648  else if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vec_replace_elt &&
15649  Ops[1]->getType()->isIntegerTy())
15650  return Call;
15651  else
15652  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Call,
15653  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int8Ty, 16));
15654  }
15655  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vpopcntb:
15656  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vpopcnth:
15657  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vpopcntw:
15658  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vpopcntd: {
15659  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15660  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15661  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctpop, ResultType);
15662  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
15663  }
15664  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vadduqm:
15665  case PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vsubuqm: {
15666  llvm::Type *Int128Ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(getLLVMContext(), 128);
15667  Ops[0] =
15668  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int128Ty, 1));
15669  Ops[1] =
15670  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int128Ty, 1));
15671  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_altivec_vadduqm)
15672  return Builder.CreateAdd(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vadduqm");
15673  else
15674  return Builder.CreateSub(Ops[0], Ops[1], "vsubuqm");
15675  }
15676  // Rotate and insert under mask operation.
15677  // __rldimi(rs, is, shift, mask)
15678  // (rotl64(rs, shift) & mask) | (is & ~mask)
15679  // __rlwimi(rs, is, shift, mask)
15680  // (rotl(rs, shift) & mask) | (is & ~mask)
15681  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rldimi:
15682  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rlwimi: {
15683  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[0]->getType();
15684  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fshl, Ty);
15685  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rldimi)
15686  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateZExt(Ops[2], Int64Ty);
15687  Value *Shift = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[0], Ops[2]});
15688  Value *X = Builder.CreateAnd(Shift, Ops[3]);
15689  Value *Y = Builder.CreateAnd(Ops[1], Builder.CreateNot(Ops[3]));
15690  return Builder.CreateOr(X, Y);
15691  }
15692  // Rotate and insert under mask operation.
15693  // __rlwnm(rs, shift, mask)
15694  // rotl(rs, shift) & mask
15695  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rlwnm: {
15696  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[0]->getType();
15697  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fshl, Ty);
15698  Value *Shift = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[0], Ops[1]});
15699  return Builder.CreateAnd(Shift, Ops[2]);
15700  }
15701  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_poppar4:
15702  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_poppar8: {
15703  llvm::Type *ArgType = Ops[0]->getType();
15704  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctpop, ArgType);
15705  Value *Tmp = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops[0]);
15706 
15707  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15708  Value *Result = Builder.CreateAnd(Tmp, llvm::ConstantInt::get(ArgType, 1));
15709  if (Result->getType() != ResultType)
15710  Result = Builder.CreateIntCast(Result, ResultType, /*isSigned*/true,
15711  "cast");
15712  return Result;
15713  }
15714  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_cmpb: {
15715  if (getTarget().getTriple().isPPC64()) {
15716  Function *F =
15717  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_cmpb, {Int64Ty, Int64Ty, Int64Ty});
15718  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "cmpb");
15719  }
15720  // For 32 bit, emit the code as below:
15721  // %conv = trunc i64 %a to i32
15722  // %conv1 = trunc i64 %b to i32
15723  // %shr = lshr i64 %a, 32
15724  // %conv2 = trunc i64 %shr to i32
15725  // %shr3 = lshr i64 %b, 32
15726  // %conv4 = trunc i64 %shr3 to i32
15727  // %0 = tail call i32 @llvm.ppc.cmpb32(i32 %conv, i32 %conv1)
15728  // %conv5 = zext i32 %0 to i64
15729  // %1 = tail call i32 @llvm.ppc.cmpb32(i32 %conv2, i32 %conv4)
15730  // %conv614 = zext i32 %1 to i64
15731  // %shl = shl nuw i64 %conv614, 32
15732  // %or = or i64 %shl, %conv5
15733  // ret i64 %or
15734  Function *F =
15735  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_cmpb, {Int32Ty, Int32Ty, Int32Ty});
15736  Value *ArgOneLo = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[0], Int32Ty);
15737  Value *ArgTwoLo = Builder.CreateTrunc(Ops[1], Int32Ty);
15738  Constant *ShiftAmt = ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, 32);
15739  Value *ArgOneHi =
15740  Builder.CreateTrunc(Builder.CreateLShr(Ops[0], ShiftAmt), Int32Ty);
15741  Value *ArgTwoHi =
15742  Builder.CreateTrunc(Builder.CreateLShr(Ops[1], ShiftAmt), Int32Ty);
15743  Value *ResLo = Builder.CreateZExt(
15744  Builder.CreateCall(F, {ArgOneLo, ArgTwoLo}, "cmpb"), Int64Ty);
15745  Value *ResHiShift = Builder.CreateZExt(
15746  Builder.CreateCall(F, {ArgOneHi, ArgTwoHi}, "cmpb"), Int64Ty);
15747  Value *ResHi = Builder.CreateShl(ResHiShift, ShiftAmt);
15748  return Builder.CreateOr(ResLo, ResHi);
15749  }
15750  // Copy sign
15751  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvcpsgnsp:
15752  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvcpsgndp: {
15753  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15754  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15755  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
15756  ID = Intrinsic::copysign;
15757  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID, ResultType);
15758  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y});
15759  }
15760  // Rounding/truncation
15761  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspip:
15762  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpip:
15763  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpim:
15764  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspim:
15765  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpi:
15766  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspi:
15767  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpic:
15768  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspic:
15769  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpiz:
15770  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspiz: {
15771  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15772  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15773  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpim ||
15774  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspim)
15775  ID = Builder.getIsFPConstrained()
15776  ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor
15777  : Intrinsic::floor;
15778  else if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpi ||
15779  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspi)
15780  ID = Builder.getIsFPConstrained()
15781  ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round
15782  : Intrinsic::round;
15783  else if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpic ||
15784  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspic)
15785  ID = Builder.getIsFPConstrained()
15786  ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint
15787  : Intrinsic::rint;
15788  else if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpip ||
15789  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspip)
15790  ID = Builder.getIsFPConstrained()
15791  ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil
15792  : Intrinsic::ceil;
15793  else if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrdpiz ||
15794  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvrspiz)
15795  ID = Builder.getIsFPConstrained()
15796  ? Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc
15797  : Intrinsic::trunc;
15798  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID, ResultType);
15799  return Builder.getIsFPConstrained() ? Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, X)
15800  : Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
15801  }
15802 
15803  // Absolute value
15804  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvabsdp:
15805  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvabssp: {
15806  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15807  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15808  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, ResultType);
15809  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
15810  }
15811 
15812  // Fastmath by default
15813  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_recipdivf:
15814  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_recipdivd:
15815  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rsqrtf:
15816  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rsqrtd: {
15817  FastMathFlags FMF = Builder.getFastMathFlags();
15818  Builder.getFastMathFlags().setFast();
15819  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15820  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15821 
15822  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_recipdivf ||
15823  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_recipdivd) {
15824  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
15825  Value *FDiv = Builder.CreateFDiv(X, Y, "recipdiv");
15826  Builder.getFastMathFlags() &= (FMF);
15827  return FDiv;
15828  }
15829  auto *One = ConstantFP::get(ResultType, 1.0);
15830  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sqrt, ResultType);
15831  Value *FDiv = Builder.CreateFDiv(One, Builder.CreateCall(F, X), "rsqrt");
15832  Builder.getFastMathFlags() &= (FMF);
15833  return FDiv;
15834  }
15835  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_alignx: {
15836  ConstantInt *AlignmentCI = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[0]);
15837  if (AlignmentCI->getValue().ugt(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment))
15838  AlignmentCI = ConstantInt::get(AlignmentCI->getType(),
15839  llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment);
15840 
15841  emitAlignmentAssumption(Ops[1], E->getArg(1),
15842  /*The expr loc is sufficient.*/ SourceLocation(),
15843  AlignmentCI, nullptr);
15844  return Ops[1];
15845  }
15846  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_rdlam: {
15847  llvm::Type *Ty = Ops[0]->getType();
15848  Value *ShiftAmt = Builder.CreateIntCast(Ops[1], Ty, false);
15849  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fshl, Ty);
15850  Value *Rotate = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Ops[0], ShiftAmt});
15851  return Builder.CreateAnd(Rotate, Ops[2]);
15852  }
15853  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_load2r: {
15854  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_load2r);
15855  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Int8PtrTy);
15856  Value *LoadIntrinsic = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15857  return Builder.CreateTrunc(LoadIntrinsic, Int16Ty);
15858  }
15859  // FMA variations
15860  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fnmsub:
15861  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fnmsubs:
15862  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmaddadp:
15863  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmaddasp:
15864  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmaddadp:
15865  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmaddasp:
15866  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmsubadp:
15867  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmsubasp:
15868  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmsubadp:
15869  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmsubasp: {
15870  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
15871  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
15872  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
15873  Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
15874  llvm::Function *F;
15875  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained())
15876  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, ResultType);
15877  else
15878  F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, ResultType);
15879  switch (BuiltinID) {
15880  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmaddadp:
15881  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmaddasp:
15882  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained())
15883  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, Z});
15884  else
15885  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Z});
15886  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmaddadp:
15887  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmaddasp:
15888  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained())
15889  return Builder.CreateFNeg(
15890  Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, Z}), "neg");
15891  else
15892  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Z}), "neg");
15893  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmsubadp:
15894  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvmsubasp:
15895  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained())
15896  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(
15897  F, {X, Y, Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg")});
15898  else
15899  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg")});
15900  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fnmsub:
15901  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fnmsubs:
15902  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmsubadp:
15903  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xvnmsubasp:
15904  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained())
15905  return Builder.CreateFNeg(
15906  Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(
15907  F, {X, Y, Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg")}),
15908  "neg");
15909  else
15910  return Builder.CreateCall(
15911  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_fnmsub, ResultType), {X, Y, Z});
15912  }
15913  llvm_unreachable("Unknown FMA operation");
15914  return nullptr; // Suppress no-return warning
15915  }
15916 
15917  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_insertword: {
15918  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xxinsertw);
15919 
15920  // Third argument is a compile time constant int. It must be clamped to
15921  // to the range [0, 12].
15922  ConstantInt *ArgCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2]);
15923  assert(ArgCI &&
15924  "Third arg to xxinsertw intrinsic must be constant integer");
15925  const int64_t MaxIndex = 12;
15926  int64_t Index = clamp(ArgCI->getSExtValue(), 0, MaxIndex);
15927 
15928  // The builtin semantics don't exactly match the xxinsertw instructions
15929  // semantics (which ppc_vsx_xxinsertw follows). The builtin extracts the
15930  // word from the first argument, and inserts it in the second argument. The
15931  // instruction extracts the word from its second input register and inserts
15932  // it into its first input register, so swap the first and second arguments.
15933  std::swap(Ops[0], Ops[1]);
15934 
15935  // Need to cast the second argument from a vector of unsigned int to a
15936  // vector of long long.
15937  Ops[1] =
15938  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15939 
15940  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian()) {
15941  // Reverse the double words in the vector we will extract from.
15942  Ops[0] =
15943  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15944  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[0], ArrayRef<int>{1, 0});
15945 
15946  // Reverse the index.
15947  Index = MaxIndex - Index;
15948  }
15949 
15950  // Intrinsic expects the first arg to be a vector of int.
15951  Ops[0] =
15952  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int32Ty, 4));
15953  Ops[2] = ConstantInt::getSigned(Int32Ty, Index);
15954  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15955  }
15956 
15957  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_extractuword: {
15958  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xxextractuw);
15959 
15960  // Intrinsic expects the first argument to be a vector of doublewords.
15961  Ops[0] =
15962  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15963 
15964  // The second argument is a compile time constant int that needs to
15965  // be clamped to the range [0, 12].
15966  ConstantInt *ArgCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1]);
15967  assert(ArgCI &&
15968  "Second Arg to xxextractuw intrinsic must be a constant integer!");
15969  const int64_t MaxIndex = 12;
15970  int64_t Index = clamp(ArgCI->getSExtValue(), 0, MaxIndex);
15971 
15972  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian()) {
15973  // Reverse the index.
15974  Index = MaxIndex - Index;
15975  Ops[1] = ConstantInt::getSigned(Int32Ty, Index);
15976 
15977  // Emit the call, then reverse the double words of the results vector.
15978  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15979 
15980  Value *ShuffleCall =
15981  Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Call, Call, ArrayRef<int>{1, 0});
15982  return ShuffleCall;
15983  } else {
15984  Ops[1] = ConstantInt::getSigned(Int32Ty, Index);
15985  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
15986  }
15987  }
15988 
15989  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxpermdi: {
15990  ConstantInt *ArgCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2]);
15991  assert(ArgCI && "Third arg must be constant integer!");
15992 
15993  unsigned Index = ArgCI->getZExtValue();
15994  Ops[0] =
15995  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15996  Ops[1] =
15997  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int64Ty, 2));
15998 
15999  // Account for endianness by treating this as just a shuffle. So we use the
16000  // same indices for both LE and BE in order to produce expected results in
16001  // both cases.
16002  int ElemIdx0 = (Index & 2) >> 1;
16003  int ElemIdx1 = 2 + (Index & 1);
16004 
16005  int ShuffleElts[2] = {ElemIdx0, ElemIdx1};
16006  Value *ShuffleCall =
16007  Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[1], ShuffleElts);
16008  QualType BIRetType = E->getType();
16009  auto RetTy = ConvertType(BIRetType);
16010  return Builder.CreateBitCast(ShuffleCall, RetTy);
16011  }
16012 
16013  case PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_xxsldwi: {
16014  ConstantInt *ArgCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[2]);
16015  assert(ArgCI && "Third argument must be a compile time constant");
16016  unsigned Index = ArgCI->getZExtValue() & 0x3;
16017  Ops[0] =
16018  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int32Ty, 4));
16019  Ops[1] =
16020  Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int32Ty, 4));
16021 
16022  // Create a shuffle mask
16023  int ElemIdx0;
16024  int ElemIdx1;
16025  int ElemIdx2;
16026  int ElemIdx3;
16027  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian()) {
16028  // Little endian element N comes from element 8+N-Index of the
16029  // concatenated wide vector (of course, using modulo arithmetic on
16030  // the total number of elements).
16031  ElemIdx0 = (8 - Index) % 8;
16032  ElemIdx1 = (9 - Index) % 8;
16033  ElemIdx2 = (10 - Index) % 8;
16034  ElemIdx3 = (11 - Index) % 8;
16035  } else {
16036  // Big endian ElemIdx<N> = Index + N
16037  ElemIdx0 = Index;
16038  ElemIdx1 = Index + 1;
16039  ElemIdx2 = Index + 2;
16040  ElemIdx3 = Index + 3;
16041  }
16042 
16043  int ShuffleElts[4] = {ElemIdx0, ElemIdx1, ElemIdx2, ElemIdx3};
16044  Value *ShuffleCall =
16045  Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[1], ShuffleElts);
16046  QualType BIRetType = E->getType();
16047  auto RetTy = ConvertType(BIRetType);
16048  return Builder.CreateBitCast(ShuffleCall, RetTy);
16049  }
16050 
16051  case PPC::BI__builtin_pack_vector_int128: {
16052  bool isLittleEndian = getTarget().isLittleEndian();
16053  Value *UndefValue =
16054  llvm::UndefValue::get(llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Ops[0]->getType(), 2));
16055  Value *Res = Builder.CreateInsertElement(
16056  UndefValue, Ops[0], (uint64_t)(isLittleEndian ? 1 : 0));
16057  Res = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Res, Ops[1],
16058  (uint64_t)(isLittleEndian ? 0 : 1));
16059  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, ConvertType(E->getType()));
16060  }
16061 
16062  case PPC::BI__builtin_unpack_vector_int128: {
16063  ConstantInt *Index = cast<ConstantInt>(Ops[1]);
16064  Value *Unpacked = Builder.CreateBitCast(
16065  Ops[0], llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ConvertType(E->getType()), 2));
16066 
16067  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian())
16068  Index = ConstantInt::get(Index->getType(), 1 - Index->getZExtValue());
16069 
16070  return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Unpacked, Index);
16071  }
16072 
16073  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_sthcx: {
16074  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_sthcx);
16075  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], Int8PtrTy);
16076  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops[1], Int32Ty);
16077  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
16078  }
16079 
16080  // The PPC MMA builtins take a pointer to a __vector_quad as an argument.
16081  // Some of the MMA instructions accumulate their result into an existing
16082  // accumulator whereas the others generate a new accumulator. So we need to
16083  // use custom code generation to expand a builtin call with a pointer to a
16084  // load (if the corresponding instruction accumulates its result) followed by
16085  // the call to the intrinsic and a store of the result.
16086 #define CUSTOM_BUILTIN(Name, Intr, Types, Accumulate) \
16087  case PPC::BI__builtin_##Name:
16088 #include "clang/Basic/BuiltinsPPC.def"
16089  {
16090  // The first argument of these two builtins is a pointer used to store their
16091  // result. However, the llvm intrinsics return their result in multiple
16092  // return values. So, here we emit code extracting these values from the
16093  // intrinsic results and storing them using that pointer.
16094  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_disassemble_acc ||
16095  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_disassemble_pair ||
16096  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_disassemble_pair) {
16097  unsigned NumVecs = 2;
16098  auto Intrinsic = Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_disassemble_pair;
16099  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_disassemble_acc) {
16100  NumVecs = 4;
16101  Intrinsic = Intrinsic::ppc_mma_disassemble_acc;
16102  }
16103  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic);
16104  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(1));
16105  Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
16106  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Vec});
16107  llvm::Type *VTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Int8Ty, 16);
16108  Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[0], VTy->getPointerTo());
16109  for (unsigned i=0; i<NumVecs; i++) {
16110  Value *Vec = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, i);
16111  llvm::ConstantInt* Index = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, i);
16112  Value *GEP = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(VTy, Ptr, Index);
16113  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Vec, GEP, MaybeAlign(16));
16114  }
16115  return Call;
16116  }
16117  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_build_pair ||
16118  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_build_acc) {
16119  // Reverse the order of the operands for LE, so the
16120  // same builtin call can be used on both LE and BE
16121  // without the need for the programmer to swap operands.
16122  // The operands are reversed starting from the second argument,
16123  // the first operand is the pointer to the pair/accumulator
16124  // that is being built.
16125  if (getTarget().isLittleEndian())
16126  std::reverse(Ops.begin() + 1, Ops.end());
16127  }
16128  bool Accumulate;
16129  switch (BuiltinID) {
16130  #define CUSTOM_BUILTIN(Name, Intr, Types, Acc) \
16131  case PPC::BI__builtin_##Name: \
16132  ID = Intrinsic::ppc_##Intr; \
16133  Accumulate = Acc; \
16134  break;
16135  #include "clang/Basic/BuiltinsPPC.def"
16136  }
16137  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvp ||
16138  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_stxvp ||
16139  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_lxvp ||
16140  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_stxvp) {
16141  if (BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_vsx_lxvp ||
16142  BuiltinID == PPC::BI__builtin_mma_lxvp) {
16143  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[1], Int8PtrTy);
16144  Ops[0] = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Ops[1], Ops[0]);
16145  } else {
16146  Ops[2] = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ops[2], Int8PtrTy);
16147  Ops[1] = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Ops[2], Ops[1]);
16148  }
16149  Ops.pop_back();
16150  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
16151  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "");
16152  }
16153  SmallVector<Value*, 4> CallOps;
16154  if (Accumulate) {
16155  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
16156  Value *Acc = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
16157  CallOps.push_back(Acc);
16158  }
16159  for (unsigned i=1; i<Ops.size(); i++)
16160  CallOps.push_back(Ops[i]);
16161  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
16162  Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, CallOps);
16163  return Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Call, Ops[0], MaybeAlign(64));
16164  }
16165 
16166  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_and_swap:
16167  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_compare_and_swaplp: {
16168  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
16169  Address OldValAddr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(1));
16170  Value *OldVal = Builder.CreateLoad(OldValAddr);
16171  QualType AtomicTy = E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType();
16172  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, AtomicTy);
16173  auto Pair = EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
16174  LV, RValue::get(OldVal), RValue::get(Ops[2]), E->getExprLoc(),
16175  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, true);
16176  // Unlike c11's atomic_compare_exchange, accroding to
16177  // https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/xl-c-and-cpp-aix/16.1?topic=functions-compare-swap-compare-swaplp
16178  // > In either case, the contents of the memory location specified by addr
16179  // > are copied into the memory location specified by old_val_addr.
16180  // But it hasn't specified storing to OldValAddr is atomic or not and
16181  // which order to use. Now following XL's codegen, treat it as a normal
16182  // store.
16183  Value *LoadedVal = Pair.first.getScalarVal();
16184  Builder.CreateStore(LoadedVal, OldValAddr);
16185  return Builder.CreateZExt(Pair.second, Builder.getInt32Ty());
16186  }
16187  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_add:
16188  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_addlp: {
16189  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, AtomicRMWInst::Add, E,
16190  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
16191  }
16192  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_and:
16193  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_andlp: {
16194  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, AtomicRMWInst::And, E,
16195  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
16196  }
16197 
16198  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_or:
16199  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_orlp: {
16200  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, AtomicRMWInst::Or, E,
16201  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
16202  }
16203  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_swap:
16204  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fetch_and_swaplp: {
16205  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, E,
16206  llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
16207  }
16208  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_ldarx:
16209  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_lwarx:
16210  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_lharx:
16211  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_lbarx:
16212  return emitPPCLoadReserveIntrinsic(*this, BuiltinID, E);
16213  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mfspr: {
16214  llvm::Type *RetType = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(VoidPtrTy) == 32
16215  ? Int32Ty
16216  : Int64Ty;
16217  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_mfspr, RetType);
16218  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
16219  }
16220  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtspr: {
16221  llvm::Type *RetType = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(VoidPtrTy) == 32
16222  ? Int32Ty
16223  : Int64Ty;
16224  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_mtspr, RetType);
16225  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops);
16226  }
16227  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_popcntb: {
16228  Value *ArgValue = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16229  llvm::Type *ArgType = ArgValue->getType();
16230  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_popcntb, {ArgType, ArgType});
16231  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Ops, "popcntb");
16232  }
16233  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_mtfsf: {
16234  // The builtin takes a uint32 that needs to be cast to an
16235  // f64 to be passed to the intrinsic.
16236  Value *Cast = Builder.CreateUIToFP(Ops[1], DoubleTy);
16237  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ppc_mtfsf);
16238  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ops[0], Cast}, "");
16239  }
16240 
16241  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_swdiv_nochk:
16242  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_swdivs_nochk: {
16243  FastMathFlags FMF = Builder.getFastMathFlags();
16244  Builder.getFastMathFlags().setFast();
16245  Value *FDiv = Builder.CreateFDiv(Ops[0], Ops[1], "swdiv_nochk");
16246  Builder.getFastMathFlags() &= (FMF);
16247  return FDiv;
16248  }
16249  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fric:
16250  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16251  *this, E, Intrinsic::rint,
16252  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint))
16253  .getScalarVal();
16254  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frim:
16255  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frims:
16256  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16257  *this, E, Intrinsic::floor,
16258  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor))
16259  .getScalarVal();
16260  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frin:
16261  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frins:
16262  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16263  *this, E, Intrinsic::round,
16264  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round))
16265  .getScalarVal();
16266  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frip:
16267  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frips:
16268  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16269  *this, E, Intrinsic::ceil,
16270  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil))
16271  .getScalarVal();
16272  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_friz:
16273  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_frizs:
16274  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16275  *this, E, Intrinsic::trunc,
16276  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc))
16277  .getScalarVal();
16278  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fsqrt:
16279  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_fsqrts:
16280  return RValue::get(emitUnaryMaybeConstrainedFPBuiltin(
16281  *this, E, Intrinsic::sqrt,
16282  Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt))
16283  .getScalarVal();
16284  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_test_data_class: {
16285  llvm::Type *ArgType = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0))->getType();
16286  unsigned IntrinsicID;
16287  if (ArgType->isDoubleTy())
16288  IntrinsicID = Intrinsic::ppc_test_data_class_d;
16289  else if (ArgType->isFloatTy())
16290  IntrinsicID = Intrinsic::ppc_test_data_class_f;
16291  else
16292  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Argument Type");
16293  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID), Ops,
16294  "test_data_class");
16295  }
16296  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_swdiv:
16297  case PPC::BI__builtin_ppc_swdivs:
16298  return Builder.CreateFDiv(Ops[0], Ops[1], "swdiv");
16299  }
16300 }

16302 namespace {
16303 // If \p E is not null pointer, insert address space cast to match return
16304 // type of \p E if necessary.
16305 Value *EmitAMDGPUDispatchPtr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
16306  const CallExpr *E = nullptr) {
16307  auto *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_dispatch_ptr);
16308  auto *Call = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F);
16309  Call->addRetAttr(
16310  Attribute::getWithDereferenceableBytes(Call->getContext(), 64));
16311  Call->addRetAttr(Attribute::getWithAlignment(Call->getContext(), Align(4)));
16312  if (!E)
16313  return Call;
16314  QualType BuiltinRetType = E->getType();
16315  auto *RetTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(CGF.ConvertType(BuiltinRetType));
16316  if (RetTy == Call->getType())
16317  return Call;
16318  return CGF.Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Call, RetTy);
16319 }
16320 
16321 Value *EmitAMDGPUImplicitArgPtr(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
16322  auto *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_implicitarg_ptr);
16323  auto *Call = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F);
16324  Call->addRetAttr(
16325  Attribute::getWithDereferenceableBytes(Call->getContext(), 256));
16326  Call->addRetAttr(Attribute::getWithAlignment(Call->getContext(), Align(8)));
16327  return Call;
16328 }
16329 
16330 // \p Index is 0, 1, and 2 for x, y, and z dimension, respectively.
16331 Value *EmitAMDGPUWorkGroupSize(CodeGenFunction &CGF, unsigned Index) {
16332  bool IsCOV_5 = CGF.getTarget().getTargetOpts().CodeObjectVersion ==
16333  clang::TargetOptions::COV_5;
16334  Constant *Offset;
16335  Value *DP;
16336  if (IsCOV_5) {
16337  // Indexing the implicit kernarg segment.
16338  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, 12 + Index * 2);
16339  DP = EmitAMDGPUImplicitArgPtr(CGF);
16340  } else {
16341  // Indexing the HSA kernel_dispatch_packet struct.
16342  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, 4 + Index * 2);
16343  DP = EmitAMDGPUDispatchPtr(CGF);
16344  }
16345 
16346  auto *GEP = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, DP, Offset);
16347  auto *DstTy =
16348  CGF.Int16Ty->getPointerTo(GEP->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
16349  auto *Cast = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(GEP, DstTy);
16350  auto *LD = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
16351  Address(Cast, CGF.Int16Ty, CharUnits::fromQuantity(2)));
16352  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(CGF.getLLVMContext());
16353  llvm::MDNode *RNode = MDHelper.createRange(APInt(16, 1),
16354  APInt(16, CGF.getTarget().getMaxOpenCLWorkGroupSize() + 1));
16355  LD->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_range, RNode);
16356  LD->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load,
16357  llvm::MDNode::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), None));
16358  return LD;
16359 }
16360 
16361 // \p Index is 0, 1, and 2 for x, y, and z dimension, respectively.
16362 Value *EmitAMDGPUGridSize(CodeGenFunction &CGF, unsigned Index) {
16363  const unsigned XOffset = 12;
16364  auto *DP = EmitAMDGPUDispatchPtr(CGF);
16365  // Indexing the HSA kernel_dispatch_packet struct.
16366  auto *Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, XOffset + Index * 4);
16367  auto *GEP = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, DP, Offset);
16368  auto *DstTy =
16369  CGF.Int32Ty->getPointerTo(GEP->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
16370  auto *Cast = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(GEP, DstTy);
16371  auto *LD = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
16372  Address(Cast, CGF.Int32Ty, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4)));
16373  LD->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load,
16374  llvm::MDNode::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), None));
16375  return LD;
16376 }
16377 } // namespace
16378 
16379 // For processing memory ordering and memory scope arguments of various
16380 // amdgcn builtins.
16381 // \p Order takes a C++11 comptabile memory-ordering specifier and converts
16382 // it into LLVM's memory ordering specifier using atomic C ABI, and writes
16383 // to \p AO. \p Scope takes a const char * and converts it into AMDGCN
16384 // specific SyncScopeID and writes it to \p SSID.
16385 bool CodeGenFunction::ProcessOrderScopeAMDGCN(Value *Order, Value *Scope,
16386  llvm::AtomicOrdering &AO,
16387  llvm::SyncScope::ID &SSID) {
16388  if (isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)) {
16389  int ord = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)->getZExtValue();
16390 
16391  // Map C11/C++11 memory ordering to LLVM memory ordering
16392  assert(llvm::isValidAtomicOrderingCABI(ord));
16393  switch (static_cast<llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI>(ord)) {
16394  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire:
16395  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume:
16396  AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
16397  break;
16398  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release:
16399  AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release;
16400  break;
16401  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel:
16402  AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease;
16403  break;
16404  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst:
16405  AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
16406  break;
16407  case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::relaxed:
16408  AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
16409  break;
16410  }
16411 
16412  StringRef scp;
16413  llvm::getConstantStringInfo(Scope, scp);
16414  SSID = getLLVMContext().getOrInsertSyncScopeID(scp);
16415  return true;
16416  }
16417  return false;
16418 }
16419 
16420 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitAMDGPUBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
16421  const CallExpr *E) {
16422  llvm::AtomicOrdering AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
16423  llvm::SyncScope::ID SSID;
16424  switch (BuiltinID) {
16425  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_scale:
16426  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_scalef: {
16427  // Translate from the intrinsics's struct return to the builtin's out
16428  // argument.
16429 
16430  Address FlagOutPtr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(3));
16431 
16432  llvm::Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16433  llvm::Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16434  llvm::Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16435 
16436  llvm::Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_scale,
16437  X->getType());
16438 
16439  llvm::Value *Tmp = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {X, Y, Z});
16440 
16441  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Tmp, 0);
16442  llvm::Value *Flag = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Tmp, 1);
16443 
16444  llvm::Type *RealFlagType = FlagOutPtr.getElementType();
16445 
16446  llvm::Value *FlagExt = Builder.CreateZExt(Flag, RealFlagType);
16447  Builder.CreateStore(FlagExt, FlagOutPtr);
16448  return Result;
16449  }
16450  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_fmas:
16451  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_fmasf: {
16452  llvm::Value *Src0 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16453  llvm::Value *Src1 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16454  llvm::Value *Src2 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16455  llvm::Value *Src3 = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3));
16456 
16457  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fmas,
16458  Src0->getType());
16459  llvm::Value *Src3ToBool = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Src3);
16460  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Src0, Src1, Src2, Src3ToBool});
16461  }
16462 
16463  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_ds_swizzle:
16464  return emitBinaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_swizzle);
16465  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_mov_dpp8:
16466  return emitBinaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_mov_dpp8);
16467  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_mov_dpp:
16468  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_update_dpp: {
16469  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 6> Args;
16470  for (unsigned I = 0; I != E->getNumArgs(); ++I)
16471  Args.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(I)));
16472  assert(Args.size() == 5 || Args.size() == 6);
16473  if (Args.size() == 5)
16474  Args.insert(Args.begin(), llvm::UndefValue::get(Args[0]->getType()));
16475  Function *F =
16476  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_update_dpp, Args[0]->getType());
16477  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Args);
16478  }
16479  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_fixup:
16480  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_fixupf:
16481  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_div_fixuph:
16482  return emitTernaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fixup);
16483  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_trig_preop:
16484  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_trig_preopf:
16485  return emitFPIntBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_trig_preop);
16486  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rcp:
16487  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rcpf:
16488  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rcph:
16489  return emitUnaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp);
16490  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_sqrt:
16491  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_sqrtf:
16492  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_sqrth:
16493  return emitUnaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_sqrt);
16494  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rsq:
16495  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rsqf:
16496  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rsqh:
16497  return emitUnaryBuiltin(*this, E, Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq);
16498  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_rsq_clamp:

16789  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
16790  }
16791  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc32:
16792  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc64:
16793  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec32:
16794  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec64: {
16795  unsigned BuiltinAtomicOp;
16796  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16797 
16798  switch (BuiltinID) {
16799  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc32:
16800  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_inc64:
16801  BuiltinAtomicOp = Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_inc;
16802  break;
16803  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec32:
16804  case AMDGPU::BI__builtin_amdgcn_atomic_dec64:
16805  BuiltinAtomicOp = Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_dec;
16806  break;
16807  }
16808 
16809  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16810  Value *Val = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16811 
16812  llvm::Function *F =
16813  CGM.getIntrinsic(BuiltinAtomicOp, {ResultType, Ptr->getType()});
16814 
16815  if (ProcessOrderScopeAMDGCN(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2)),
16816  EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(3)), AO, SSID)) {
16817 
16818  // llvm.amdgcn.atomic.inc and llvm.amdgcn.atomic.dec expects ordering and
16819  // scope as unsigned values
16820  Value *MemOrder = Builder.getInt32(static_cast<int>(AO));
16821  Value *MemScope = Builder.getInt32(static_cast<int>(SSID));
16822 
16823  QualType PtrTy = E->getArg(0)->IgnoreImpCasts()->getType();
16824  bool Volatile =
16825  PtrTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType().isVolatileQualified();
16826  Value *IsVolatile = Builder.getInt1(static_cast<bool>(Volatile));
16827 
16828  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ptr, Val, MemOrder, MemScope, IsVolatile});
16829  }
16830  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
16831  }
16832  default:
16833  return nullptr;
16834  }
16835 }
