16837 /// Handle a SystemZ function in which the final argument is a pointer
16838 /// to an int that receives the post-instruction CC value. At the LLVM level
16839 /// this is represented as a function that returns a {result, cc} pair.
16840 static Value *EmitSystemZIntrinsicWithCC(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
16841  unsigned IntrinsicID,
16842  const CallExpr *E) {
16843  unsigned NumArgs = E->getNumArgs() - 1;
16844  SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args(NumArgs);
16845  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumArgs; ++I)
16846  Args[I] = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(I));
16847  Address CCPtr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(NumArgs));
16848  Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID);
16849  Value *Call = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, Args);
16850  Value *CC = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 1);
16851  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CC, CCPtr);
16852  return CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0);
16853 }
16854 
16855 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitSystemZBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
16856  const CallExpr *E) {
16857  switch (BuiltinID) {
16858  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_tbegin: {
16859  Value *TDB = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16860  Value *Control = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0xff0c);
16861  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::s390_tbegin);
16862  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {TDB, Control});
16863  }
16864  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_tbegin_nofloat: {
16865  Value *TDB = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16866  Value *Control = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0xff0c);
16867  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::s390_tbegin_nofloat);
16868  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {TDB, Control});
16869  }
16870  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_tbeginc: {
16871  Value *TDB = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(Int8PtrTy);
16872  Value *Control = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0xff08);
16873  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::s390_tbeginc);
16874  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {TDB, Control});
16875  }
16876  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_tabort: {
16877  Value *Data = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16878  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::s390_tabort);
16879  return Builder.CreateCall(F, Builder.CreateSExt(Data, Int64Ty, "tabort"));
16880  }
16881  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_non_tx_store: {
16882  Value *Address = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16883  Value *Data = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16884  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::s390_ntstg);
16885  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {Data, Address});
16886  }
16887 
16888  // Vector builtins. Note that most vector builtins are mapped automatically
16889  // to target-specific LLVM intrinsics. The ones handled specially here can
16890  // be represented via standard LLVM IR, which is preferable to enable common
16891  // LLVM optimizations.
16892 
16893  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vpopctb:
16894  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vpopcth:
16895  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vpopctf:
16896  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vpopctg: {
16897  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16898  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16899  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctpop, ResultType);
16900  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
16901  }
16902 
16903  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclzb:
16904  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclzh:
16905  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclzf:
16906  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vclzg: {
16907  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16908  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16909  Value *Undef = ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), false);
16910  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctlz, ResultType);
16911  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Undef});
16912  }
16913 
16914  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vctzb:
16915  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vctzh:
16916  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vctzf:
16917  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vctzg: {
16918  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16919  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16920  Value *Undef = ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), false);
16921  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cttz, ResultType);
16922  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Undef});
16923  }
16924 
16925  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfsqsb:
16926  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfsqdb: {
16927  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16928  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16929  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
16930  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt, ResultType);
16931  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, { X });
16932  } else {
16933  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sqrt, ResultType);
16934  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
16935  }
16936  }
16937  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmasb:
16938  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmadb: {
16939  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16940  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16941  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16942  Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16943  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
16944  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, ResultType);
16945  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, Z});
16946  } else {
16947  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, ResultType);
16948  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Z});
16949  }
16950  }
16951  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmssb:
16952  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmsdb: {
16953  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16954  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16955  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16956  Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16957  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
16958  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, ResultType);
16959  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg")});
16960  } else {
16961  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, ResultType);
16962  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg")});
16963  }
16964  }
16965  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfnmasb:
16966  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfnmadb: {
16967  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16968  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16969  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16970  Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16971  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
16972  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, ResultType);
16973  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, Z}), "neg");
16974  } else {
16975  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, ResultType);
16976  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, Z}), "neg");
16977  }
16978  }
16979  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfnmssb:
16980  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfnmsdb: {
16981  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16982  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16983  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
16984  Value *Z = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
16985  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
16986  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma, ResultType);
16987  Value *NegZ = Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "sub");
16988  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y, NegZ}));
16989  } else {
16990  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fma, ResultType);
16991  Value *NegZ = Builder.CreateFNeg(Z, "neg");
16992  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, NegZ}));
16993  }
16994  }
16995  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vflpsb:
16996  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vflpdb: {
16997  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
16998  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
16999  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, ResultType);
17000  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
17001  }
17002  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vflnsb:
17003  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vflndb: {
17004  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
17005  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17006  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, ResultType);
17007  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Builder.CreateCall(F, X), "neg");
17008  }
17009  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfisb:
17010  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfidb: {
17011  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
17012  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17013  // Constant-fold the M4 and M5 mask arguments.
17014  llvm::APSInt M4 = *E->getArg(1)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
17015  llvm::APSInt M5 = *E->getArg(2)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
17016  // Check whether this instance can be represented via a LLVM standard
17017  // intrinsic. We only support some combinations of M4 and M5.
17018  Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
17019  Intrinsic::ID CI;
17020  switch (M4.getZExtValue()) {
17021  default: break;
17022  case 0: // IEEE-inexact exception allowed
17023  switch (M5.getZExtValue()) {
17024  default: break;
17025  case 0: ID = Intrinsic::rint;
17026  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint; break;
17027  }
17028  break;
17029  case 4: // IEEE-inexact exception suppressed
17030  switch (M5.getZExtValue()) {
17031  default: break;
17032  case 0: ID = Intrinsic::nearbyint;
17033  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_nearbyint; break;
17034  case 1: ID = Intrinsic::round;
17035  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round; break;
17036  case 5: ID = Intrinsic::trunc;
17037  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc; break;
17038  case 6: ID = Intrinsic::ceil;
17039  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil; break;
17040  case 7: ID = Intrinsic::floor;
17041  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor; break;
17042  }
17043  break;
17044  }
17045  if (ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
17046  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
17047  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CI, ResultType);
17048  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, X);
17049  } else {
17050  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID, ResultType);
17051  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
17052  }
17053  }
17054  switch (BuiltinID) { // FIXME: constrained version?
17055  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfisb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfisb; break;
17056  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfidb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfidb; break;
17057  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown BuiltinID");
17058  }
17059  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
17060  Value *M4Value = llvm::ConstantInt::get(getLLVMContext(), M4);
17061  Value *M5Value = llvm::ConstantInt::get(getLLVMContext(), M5);
17062  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, M4Value, M5Value});
17063  }
17064  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmaxsb:
17065  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmaxdb: {
17066  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
17067  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17068  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
17069  // Constant-fold the M4 mask argument.
17070  llvm::APSInt M4 = *E->getArg(2)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
17071  // Check whether this instance can be represented via a LLVM standard
17072  // intrinsic. We only support some values of M4.
17073  Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
17074  Intrinsic::ID CI;
17075  switch (M4.getZExtValue()) {
17076  default: break;
17077  case 4: ID = Intrinsic::maxnum;
17078  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_maxnum; break;
17079  }
17080  if (ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
17081  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
17082  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CI, ResultType);
17083  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y});
17084  } else {
17085  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID, ResultType);
17086  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y});
17087  }
17088  }
17089  switch (BuiltinID) {
17090  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmaxsb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfmaxsb; break;
17091  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmaxdb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfmaxdb; break;
17092  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown BuiltinID");
17093  }
17094  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
17095  Value *M4Value = llvm::ConstantInt::get(getLLVMContext(), M4);
17096  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, M4Value});
17097  }
17098  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfminsb:
17099  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmindb: {
17100  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
17101  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17102  Value *Y = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
17103  // Constant-fold the M4 mask argument.
17104  llvm::APSInt M4 = *E->getArg(2)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
17105  // Check whether this instance can be represented via a LLVM standard
17106  // intrinsic. We only support some values of M4.
17107  Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
17108  Intrinsic::ID CI;
17109  switch (M4.getZExtValue()) {
17110  default: break;
17111  case 4: ID = Intrinsic::minnum;
17112  CI = Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_minnum; break;
17113  }
17114  if (ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
17115  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
17116  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(CI, ResultType);
17117  return Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(F, {X, Y});
17118  } else {
17119  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID, ResultType);
17120  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y});
17121  }
17122  }
17123  switch (BuiltinID) {
17124  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfminsb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfminsb; break;
17125  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vfmindb: ID = Intrinsic::s390_vfmindb; break;
17126  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown BuiltinID");
17127  }
17128  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
17129  Value *M4Value = llvm::ConstantInt::get(getLLVMContext(), M4);
17130  return Builder.CreateCall(F, {X, Y, M4Value});
17131  }
17132 
17133  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vlbrh:
17134  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vlbrf:
17135  case SystemZ::BI__builtin_s390_vlbrg: {
17136  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
17137  Value *X = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17138  Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bswap, ResultType);
17139  return Builder.CreateCall(F, X);
17140  }

17232 namespace {
17233 // Helper classes for mapping MMA builtins to particular LLVM intrinsic variant.
17234 struct NVPTXMmaLdstInfo {
17235  unsigned NumResults; // Number of elements to load/store
17236  // Intrinsic IDs for row/col variants. 0 if particular layout is unsupported.
17237  unsigned IID_col;
17238  unsigned IID_row;
17239 };
17240 
17241 #define MMA_INTR(geom_op_type, layout) \
17242  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom_op_type##_##layout##_stride
17243 #define MMA_LDST(n, geom_op_type) \
17244  { n, MMA_INTR(geom_op_type, col), MMA_INTR(geom_op_type, row) }
17245 
17246 static NVPTXMmaLdstInfo getNVPTXMmaLdstInfo(unsigned BuiltinID) {
17247  switch (BuiltinID) {
17248  // FP MMA loads
17249  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_ld_a:
17250  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_load_a_f16);
17251  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_ld_b:
17252  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_load_b_f16);
17253  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_ld_c_f16:
17254  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k16_load_c_f16);
17255  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_ld_c_f32:
17256  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_load_c_f32);
17257  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_ld_a:
17258  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_load_a_f16);
17259  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_ld_b:
17260  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_load_b_f16);
17261  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_ld_c_f16:
17262  return MMA_LDST(4, m32n8k16_load_c_f16);
17263  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_ld_c_f32:
17264  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_load_c_f32);
17265  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_ld_a:
17266  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_load_a_f16);
17267  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_ld_b:
17268  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_load_b_f16);
17269  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_ld_c_f16:
17270  return MMA_LDST(4, m8n32k16_load_c_f16);
17271  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_ld_c_f32:
17272  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_load_c_f32);
17273 
17274  // Integer MMA loads
17275  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_ld_a_s8:
17276  return MMA_LDST(2, m16n16k16_load_a_s8);
17277  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_ld_a_u8:
17278  return MMA_LDST(2, m16n16k16_load_a_u8);
17279  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_ld_b_s8:
17280  return MMA_LDST(2, m16n16k16_load_b_s8);
17281  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_ld_b_u8:
17282  return MMA_LDST(2, m16n16k16_load_b_u8);
17283  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_ld_c:
17284  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_load_c_s32);
17285  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_ld_a_s8:
17286  return MMA_LDST(4, m32n8k16_load_a_s8);
17287  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_ld_a_u8:
17288  return MMA_LDST(4, m32n8k16_load_a_u8);
17289  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_ld_b_s8:
17290  return MMA_LDST(1, m32n8k16_load_b_s8);
17291  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_ld_b_u8:
17292  return MMA_LDST(1, m32n8k16_load_b_u8);
17293  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_ld_c:
17294  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_load_c_s32);
17295  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_ld_a_s8:
17296  return MMA_LDST(1, m8n32k16_load_a_s8);
17297  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_ld_a_u8:
17298  return MMA_LDST(1, m8n32k16_load_a_u8);
17299  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_ld_b_s8:
17300  return MMA_LDST(4, m8n32k16_load_b_s8);
17301  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_ld_b_u8:
17302  return MMA_LDST(4, m8n32k16_load_b_u8);
17303  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_ld_c:
17304  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_load_c_s32);
17305 
17306  // Sub-integer MMA loads.
17307  // Only row/col layout is supported by A/B fragments.
17308  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_ld_a_s4:
17309  return {1, 0, MMA_INTR(m8n8k32_load_a_s4, row)};
17310  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_ld_a_u4:
17311  return {1, 0, MMA_INTR(m8n8k32_load_a_u4, row)};
17312  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_ld_b_s4:
17313  return {1, MMA_INTR(m8n8k32_load_b_s4, col), 0};
17314  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_ld_b_u4:
17315  return {1, MMA_INTR(m8n8k32_load_b_u4, col), 0};
17316  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_ld_c:
17317  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k32_load_c_s32);
17318  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_ld_a_b1:
17319  return {1, 0, MMA_INTR(m8n8k128_load_a_b1, row)};
17320  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_ld_b_b1:
17321  return {1, MMA_INTR(m8n8k128_load_b_b1, col), 0};
17322  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_ld_c:
17323  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k128_load_c_s32);
17324 
17325  // Double MMA loads
17326  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_ld_a:
17327  return MMA_LDST(1, m8n8k4_load_a_f64);
17328  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_ld_b:
17329  return MMA_LDST(1, m8n8k4_load_b_f64);
17330  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_ld_c:
17331  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k4_load_c_f64);
17332 
17333  // Alternate float MMA loads
17334  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m16n16k16_ld_a:
17335  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k16_load_a_bf16);
17336  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m16n16k16_ld_b:
17337  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k16_load_b_bf16);
17338  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m8n32k16_ld_a:
17339  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n32k16_load_a_bf16);
17340  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m8n32k16_ld_b:
17341  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_load_b_bf16);
17342  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m32n8k16_ld_a:
17343  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_load_a_bf16);
17344  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m32n8k16_ld_b:
17345  return MMA_LDST(2, m32n8k16_load_b_bf16);
17346  case NVPTX::BI__mma_tf32_m16n16k8_ld_a:
17347  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k8_load_a_tf32);
17348  case NVPTX::BI__mma_tf32_m16n16k8_ld_b:
17349  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k8_load_b_tf32);
17350  case NVPTX::BI__mma_tf32_m16n16k8_ld_c:
17351  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k8_load_c_f32);
17352 
17353  // NOTE: We need to follow inconsitent naming scheme used by NVCC. Unlike
17354  // PTX and LLVM IR where stores always use fragment D, NVCC builtins always
17355  // use fragment C for both loads and stores.
17356  // FP MMA stores.
17357  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_st_c_f16:
17358  return MMA_LDST(4, m16n16k16_store_d_f16);
17359  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_st_c_f32:
17360  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_store_d_f32);
17361  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_st_c_f16:
17362  return MMA_LDST(4, m32n8k16_store_d_f16);
17363  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_st_c_f32:
17364  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_store_d_f32);
17365  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_st_c_f16:
17366  return MMA_LDST(4, m8n32k16_store_d_f16);
17367  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_st_c_f32:
17368  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_store_d_f32);
17369 
17370  // Integer and sub-integer MMA stores.
17371  // Another naming quirk. Unlike other MMA builtins that use PTX types in the
17372  // name, integer loads/stores use LLVM's i32.
17373  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_st_c_i32:
17374  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k16_store_d_s32);
17375  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_st_c_i32:
17376  return MMA_LDST(8, m32n8k16_store_d_s32);
17377  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_st_c_i32:
17378  return MMA_LDST(8, m8n32k16_store_d_s32);
17379  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_st_c_i32:
17380  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k32_store_d_s32);
17381  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_st_c_i32:
17382  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k128_store_d_s32);
17383 
17384  // Double MMA store
17385  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_st_c_f64:
17386  return MMA_LDST(2, m8n8k4_store_d_f64);
17387 
17388  // Alternate float MMA store
17389  case NVPTX::BI__mma_m16n16k8_st_c_f32:
17390  return MMA_LDST(8, m16n16k8_store_d_f32);
17391 
17392  default:
17393  llvm_unreachable("Unknown MMA builtin");
17394  }
17395 }
17396 #undef MMA_LDST
17397 #undef MMA_INTR
17398 
17399 
17400 struct NVPTXMmaInfo {
17401  unsigned NumEltsA;
17402  unsigned NumEltsB;
17403  unsigned NumEltsC;
17404  unsigned NumEltsD;
17405 
17406  // Variants are ordered by layout-A/layout-B/satf, where 'row' has priority
17407  // over 'col' for layout. The index of non-satf variants is expected to match
17408  // the undocumented layout constants used by CUDA's mma.hpp.
17409  std::array<unsigned, 8> Variants;
17410 
17411  unsigned getMMAIntrinsic(int Layout, bool Satf) {
17412  unsigned Index = Layout + 4 * Satf;
17413  if (Index >= Variants.size())
17414  return 0;
17415  return Variants[Index];
17416  }
17417 };
17418 
17419  // Returns an intrinsic that matches Layout and Satf for valid combinations of
17420  // Layout and Satf, 0 otherwise.
17421 static NVPTXMmaInfo getNVPTXMmaInfo(unsigned BuiltinID) {
17422  // clang-format off
17423 #define MMA_VARIANTS(geom, type) \
17424  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_row_##type, \
17425  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_col_##type, \
17426  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_col_row_##type, \
17427  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_col_col_##type
17428 #define MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(geom, type) \
17429  MMA_VARIANTS(geom, type), \
17430  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_row_##type##_satfinite, \
17431  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_col_##type##_satfinite, \
17432  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_col_row_##type##_satfinite, \
17433  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_col_col_##type##_satfinite
17434 // Sub-integer MMA only supports row.col layout.
17435 #define MMA_VARIANTS_I4(geom, type) \
17436  0, \
17437  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_col_##type, \
17438  0, \
17439  0, \
17440  0, \
17441  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_row_col_##type##_satfinite, \
17442  0, \
17443  0
17444 // b1 MMA does not support .satfinite.
17445 #define MMA_VARIANTS_B1_XOR(geom, type) \
17446  0, \
17447  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_xor_popc_row_col_##type, \
17448  0, \
17449  0, \
17450  0, \
17451  0, \
17452  0, \
17453  0
17454 #define MMA_VARIANTS_B1_AND(geom, type) \
17455  0, \
17456  Intrinsic::nvvm_wmma_##geom##_mma_and_popc_row_col_##type, \
17457  0, \
17458  0, \
17459  0, \
17460  0, \
17461  0, \
17462  0
17463  // clang-format on
17464  switch (BuiltinID) {
17465  // FP MMA
17466  // Note that 'type' argument of MMA_SATF_VARIANTS uses D_C notation, while
17467  // NumEltsN of return value are ordered as A,B,C,D.
17468  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_mma_f16f16:
17469  return {8, 8, 4, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, f16_f16)}}};
17470  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_mma_f32f16:
17471  return {8, 8, 4, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, f32_f16)}}};
17472  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_mma_f16f32:
17473  return {8, 8, 8, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, f16_f32)}}};
17474  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m16n16k16_mma_f32f32:
17475  return {8, 8, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, f32_f32)}}};
17476  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_mma_f16f16:
17477  return {8, 8, 4, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, f16_f16)}}};
17478  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_mma_f32f16:
17479  return {8, 8, 4, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, f32_f16)}}};
17480  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_mma_f16f32:
17481  return {8, 8, 8, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, f16_f32)}}};
17482  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m32n8k16_mma_f32f32:
17483  return {8, 8, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, f32_f32)}}};
17484  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_mma_f16f16:
17485  return {8, 8, 4, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, f16_f16)}}};
17486  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_mma_f32f16:
17487  return {8, 8, 4, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, f32_f16)}}};
17488  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_mma_f16f32:
17489  return {8, 8, 8, 4, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, f16_f32)}}};
17490  case NVPTX::BI__hmma_m8n32k16_mma_f32f32:
17491  return {8, 8, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, f32_f32)}}};
17492 
17493  // Integer MMA
17494  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_mma_s8:
17495  return {2, 2, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, s8)}}};
17496  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m16n16k16_mma_u8:
17497  return {2, 2, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, u8)}}};
17498  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_mma_s8:
17499  return {4, 1, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, s8)}}};
17500  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_mma_u8:
17501  return {4, 1, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, u8)}}};
17502  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_mma_s8:
17503  return {1, 4, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, s8)}}};
17504  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_mma_u8:
17505  return {1, 4, 8, 8, {{MMA_SATF_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, u8)}}};
17506 
17507  // Sub-integer MMA
17508  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_mma_s4:
17509  return {1, 1, 2, 2, {{MMA_VARIANTS_I4(m8n8k32, s4)}}};
17510  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_mma_u4:
17511  return {1, 1, 2, 2, {{MMA_VARIANTS_I4(m8n8k32, u4)}}};
17512  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_xor_popc_b1:
17513  return {1, 1, 2, 2, {{MMA_VARIANTS_B1_XOR(m8n8k128, b1)}}};
17514  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_and_popc_b1:
17515  return {1, 1, 2, 2, {{MMA_VARIANTS_B1_AND(m8n8k128, b1)}}};
17516 
17517  // Double MMA
17518  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_mma_f64:
17519  return {1, 1, 2, 2, {{MMA_VARIANTS(m8n8k4, f64)}}};
17520 
17521  // Alternate FP MMA
17522  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m16n16k16_mma_f32:
17523  return {4, 4, 8, 8, {{MMA_VARIANTS(m16n16k16, bf16)}}};
17524  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m8n32k16_mma_f32:
17525  return {2, 8, 8, 8, {{MMA_VARIANTS(m8n32k16, bf16)}}};
17526  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m32n8k16_mma_f32:
17527  return {8, 2, 8, 8, {{MMA_VARIANTS(m32n8k16, bf16)}}};
17528  case NVPTX::BI__mma_tf32_m16n16k8_mma_f32:
17529  return {4, 4, 8, 8, {{MMA_VARIANTS(m16n16k8, tf32)}}};
17530  default:
17531  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected builtin ID.");
17532  }
17533 #undef MMA_VARIANTS
17534 #undef MMA_SATF_VARIANTS
17535 #undef MMA_VARIANTS_I4
17536 #undef MMA_VARIANTS_B1_AND
17537 #undef MMA_VARIANTS_B1_XOR
17538 }
17539 
17540 } // namespace
17541 
17542 Value *
17543 CodeGenFunction::EmitNVPTXBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID, const CallExpr *E) {
17544  auto MakeLdg = [&](unsigned IntrinsicID) {
17545  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17546  QualType ArgType = E->getArg(0)->getType();
17547  clang::CharUnits Align = CGM.getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(ArgType);
17548  llvm::Type *ElemTy = ConvertTypeForMem(ArgType->getPointeeType());
17549  return Builder.CreateCall(
17550  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, {ElemTy, Ptr->getType()}),
17551  {Ptr, ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt32Ty(), Align.getQuantity())});
17552  };
17553  auto MakeScopedLd = [&](unsigned IntrinsicID) {
17554  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17555  llvm::Type *ElemTy =
17556  ConvertTypeForMem(E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType());
17557  return Builder.CreateCall(
17558  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, {ElemTy, Ptr->getType()}), {Ptr});
17559  };
17560  auto MakeScopedSt = [&](unsigned IntrinsicID) {
17561  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17562  llvm::Type *ElemTy =
17563  ConvertTypeForMem(E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType());
17564  return Builder.CreateCall(
17565  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, {Ptr->getType(), ElemTy}),
17566  {Ptr, EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1))});
17567  };
17568  auto MakeScopedAtomic = [&](unsigned IntrinsicID) {
17569  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17570  llvm::Type *ElemTy =
17571  ConvertTypeForMem(E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType());
17572  return Builder.CreateCall(
17573  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, {ElemTy, Ptr->getType()}),
17574  {Ptr, EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1))});
17575  };
17576  auto MakeScopedCasAtomic = [&](unsigned IntrinsicID) {
17577  Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
17578  llvm::Type *ElemTy =
17579  ConvertTypeForMem(E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType());
17580  return Builder.CreateCall(
17581  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrinsicID, {ElemTy, Ptr->getType()}),
17582  {Ptr, EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)), EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2))});
17583  };
17584  switch (BuiltinID) {
17585 
17586 #define LD_VOLATILE_CASES(ADDR_SPACE) \
17587  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_i: \
17588  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_l: \
17589  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_ll: \
17590  return MakeScopedLd(Intrinsic::nvvm_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_i_volatile); \
17591  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_f: \
17592  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_d: \
17593  return MakeScopedLd(Intrinsic::nvvm_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_f_volatile);
17594 
17595 #define LD_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, ADDR_SPACE) \
17596  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_i: \
17597  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_l: \
17598  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_ll: \
17599  return MakeScopedLd(Intrinsic::nvvm_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_i##ORDER##SCOPE); \
17600  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_f: \
17601  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_d: \
17602  return MakeScopedLd(Intrinsic::nvvm_ld##ADDR_SPACE##_f##ORDER##SCOPE);
17603 
17604 #define LD_CASES_AS(ORDER, SCOPE) \
17605  LD_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _gen) \
17606  LD_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _global) \
17607  LD_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _shared)
17608 
17609 #define LD_CASES_AS_SCOPES(ORDER) \
17610  LD_CASES_AS(ORDER, ) \
17611  LD_CASES_AS(ORDER, _cta) \
17612  LD_CASES_AS(ORDER, _sys)
17613 
17614  LD_CASES_AS_SCOPES()
17615  LD_CASES_AS_SCOPES(_acquire)
17616  LD_VOLATILE_CASES(_gen)
17617  LD_VOLATILE_CASES(_global)
17618  LD_VOLATILE_CASES(_shared)
17619 
17620 #undef LD_VOLATILE_CASES
17621 #undef LD_CASES
17622 #undef LD_CASES_AS
17623 #undef LD_CASES_AS_SCOPES
17624 
17625 #define ST_VOLATILE_CASES(ADDR_SPACE) \
17626  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_st##ADDR_SPACE##_i: \
17627  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_st##ADDR_SPACE##_l: \
17628  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_st##ADDR_SPACE##_ll: \
17629  return MakeScopedSt(Intrinsic::nvvm_st##ADDR_SPACE##_i_volatile); \
17630  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_st##ADDR_SPACE##_f: \
17631  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_volatile_st##ADDR_SPACE##_d: \
17632  return MakeScopedSt(Intrinsic::nvvm_st##ADDR_SPACE##_f_volatile);
17633 
17634 #define ST_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, ADDR_SPACE) \
17635  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_st##ADDR_SPACE##_i: \
17636  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_st##ADDR_SPACE##_l: \
17637  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_st##ADDR_SPACE##_ll: \
17638  return MakeScopedSt(Intrinsic::nvvm_st##ADDR_SPACE##_i##ORDER##SCOPE); \
17639  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_st##ADDR_SPACE##_f: \
17640  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm##ORDER##SCOPE##_st##ADDR_SPACE##_d: \
17641  return MakeScopedSt(Intrinsic::nvvm_st##ADDR_SPACE##_f##ORDER##SCOPE);
17642 
17643 #define ST_CASES_AS(ORDER, SCOPE) \
17644  ST_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _gen) \
17645  ST_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _global) \
17646  ST_CASES(ORDER, SCOPE, _shared)
17647 
17648 #define ST_CASES_AS_SCOPES(ORDER) \
17649  ST_CASES_AS(ORDER, ) \
17650  ST_CASES_AS(ORDER, _cta) \
17651  ST_CASES_AS(ORDER, _sys)
17652 
17653  ST_CASES_AS_SCOPES()
17654  ST_CASES_AS_SCOPES(_release)
17655  ST_VOLATILE_CASES(_gen)
17656  ST_VOLATILE_CASES(_global)
17657  ST_VOLATILE_CASES(_shared)
17658 
17659 #undef ST_VOLATILE_CASES
17660 #undef ST_CASES
17661 #undef ST_CASES_AS
17662 #undef ST_CASES_AS_SCOPES
17663 
17664  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_add_gen_i:
17665  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_add_gen_l:
17666  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_add_gen_ll:
17667  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add, E);
17668 
17669  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_sub_gen_i:
17670  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_sub_gen_l:
17671  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_sub_gen_ll:
17672  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub, E);
17673 
17674  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_and_gen_i:
17675  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_and_gen_l:
17676  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_and_gen_ll:
17677  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::And, E);
17678 
17679  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_or_gen_i:
17680  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_or_gen_l:
17681  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_or_gen_ll:
17682  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Or, E);
17683 
17684  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xor_gen_i:
17685  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xor_gen_l:
17686  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xor_gen_ll:
17687  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xor, E);
17688 
17689  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xchg_gen_i:
17690  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xchg_gen_l:
17691  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_xchg_gen_ll:
17692  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, E);
17693 
17694  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_i:
17695  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_l:
17696  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_ll:
17697  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Max, E);
17698 
17699  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_ui:
17700  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_ul:
17701  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_max_gen_ull:
17702  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::UMax, E);
17703 
17704  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_i:
17705  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_l:
17706  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_ll:
17707  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Min, E);
17708 
17709  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_ui:
17710  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_ul:
17711  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_min_gen_ull:
17712  return MakeBinaryAtomicValue(*this, llvm::AtomicRMWInst::UMin, E);
17713 
17714  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_cas_gen_i:
17715  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_cas_gen_l:
17716  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_cas_gen_ll:
17717  // __nvvm_atom_cas_gen_* should return the old value rather than the
17718  // success flag.
17719  return MakeAtomicCmpXchgValue(*this, E, /*ReturnBool=*/false);
17720 
17721  case NVPTX::BI__nvvm_atom_add_gen_f:

19944  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m32n8k16_mma_u8:
19945  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_mma_s8:
19946  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n32k16_mma_u8:
19947  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_mma_s4:
19948  case NVPTX::BI__imma_m8n8k32_mma_u4:
19949  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_xor_popc_b1:
19950  case NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_and_popc_b1:
19951  case NVPTX::BI__dmma_m8n8k4_mma_f64:
19952  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m16n16k16_mma_f32:
19953  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m8n32k16_mma_f32:
19954  case NVPTX::BI__mma_bf16_m32n8k16_mma_f32:
19955  case NVPTX::BI__mma_tf32_m16n16k8_mma_f32: {
19956  Address Dst = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
19957  Address SrcA = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(1));
19958  Address SrcB = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(2));
19959  Address SrcC = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(3));
19960  Optional<llvm::APSInt> LayoutArg =
19961  E->getArg(4)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
19962  if (!LayoutArg)
19963  return nullptr;
19964  int Layout = LayoutArg->getSExtValue();
19965  if (Layout < 0 || Layout > 3)
19966  return nullptr;
19967  llvm::APSInt SatfArg;
19968  if (BuiltinID == NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_xor_popc_b1 ||
19969  BuiltinID == NVPTX::BI__bmma_m8n8k128_mma_and_popc_b1)
19970  SatfArg = 0; // .b1 does not have satf argument.
19971  else if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> OptSatfArg =
19972  E->getArg(5)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext()))
19973  SatfArg = *OptSatfArg;
19974  else
19975  return nullptr;
19976  bool Satf = SatfArg.getSExtValue();

19978  unsigned IID = MI.getMMAIntrinsic(Layout, Satf);
19979  if (IID == 0) // Unsupported combination of Layout/Satf.
19980  return nullptr;
19981 
19982  SmallVector<Value *, 24> Values;
19983  Function *Intrinsic = CGM.getIntrinsic(IID);
19984  llvm::Type *AType = Intrinsic->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0);
19985  // Load A
19986  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MI.NumEltsA; ++i) {
19987  Value *V = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
19988  SrcA.getElementType(),
19989  Builder.CreateGEP(SrcA.getElementType(), SrcA.getPointer(),
19990  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, i)),
19991  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
19992  Values.push_back(Builder.CreateBitCast(V, AType));
19993  }
19994  // Load B
19995  llvm::Type *BType = Intrinsic->getFunctionType()->getParamType(MI.NumEltsA);
19996  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MI.NumEltsB; ++i) {
19997  Value *V = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
19998  SrcB.getElementType(),
19999  Builder.CreateGEP(SrcB.getElementType(), SrcB.getPointer(),
20000  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, i)),
20001  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
20002  Values.push_back(Builder.CreateBitCast(V, BType));
20003  }
20004  // Load C
20005  llvm::Type *CType =
20006  Intrinsic->getFunctionType()->getParamType(MI.NumEltsA + MI.NumEltsB);
20007  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MI.NumEltsC; ++i) {
20008  Value *V = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
20009  SrcC.getElementType(),
20010  Builder.CreateGEP(SrcC.getElementType(), SrcC.getPointer(),
20011  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, i)),
20012  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
20013  Values.push_back(Builder.CreateBitCast(V, CType));
20014  }
20015  Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic, Values);
20016  llvm::Type *DType = Dst.getElementType();
20017  for (unsigned i = 0; i < MI.NumEltsD; ++i)
20018  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(
20019  Builder.CreateBitCast(Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, i), DType),
20020  Builder.CreateGEP(Dst.getElementType(), Dst.getPointer(),
20021  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, i)),
20022  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
20023  return Result;
20024  }
20025  default:
20026  return nullptr;
20027  }

20030 namespace {
20031 struct BuiltinAlignArgs {
20032  llvm::Value *Src = nullptr;
20033  llvm::Type *SrcType = nullptr;
20034  llvm::Value *Alignment = nullptr;
20035  llvm::Value *Mask = nullptr;
20036  llvm::IntegerType *IntType = nullptr;
20037 
20038  BuiltinAlignArgs(const CallExpr *E, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
20039  QualType AstType = E->getArg(0)->getType();
20040  if (AstType->isArrayType())
20041  Src = CGF.EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E->getArg(0)).getPointer();
20042  else
20043  Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20044  SrcType = Src->getType();
20045  if (SrcType->isPointerTy()) {
20046  IntType = IntegerType::get(
20047  CGF.getLLVMContext(),
20048  CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getIndexTypeSizeInBits(SrcType));
20049  } else {
20050  assert(SrcType->isIntegerTy());
20051  IntType = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcType);
20052  }
20053  Alignment = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
20054  Alignment = CGF.Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(Alignment, IntType, "alignment");
20055  auto *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntType, 1);
20056  Mask = CGF.Builder.CreateSub(Alignment, One, "mask");
20057  }
20058 };
20059 } // namespace
20060 
20061 /// Generate (x & (y-1)) == 0.
20062 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBuiltinIsAligned(const CallExpr *E) {
20063  BuiltinAlignArgs Args(E, *this);
20064  llvm::Value *SrcAddress = Args.Src;
20065  if (Args.SrcType->isPointerTy())
20066  SrcAddress =
20067  Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(Args.Src, Args.IntType, "src_addr");
20068  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
20069  Builder.CreateAnd(SrcAddress, Args.Mask, "set_bits"),
20070  llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Args.IntType), "is_aligned"));
20071 }
20072 
20073 /// Generate (x & ~(y-1)) to align down or ((x+(y-1)) & ~(y-1)) to align up.
20074 /// Note: For pointer types we can avoid ptrtoint/inttoptr pairs by using the
20075 /// llvm.ptrmask instrinsic (with a GEP before in the align_up case).
20076 /// TODO: actually use ptrmask once most optimization passes know about it.
20077 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBuiltinAlignTo(const CallExpr *E, bool AlignUp) {
20078  BuiltinAlignArgs Args(E, *this);
20079  llvm::Value *SrcAddr = Args.Src;
20080  if (Args.Src->getType()->isPointerTy())
20081  SrcAddr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Args.Src, Args.IntType, "intptr");
20082  llvm::Value *SrcForMask = SrcAddr;
20083  if (AlignUp) {
20084  // When aligning up we have to first add the mask to ensure we go over the
20085  // next alignment value and then align down to the next valid multiple.
20086  // By adding the mask, we ensure that align_up on an already aligned
20087  // value will not change the value.
20088  SrcForMask = Builder.CreateAdd(SrcForMask, Args.Mask, "over_boundary");
20089  }
20090  // Invert the mask to only clear the lower bits.
20091  llvm::Value *InvertedMask = Builder.CreateNot(Args.Mask, "inverted_mask");
20092  llvm::Value *Result =
20093  Builder.CreateAnd(SrcForMask, InvertedMask, "aligned_result");
20094  if (Args.Src->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
20095  /// TODO: Use ptrmask instead of ptrtoint+gep once it is optimized well.
20096  // Result = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
20097  // Intrinsic::ptrmask, {Args.SrcType, SrcForMask->getType(), Args.IntType},
20098  // {SrcForMask, NegatedMask}, nullptr, "aligned_result");
20099  Result->setName("aligned_intptr");
20100  llvm::Value *Difference = Builder.CreateSub(Result, SrcAddr, "diff");
20101  // The result must point to the same underlying allocation. This means we
20102  // can use an inbounds GEP to enable better optimization.
20103  Value *Base = EmitCastToVoidPtr(Args.Src);
20104  if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
20105  Result = Builder.CreateGEP(Int8Ty, Base, Difference, "aligned_result");
20106  else
20107  Result = EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(Int8Ty, Base, Difference,
20108  /*SignedIndices=*/true,
20109  /*isSubtraction=*/!AlignUp,
20110  E->getExprLoc(), "aligned_result");
20111  Result = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Result, Args.SrcType);
20112  // Emit an alignment assumption to ensure that the new alignment is
20113  // propagated to loads/stores, etc.
20114  emitAlignmentAssumption(Result, E, E->getExprLoc(), Args.Alignment);
20115  }
20116  assert(Result->getType() == Args.SrcType);
20117  return RValue::get(Result);
20118 }
20119 
20120 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitWebAssemblyBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
20121  const CallExpr *E) {
20122  switch (BuiltinID) {
20123  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_memory_size: {
20124  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
20125  Value *I = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20126  Function *Callee =
20127  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_memory_size, ResultType);
20128  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, I);
20129  }
20130  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_memory_grow: {
20131  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
20132  Value *Args[] = {EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)),
20133  EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1))};
20134  Function *Callee =
20135  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_memory_grow, ResultType);
20136  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args);
20137  }
20138  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_tls_size: {
20139  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
20140  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_tls_size, ResultType);
20141  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee);
20142  }
20143  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_tls_align: {
20144  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
20145  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_tls_align, ResultType);
20146  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee);
20147  }

20549  unsigned IntNo;
20550  switch (BuiltinID) {
20551  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_fma_f32x4:
20552  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_fma_f64x2:
20553  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_fma;
20554  break;
20555  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_fms_f32x4:
20556  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_fms_f64x2:
20557  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_fms;
20558  break;
20559  default:
20560  llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin ID");
20561  }
20562  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntNo, A->getType());
20563  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {A, B, C});
20564  }
20565  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_laneselect_i8x16:
20566  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_laneselect_i16x8:
20567  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_laneselect_i32x4:
20568  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_laneselect_i64x2: {
20569  Value *A = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20570  Value *B = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
20571  Value *C = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2));
20572  Function *Callee =
20573  CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_laneselect, A->getType());
20574  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {A, B, C});
20575  }
20576  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_swizzle_i8x16: {
20577  Value *Src = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20578  Value *Indices = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
20579  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_swizzle);
20580  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {Src, Indices});
20581  }
20582  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_min_f32x4:
20583  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_max_f32x4:
20584  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_min_f64x2:
20585  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_max_f64x2: {
20586  Value *LHS = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20587  Value *RHS = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1));
20588  unsigned IntNo;
20589  switch (BuiltinID) {
20590  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_min_f32x4:
20591  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_min_f64x2:
20592  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_min;
20593  break;
20594  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_max_f32x4:
20595  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_max_f64x2:
20596  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_max;
20597  break;
20598  default:
20599  llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin ID");
20600  }
20601  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntNo, LHS->getType());
20602  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {LHS, RHS});
20603  }
20604  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_s_i32x4_f32x4:
20605  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_u_i32x4_f32x4:
20606  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_s_zero_i32x4_f64x2:
20607  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_u_zero_i32x4_f64x2: {
20608  Value *Vec = EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0));
20609  unsigned IntNo;
20610  switch (BuiltinID) {
20611  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_s_i32x4_f32x4:
20612  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_trunc_signed;
20613  break;
20614  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_u_i32x4_f32x4:
20615  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_trunc_unsigned;
20616  break;
20617  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_s_zero_i32x4_f64x2:
20618  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_trunc_signed_zero;
20619  break;
20620  case WebAssembly::BI__builtin_wasm_relaxed_trunc_u_zero_i32x4_f64x2:
20621  IntNo = Intrinsic::wasm_relaxed_trunc_unsigned_zero;
20622  break;
20623  default:
20624  llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin ID");
20625  }
20626  Function *Callee = CGM.getIntrinsic(IntNo);
20627  return Builder.CreateCall(Callee, {Vec});
20628  }
20629  default:
20630  return nullptr;
20631  }
20632 }
20633 
20634 static std::pair<Intrinsic::ID, unsigned>
20635 getIntrinsicForHexagonNonGCCBuiltin(unsigned BuiltinID) {
20636  struct Info {
20637  unsigned BuiltinID;
20638  Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID;
20639  unsigned VecLen;
20640  };
20641  Info Infos[] = {
20642 #define CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(x,s) \
20643  { Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_##x, Intrinsic::hexagon_##x, s },
20644  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrub_pci, 0)
20645  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrb_pci, 0)
20646  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadruh_pci, 0)
20647  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrh_pci, 0)
20648  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadri_pci, 0)
20649  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrd_pci, 0)
20650  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrub_pcr, 0)
20651  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrb_pcr, 0)
20652  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadruh_pcr, 0)
20653  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrh_pcr, 0)
20654  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadri_pcr, 0)
20655  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(L2_loadrd_pcr, 0)
20656  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerb_pci, 0)
20657  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerh_pci, 0)
20658  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerf_pci, 0)
20659  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storeri_pci, 0)
20660  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerd_pci, 0)
20661  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerb_pcr, 0)
20662  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerh_pcr, 0)
20663  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerf_pcr, 0)
20664  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storeri_pcr, 0)
20665  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(S2_storerd_pcr, 0)
20666  // Legacy builtins that take a vector in place of a vector predicate.
20667  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstoreq, 64)
20668  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorenq, 64)
20669  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorentq, 64)
20670  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorentnq, 64)
20671  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstoreq_128B, 128)
20672  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorenq_128B, 128)
20673  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorentq_128B, 128)
20674  CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING(V6_vmaskedstorentnq_128B, 128)
20675 #include "clang/Basic/BuiltinsHexagonMapCustomDep.def"
20676 #undef CUSTOM_BUILTIN_MAPPING
20677  };
20678 
20679  auto CmpInfo = [] (Info A, Info B) { return A.BuiltinID < B.BuiltinID; };
20680  static const bool SortOnce = (llvm::sort(Infos, CmpInfo), true);
20681  (void)SortOnce;
20682 
20683  const Info *F = std::lower_bound(std::begin(Infos), std::end(Infos),
20684  Info{BuiltinID, 0, 0}, CmpInfo);
20685  if (F == std::end(Infos) || F->BuiltinID != BuiltinID)
20686  return {Intrinsic::not_intrinsic, 0};
20687 
20688  return {F->IntrinsicID, F->VecLen};
20689 }
20690 
20691 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitHexagonBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
20692  const CallExpr *E) {
20693  Intrinsic::ID ID;
20694  unsigned VecLen;
20695  std::tie(ID, VecLen) = getIntrinsicForHexagonNonGCCBuiltin(BuiltinID);
20696 
20697  auto MakeCircOp = [this, E](unsigned IntID, bool IsLoad) {
20698  // The base pointer is passed by address, so it needs to be loaded.
20699  Address A = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
20700  Address BP = Address(Builder.CreateBitCast(
20701  A.getPointer(), Int8PtrPtrTy), Int8PtrTy, A.getAlignment());
20702  llvm::Value *Base = Builder.CreateLoad(BP);
20703  // The treatment of both loads and stores is the same: the arguments for
20704  // the builtin are the same as the arguments for the intrinsic.
20705  // Load:
20706  // builtin(Base, Inc, Mod, Start) -> intr(Base, Inc, Mod, Start)
20707  // builtin(Base, Mod, Start) -> intr(Base, Mod, Start)
20708  // Store:
20709  // builtin(Base, Inc, Mod, Val, Start) -> intr(Base, Inc, Mod, Val, Start)
20710  // builtin(Base, Mod, Val, Start) -> intr(Base, Mod, Val, Start)
20711  SmallVector<llvm::Value*,5> Ops = { Base };
20712  for (unsigned i = 1, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i)
20713  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
20714 
20715  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID), Ops);
20716  // The load intrinsics generate two results (Value, NewBase), stores
20717  // generate one (NewBase). The new base address needs to be stored.
20718  llvm::Value *NewBase = IsLoad ? Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 1)
20719  : Result;
20720  llvm::Value *LV = Builder.CreateBitCast(
20721  EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), NewBase->getType()->getPointerTo());
20722  Address Dest = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(0));
20723  llvm::Value *RetVal =
20724  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(NewBase, LV, Dest.getAlignment());
20725  if (IsLoad)
20726  RetVal = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 0);
20727  return RetVal;
20728  };
20729 
20730  // Handle the conversion of bit-reverse load intrinsics to bit code.
20731  // The intrinsic call after this function only reads from memory and the
20732  // write to memory is dealt by the store instruction.
20733  auto MakeBrevLd = [this, E](unsigned IntID, llvm::Type *DestTy) {
20734  // The intrinsic generates one result, which is the new value for the base
20735  // pointer. It needs to be returned. The result of the load instruction is
20736  // passed to intrinsic by address, so the value needs to be stored.
20737  llvm::Value *BaseAddress =
20738  Builder.CreateBitCast(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), Int8PtrTy);
20739 
20740  // Expressions like &(*pt++) will be incremented per evaluation.
20741  // EmitPointerWithAlignment and EmitScalarExpr evaluates the expression
20742  // per call.
20743  Address DestAddr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(1));
20744  DestAddr = Address(Builder.CreateBitCast(DestAddr.getPointer(), Int8PtrTy),
20745  Int8Ty, DestAddr.getAlignment());
20746  llvm::Value *DestAddress = DestAddr.getPointer();
20747 
20748  // Operands are Base, Dest, Modifier.
20749  // The intrinsic format in LLVM IR is defined as
20750  // { ValueType, i8* } (i8*, i32).
20751  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(
20752  CGM.getIntrinsic(IntID), {BaseAddress, EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(2))});
20753 
20754  // The value needs to be stored as the variable is passed by reference.
20755  llvm::Value *DestVal = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 0);
20756 
20757  // The store needs to be truncated to fit the destination type.
20758  // While i32 and i64 are natively supported on Hexagon, i8 and i16 needs
20759  // to be handled with stores of respective destination type.
20760  DestVal = Builder.CreateTrunc(DestVal, DestTy);
20761 
20762  llvm::Value *DestForStore =
20763  Builder.CreateBitCast(DestAddress, DestVal->getType()->getPointerTo());
20764  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(DestVal, DestForStore, DestAddr.getAlignment());
20765  // The updated value of the base pointer is returned.
20766  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 1);
20767  };
20768 
20769  auto V2Q = [this, VecLen] (llvm::Value *Vec) {
20770  Intrinsic::ID ID = VecLen == 128 ? Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandvrt_128B
20771  : Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandvrt;
20772  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID),
20773  {Vec, Builder.getInt32(-1)});
20774  };
20775  auto Q2V = [this, VecLen] (llvm::Value *Pred) {
20776  Intrinsic::ID ID = VecLen == 128 ? Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandqrt_128B
20777  : Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandqrt;
20778  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID),
20779  {Pred, Builder.getInt32(-1)});
20780  };
20781 
20782  switch (BuiltinID) {
20783  // These intrinsics return a tuple {Vector, VectorPred} in LLVM IR,
20784  // and the corresponding C/C++ builtins use loads/stores to update
20785  // the predicate.
20786  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vaddcarry:
20787  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vaddcarry_128B:
20788  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vsubcarry:
20789  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vsubcarry_128B: {
20790  // Get the type from the 0-th argument.
20791  llvm::Type *VecType = ConvertType(E->getArg(0)->getType());
20792  Address PredAddr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
20793  EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getArg(2)), VecType);
20794  llvm::Value *PredIn = V2Q(Builder.CreateLoad(PredAddr));
20795  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID),
20796  {EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(0)), EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(1)), PredIn});
20797 
20798  llvm::Value *PredOut = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 1);
20799  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Q2V(PredOut), PredAddr.getPointer(),
20800  PredAddr.getAlignment());
20801  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, 0);
20802  }
20803 
20804  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstoreq:
20805  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorenq:
20806  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorentq:
20807  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorentnq:
20808  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstoreq_128B:
20809  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorenq_128B:
20810  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorentq_128B:
20811  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_V6_vmaskedstorentnq_128B: {
20812  SmallVector<llvm::Value*,4> Ops;
20813  const Expr *PredOp = E->getArg(0);
20814  // There will be an implicit cast to a boolean vector. Strip it.
20815  if (auto *Cast = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(PredOp)) {
20816  if (Cast->getCastKind() == CK_BitCast)
20817  PredOp = Cast->getSubExpr();
20818  Ops.push_back(V2Q(EmitScalarExpr(PredOp)));
20819  }
20820  for (int i = 1, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i)
20821  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
20822  return Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(ID), Ops);
20823  }
20824 
20825  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrub_pci:
20826  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrb_pci:
20827  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadruh_pci:
20828  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrh_pci:
20829  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadri_pci:
20830  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrd_pci:
20831  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrub_pcr:
20832  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrb_pcr:
20833  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadruh_pcr:
20834  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrh_pcr:
20835  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadri_pcr:
20836  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_L2_loadrd_pcr:
20837  return MakeCircOp(ID, /*IsLoad=*/true);
20838  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerb_pci:
20839  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerh_pci:
20840  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerf_pci:
20841  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storeri_pci:
20842  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerd_pci:
20843  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerb_pcr:
20844  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerh_pcr:
20845  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerf_pcr:
20846  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storeri_pcr:
20847  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_HEXAGON_S2_storerd_pcr:
20848  return MakeCircOp(ID, /*IsLoad=*/false);
20849  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_ldub:
20850  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrub_pbr, Int8Ty);
20851  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_ldb:
20852  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrb_pbr, Int8Ty);
20853  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_lduh:
20854  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadruh_pbr, Int16Ty);
20855  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_ldh:
20856  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrh_pbr, Int16Ty);
20857  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_ldw:
20858  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadri_pbr, Int32Ty);
20859  case Hexagon::BI__builtin_brev_ldd:
20860  return MakeBrevLd(Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrd_pbr, Int64Ty);
20861  } // switch
20862 
20863  return nullptr;
20864 }
20865 
20866 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitIntelFPGARegBuiltin(const CallExpr *E,
20867  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
20868  const Expr *PtrArg = E->getArg(0);
20869  QualType ArgType = PtrArg->getType();
20870  StringRef AnnotStr = "__builtin_intel_fpga_reg";
20871 
20872  if (ArgType->isRecordType()) {
20873  Address DstAddr = ReturnValue.getValue();
20874  EmitAnyExprToMem(PtrArg, DstAddr, ArgType.getQualifiers(), true);
20875  Address A =
20876  EmitIntelFPGAFieldAnnotations(E->getExprLoc(), DstAddr, AnnotStr);
20877  return RValue::getAggregate(A);
20878  }
20879 
20880  // if scalar type
20881  llvm::Value *V = EmitScalarExpr(PtrArg);
20882 
20883  // llvm.annotation does not accept anything but integer types.
20884  llvm::Type *OrigVType = V->getType();
20885  if (!OrigVType->isIntegerTy()) {
20886  IntegerType *IntTy =
20887  Builder.getIntNTy(CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(OrigVType));
20888  V = Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(V, IntTy);
20889  }
20890  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::annotation,
20891  V->getType());
20892  llvm::Value *AnnotatedV =
20893  EmitAnnotationCall(F, V, AnnotStr, E->getExprLoc());
20894 
20895  if (AnnotatedV->getType() != OrigVType) {
20896  AnnotatedV = Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(AnnotatedV, OrigVType);
20897  }
20898 
20899  return RValue::get(AnnotatedV);
20900 }
20901 
20902 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitIntelFPGAMemBuiltin(const CallExpr *E) {
20903  // Arguments
20904  const Expr *PtrArg = E->getArg(0);
20905  Value *PtrVal = EmitScalarExpr(PtrArg);
20906 
20907  // Create the pointer annotation
20908  Function *F =
20909  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::ptr_annotation, PtrVal->getType());
20910  SmallString<256> AnnotStr;
20911  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(AnnotStr);
20912 
20913  Optional<llvm::APSInt> Params =
20914  E->getArg(1)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
20915  assert(Params.hasValue() && "Constant arg isn't actually constant?");
20916  Out << "{params:" << toString(*Params, 10) << "}";
20917 
20918  Optional<llvm::APSInt> CacheSize =
20919  E->getArg(2)->getIntegerConstantExpr(getContext());
20920  assert(CacheSize.hasValue() && "Constant arg isn't actually constant?");
20921  Out << "{cache-size:" << toString(*CacheSize, 10) << "}";
20922 
20923  llvm::Value *Ann = EmitAnnotationCall(F, PtrVal, AnnotStr, SourceLocation());
20924 
20925  cast<CallBase>(Ann)->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
20926 
20927  return RValue::get(Ann);
20928 }
20929 
20930 Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitRISCVBuiltinExpr(unsigned BuiltinID,
20931  const CallExpr *E,
20932  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
20933  SmallVector<Value *, 4> Ops;
20934  llvm::Type *ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
20935 
20936  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumArgs(); i != e; i++)
20937  Ops.push_back(EmitScalarExpr(E->getArg(i)));
20938 
20939  Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
20940  unsigned NF = 1;
20941  constexpr unsigned TAIL_UNDISTURBED = 0;
20942 
20943  // Required for overloaded intrinsics.
20944  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2> IntrinsicTypes;
20945  switch (BuiltinID) {
20946  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected builtin ID");
20947  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_orc_b_32:
20948  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_orc_b_64:
20949  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_clmul:
20950  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_clmulh:
20951  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_clmulr:
20952  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bcompress_32:
20953  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bcompress_64:
20954  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bdecompress_32:
20955  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bdecompress_64:
20956  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bfp_32:
20957  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_bfp_64:
20958  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_grev_32:
20959  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_grev_64:
20960  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_gorc_32:
20961  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_gorc_64:
20962  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_shfl_32:
20963  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_shfl_64:
20964  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_unshfl_32:
20965  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_unshfl_64:
20966  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_xperm4:
20967  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_xperm8:
20968  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_xperm_n:
20969  case RISCV::BI__builtin_riscv_xperm_b:
